INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',1,'Wandering Whistling Duck','Dendrocygna arcuata','Belibis Merantau','斑胸树鸭','Non-rarity','I','Looks similar to Lesser Whistling Duck but slightly bigger, has pronounced blackish line down centre of nape and hindneck, richer chestnut flanks with very prominent thick black and white markings, black spotted breasts and white vent.','Ponds within gardens and parks.','Gregarious. Flock with the more common and similar looking Lesser Whistling Ducks. Hybrids of the two species have been documented in Singapore.',40.0,45.0,'wet','brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',2,'Lesser Whistling Duck','Dendrocygna javanica','Belibis Kecil','栗树鸭','Non-rarity','R','Distinguished from Wandering Whistling Duck by smaller size, distinctive yellow eyering, very fine whitish plumes at the flanks and reddish-chestnut uppertail-coverts.','Various wetlands like lakes, marshes and ponds.','Very gregarious. Can form big flocks in suitable habitats.',38.0,41.0,'wet','brown/green','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',3,'Cotton Pygmy Goose','Nettapus coromandelianus','Belebas Kapas','棉凫','Rarity','Vi','Male has blackish cap, white head-sides/neck and underparts, grey-washed flanks, glossed green upperparts and blackish collar. Non-breeding male has more greyish head-sides and flanks, a thick eyestripe and no obvious collar. Female and juvenile resemble non-breeding male but has duller/browner plumage.','Marshes and other suitable freshwater wetlands.','Forages for seeds, grass and aquatic plants and will also take insects.',33.0,38.0,'wet','brown/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',4,'Garganey','Spatula querquedula','Itik Kening Putih','白眉鸭','Rarity','Va','Male has mostly dark brownish head and neck with diagnostic bold white supercilium. In flight shows mostly bluish-grey upperwing-coverts and blackish-green secondaries bordered by broad white bands. Female resembles male but has narrow whitish supercilium and large whitish loral patch extending in line below blackish eyestripe.','Lakes, marshes and suitable wetlands.',NULL,36.0,41.0,'wet','brown/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',5,'Northern Shoveler','Spatula clypeata','Itik-Sudu Utara','琵嘴鸭','Rarity','Va','Male has long, wide, spatula-shaped bill, dark green head and upper neck, white breast, chestnut flanks and black tail-coverts. Female and juvenile can be easily distinguished from other duck species from the distinctive bill shape.','Lakes, rivers, marshes and various wetland habitats.','Feeds in very shallow water, using its bill to sift through the mud for minute aquatic animals, plants and seeds.',43.0,52.0,'wet','white/brown/green','feed/swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',6,'Gadwall','Mareca strepera','Itik-Bersiul Kelabu','赤膀鸭','Rarity','Va','Male has greyish overall plumage with contrasting black vent and blackish bill. Female has mostly brown plumage with dark brown markings on back and flanks, greyish head and fine blackish bill with orange sides. Juvenile resembles female but richer brown below.','Rivers, marshes and various freshwater wetland habitats.','Keeps close to waterside vegetation when feeding.',46.0,56.0,'wet','grey/brown/black','feed/swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',7,'Eurasian Wigeon','Mareca penelope','Itik-Bersiul Kepala Merah','赤颈鸭','Rarity','Va','Male has bright chestnut head with broad yellowish median stripe, pinkish breast and mostly greyish remaining of body with black vent. Female has rather plain dark brownish head and neck, shortish pale grey bill with black tip and chestnut-tinged breast and flanks. Juvenile resembles female.','Mudflats, mangroves, marshes and various wetland habitats.','Keeps to shallow waterside vegetation, feeding on small aquatic plants.',45.0,51.0,'wet','grey/brown/black','feed/swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',8,'Northern Pintail','Anas acuta','Itik-Runcing Utara','针尾鸭','Rarity','Va','Male has distinctive long slender neck with dark chocolate-brown head, white lower foreneck and upper breast, black tail-coverts and elongated central tail feathers. Female has long darkish grey bill, plain brown head and pointed tail. Juvenile resembles female but upperparts darker.','Lakes, rivers, marshes and various wetland habitats.','Keeps to shallow water, feeding on minute aquatic animals and plants.',51.0,56.0,'wet','grey','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ducks, Geese, Swans (Anatidae)',9,'Tufted Duck','Aythya fuligula','Itik-Selam Berjambul','凤头潜鸭','Rarity','Va','Male has mostly blackish plumage with contrasting white flanks, drooping crest, greyish bill with black tip, yellowish eyes and dark purplish-glossed head. Female has rather uniform dull dark brownish plumage with paler lower neck, breast and flanks, squarish head and slight nuchal tuft. Juvenile resembles female but has paler head and upperparts.','Lakes, rivers, marshes and various wetland habitats.','Seldom flies off when disturbed, preferring to drift out to deeper parts in centre of water body.',40.0,47.0,'wet','black/brown','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pheasants & Allies (Phasianidae)',10,'Red Junglefowl','Gallus gallus','Ayam-Hutan Biasa','红原鸡','Non-rarity','I/R','Male has red comb, facial skin and lappets, white ear patch, golden-yellow neck feathers, maroon scapulars and arched dark green tail. Female has drab brown overall plumage, golden-buff neck feathers and blunt dark tail.','Forest edge, wooded area, parks and gardens.',NULL,41.0,78.0,'fst/pnr','brown/blue/red','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pheasants & Allies (Phasianidae)',11,'King Quail','Synoicus chinensis','Pikau Biru Asia','蓝胸鹑','Non-rarity','R','Male has slaty-blue head, breasts and flanks, blackish throat with enclosed white malar and throat patches, chestnut lower breast to vent and yellowish-orange legs. Female is larger than male and has buff-orange supercilium and brownish overall plumage with distinctive blackish bars on breast and flanks. Juvenile resembles female.','Dry to slightly marshy grassland and scrub.','Skulking and difficult to flush.',13.0,15.0,'fst','brown/blue','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Nightjars (Caprimulgidae)',12,'Malaysian Eared Nightjar','Lyncornis temminckii','Taptibau Melayu','马来毛腿夜鹰','Rarity','Ex','Adult resembles Long-tailed Nightjar but smaller and has significantly darker overall plumage, inconspicuous ear-tuffs, diagnostic narrow whitish collar and lacks the obvious whitish markings on wings and tail. The call, which is loud and distinctive, is the best way to distinguish it from other nightjar species when seen in flight at dawn or dusk.','Forest in Singapore.',NULL,25.0,28.0,'fst','brown/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Nightjars (Caprimulgidae)',13,'Grey Nightjar','Caprimulgus jotaka','Tukang Kelabu Timur','普通夜鹰','Non-rarity','M','Dark, greyish bird. Smaller and with a darker crown compared to Large-tailed.Male: No rufescent tinge on nape, heavier black vermiculation on upperparts. Smaller white throat patch. Darker breast, scapulars less contrasting, with black, buff and whitish bars overall; show less obvious whitish to buff bars across wing coverts. In flight, small white wing patches and tail patches.Female: Wing patches smaller than male and buff, and lack any obvious white tail patches.','On migration, found in primary forest, secondary growth, plantations and wooded parks.','Usually seen perched on taller tree branches in daytime. Active nighttime.',28.0,32.0,'fst','grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Nightjars (Caprimulgidae)',14,'Large-tailed Nightjar','Caprimulgus macrurus','Tukang Biasa','长尾夜鹰','Non-rarity','R','Male: Largest and most frequently encountered nightjar. Pale crown with dark median stripe, prominent row of black scapulars with broad buff/whitish-buff outer fringes. Large area of white/buffish-white on lower throat. Brownish tail with uneven dark bars. Often showing rufescent tinge to nape. Prominent whitish to buff bars across wing coverts. In flight, large white patches on primaries and distal part of outer tail feathers.Female: Paler and greyer on upperparts and breast. Smaller buff coloured wing patches. Duller buffish/whitish buff tail patches.','Commonly found in secondary forest, forest edge, plantations and wooded parks.','Usually seen ground in daytime. Active in nighttime.',31.5,33.0,'fst','brown/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Nightjars (Caprimulgidae)',15,'Savanna Nightjar','Caprimulgus affinis','Tukang Padang','林夜鹰','Non-rarity','R','Smallest and palest local nightjar. Upperparts uniform and heavily vermiculated brownish-grey. Lesser coverts brown speckled pale buff, rest of wing coverts paler, boldly spotted pale buff, scapulars blackish brown, broadly edged buff/whitish on outer web. Male: White outer tail feathers. Large white wing patches. Distinct roundish white/buff-white patch on each side of throat. Female: Lack white outer tail feathers. Smaller and buff wing patches,','Open grassland, barren land, scrub and sometimes urban areas resting on roofs of buildings.','Usually seen resting ground in daytime. Active in nighttime.',25.0,25.5,'fst/open','brown/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Treeswifts (Hemiprocnidae)',16,'Grey-rumped Treeswift','Hemiprocne longipennis','Layang-layang Berjambul Pinggul Pudar','灰腰凤头雨燕','Non-rarity','R','A rather big swift-like bird with dark glossy greenish crown, nape and mantle, blackish lores, greyish throat, whitish underparts. Tail-tip falls short of primary wing tips when perched. In flight, greyish back and rump contrast with dark mantle and has contrasting blackish underwing coverts. Male has chestnut ear-coverts while female has blackish ear-coverts.','Open habitat, parkland and forested area.','Feed on small insects taken in flight. Usually perch high up on tree.',18.0,21.5,'pnr','grey/green','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Treeswifts (Hemiprocnidae)',17,'Whiskered Treeswift','Hemiprocne comata','Layang-layang Berjambul Kecil','小须凤头雨燕','Rarity','Vi','Resembles Grey-rumped Treeswift but smaller. Body mostly olive-bronze with dark glossy blue crown, nape, upper throat and wings. Long white supercilium and malar streak. Whitish vent. Male has chestnut ear-coverts while female has blackish ear-coverts.','Forested area.','Feed on small insects taken in sallies from a perch.',15.0,16.5,'fst','brown/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',18,'Plume-toed Swiftlet','Collocalia affinis','Layang-layang Kecil Biasa','毛趾金丝燕','Non-rarity','R','A small swiftlet with square tail. Can be easily separate from similar looking Edible-nest Swiftlet and Black-nest Swiftlet by the whitish belly/vent and all black upperparts without any pale rump-band.','Open habitat and forested areas.','Often seen flying/feeding just above the tree line taking various insects in flight.',10.0,10.0,'pnr','black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',19,'Black-nest Swiftlet','Aerodramus maximus','Layang-layang Gua Sarang Hitam','大金丝燕','Non-rarity','I/R','A small swift with blackish-brown upperparts, dull rump-band and paler underparts. Indistinguishable from Edible-nest Swiftlet when seen in flight. Can only be conclusively identified either with a bird in hand to see its heavily feathered tarsals or at its nest which is blackish in colour. It lays only one egg as opposed to two eggs by the Edible-nest Swiftlet.','Recorded over a wide variety of habitats, forests, clearings, coast, lowlands, mountains and also out at sea.','Feed on small insects taken in flight. Gregarious and often forage in big flocks together with other Swiftlets and Swallows.',12.0,13.5,'fst/open/sea','black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',20,'Edible-nest Swiftlet','Aerodramus fuciphagus','Layang-layang Gua Sarang Putih','爪哇金丝燕','Non-rarity','I/R','Indistinguishable from Black-nest Swiftlet when seen in flight. Can only be identified conclusively with a bird in hand (from the lightly feathered to naked tarsi) or at its nest which is all white. Lays two eggs as opposed to one egg of the Black-nest Swiftlet.','Recorded over a wide variety of habitats, forests, clearings, coast, lowlands, mountains and also out at sea.','Feed on small insects taken in flight. Gregarious and often forage in big flocks together with other swiftlet species and swallows.',11.0,12.0,'resd/fst/pnr','black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',21,'Silver-rumped Spinetail','Rhaphidura leucopygialis','Layang-layang Ekor-Pendek Melayu','银腰针尾雨燕','Rarity','Vi','Smaller than the other migratory Needletail species but still look robust with all blackish underparts, dark bluish gloss upperparts, prominent silvery-white lower back, rump and uppertail-coverts, short square-cut tail, very broad paddle-shaped wings and bare shafts (spines) extending from tail-tip. Juvenile has less glossy underparts.','Broadleaved evergreen forest and clearings.','Roosts in large tree hollows in the emergent canopy.',11.0,11.0,'fst/open','black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',22,'White-throated Needletail','Hirundapus caudacutus','Layang-layang Besar Utara','白喉针尾雨燕','Rarity','M','Resembles the other two migratory Needletail species with cigar-shaped body but has the diagnostic clearly defined white throat. Juvenile has less glossy underparts.','Forested and open areas.','Forages aerially and has also been observed to roost in trees.',21.0,22.0,'fst/open','grey/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',23,'Silver-backed Needletail','Hirundapus cochinchinensis','Layang-layang Besar Rengkung Pudar','灰喉针尾雨燕','Rarity','M','Resembles Brown-backed Needletail but centre of saddle distinctively silvery-grey and lacks white spot on lores. Distinguished from White-throated Needletail by the paler, brownish-grey throat patch.','Forested and open areas.','Highly active, only staying at one site for any length of time if drinking or feeding. Often seen in association with Brown-backed Needletail.',20.5,22.0,'fst/open','brown/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',24,'Brown-backed Needletail','Hirundapus giganteus','Layang-layang Besar Biasa','褐背针尾雨燕','Non-rarity','M/Vi','Migratory subspecies indicus looks bulky and has mostly blackish body, distinctive white lower flanks and vent, brownish saddle on lower mantle and white loral spot. The resident subspecies of Thai-Malay Peninsula giganteus is larger than indicus and lacks the white loral spot.','Forested and open areas.','Has fast gliding flight, wings make loud whooshing sound when zooming overhead.',21.0,24.5,'fst/pnr','brown/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',25,'Asian Palm Swift','Cypsiurus balasiensis','Layang-layang Palma Asia','棕雨燕','Non-rarity','R','Resembles common swiftlet from far but has rather uniform greyish brown plumage, pale throat, long slender, sickle-shaped wings and distinctive long, deeply forked tail which appears long, narrow and pointed when closed. Looks very similar but is much smaller, more slender-looking and lack the diagnostic white rump-band of the Pacific Swift.','Open habitat and urban areas.','Feed on small insects egs. flying ants, termites and beetles taken in flight.',11.0,12.0,'resd','black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',26,'Common Swift','Apus apus','Layang-layang Sabit Erasia','普通雨燕','Rarity','Va','A mid-size swift with a typical slender appearance; sickle-shaped wings and a forked tail. In most views appears to be all dark blackish-brown, but the throat and forehead are pale whitish.','An exclusively aerial species on migration over a variety of open habitats.','Feeds on the wing on flying invertebrates.',17.0,17.0,'open','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',27,'Pacific Swift','Apus pacificus','Layang-layang Sabit Asia Timur','白腰雨燕','Non-rarity','M','Brownish upperpart plumage, long sickle-shaped wings and sharply forked tail separate it from House Swift. Distinguished from the similar looking Asian Palm Swift by its larger size, whitish throat and diagnostic white-rump band.','Open habitat and forested areas.','Feed on small insects egs. bees, wasps, termites, moths and flies taken in flight.',18.0,19.5,'fst/pnr','brown/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swifts (Apodidae)',28,'House Swift','Apus nipalensis','Layang-layang Sabit Biasa','小白腰雨燕','Non-rarity','R','Overall blackish plumage with whitish throat, broad clear white rump-band, long scimitar-shaped wings and squarish tail that is only slightly notched.','Forested, open and urban areas.','Feeds on flying insects, mainly flying ants, termites, bees, wasps and beetles. They also go for other tidbits that they can snatch on the wing like spiders.',14.0,15.0,'fst/pnr','black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',29,'Greater Coucal','Centropus sinensis','Bubut Besar Asia','褐翅鸦鹃','Non-rarity','R','Adult is distinctive looking with glossy purplish blue-black plumage and contrasting chestnut back and wings. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller overall plumage with rufous-chestnut streaks on body and blackish bars on wings.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, mangroves, parks and gardens.',NULL,48.0,52.0,'pnr','orange/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',30,'Lesser Coucal','Centropus bengalensis','Bubut Kecil Asia','小鸦鹃','Non-rarity','R','Adult resembles Great Coucal but much smaller, duller and has pale streaks on head, neck and upperparts. Juvenile resembles adult but has brownish overall plumage with whitish-buff streaks and blackish bars on wings.','Grasslands.','Frequently suns itself on bare branches with wings partly outstretched.',38.0,38.0,'wet','orange/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',31,'Chestnut-bellied Malkoha','Phaenicophaeus sumatranus','Cenuk Perut Coklat','棕腹地鹃','Non-rarity','R','Adult is distinctively looking with greyish head and mantle, metallic bluish-grey wings and tail, greyish breast and chestnut rest of underparts, greenish bill and orangey facial skin. Juvenile resembles adult but has shorter tail and duller overall plumage, bill and facial skin.','Forest and forest edge.','Despite being a member of the cuckoo family, malkohas do not lay their eggs in the nests of other birds but instead construct nests and raise their own chicks.',40.0,40.5,'fst','orange/black/green','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',32,'Chestnut-winged Cuckoo','Clamator coromandus','Sewah Berjambul Sayap Coklat','红翅凤头鹃','Non-rarity','M','Adult is distinctive looking with black upperparts and crest, white hindcollar, rufous-chestnut wings, whitish underparts with rufous throat and long slender black tail. Juvenile resembles adult but has whitish throat, dark greenish brown upperparts and less prominent crest.','Wooded areas, mangroves, gardens and parks.',NULL,38.0,41.5,'pnr','orange/black/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',33,'Jacobin Cuckoo','Clamator jacobinus','Sewah Berjambul Hitam-Putih','斑翅凤头鹃','Rarity','Va','Can be easily separated from similar looking Chestnut-winged Cuckoo by smaller size, glossy black hindneck and wings, all-white underparts and small white patch on primaries.','Wooded areas.',NULL,31.5,33.0,'fst','black/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',34,'Asian Koel','Eudynamys scolopaceus','Tahu Asia','噪鹃','Non-rarity','R/Vi','Male resembles crow but has glossy blue-black overall plumage, stout greenish bill and red eyes. Female resembles male but has dark brownish overall plumage with whitish spots on upperparts and streaks/barrings on underparts.','Forest edge, wooded areas, mangroves, parks and gardens.','A known brood parasite of Large-billed Crow and House Crow.',40.0,44.0,'pnr','black/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',35,'Asian Emerald Cuckoo','Chrysococcyx maculatus','Sewah-Zamrud Asia','翠金鹃','Rarity','Va','Distinguished from other male Chrysococcyx cuckoos of Singapore by the glossy golden-tinged emerald-green plumage with white bars on lower breast to vent and dark-tipped yellowish bill. Female has rufous crown/nape and coppery-green wings and tail. Juvenile resembles female but less green above with some dark and buff bars on crown to mantle.','Forest, forest edge, parks and gardens.','Frequents the canopy and crown of tall trees.',17.0,17.0,'fst','green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',36,'Violet Cuckoo','Chrysococcyx xanthorhynchus','Sewah-Zamrud Ungu','紫金鹃','Non-rarity','R','Male has glossy violet-purple head, upper breast and upperparts, white lower breast to vent with dark bars and bright orange bill with red base. Female resembles Bronze Cuckoo and female Asian Emerald Cuckoo but has reddish-bronze (with slight greenish-tinge) forehead, crown, nape and upperparts and red-based yellowish bill. Juvenile resembles female but has a more rufous-chestnut crown.','Forest, forest edge, parks and gardens.','Frequents canopy on crowns of tall trees. A known brood parasite of the Brown-throated Sunbird and Little Spiderhunter.',16.5,17.0,'resd/pnr','black/blue','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',37,'Horsfield''s Bronze Cuckoo','Chrysococcyx basalis','Sewah-Daun Australia','霍氏金鹃','Rarity','M',NULL,'Forest, forest edge, parks and gardens.',NULL,NULL,NULL,'pnr','brown/white/green','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',38,'Little Bronze Cuckoo','Chrysococcyx minutillus','Sewah-Daun Biasa','棕胸金鹃','Non-rarity','R','Male has black bill, pale fore-head, dark bars across whitish underparts, bronzy-green mantle and distinctive red eyering. Female resemble male but has duller mantle and eyering. Juvenile resembles female but has browner upperparts and faint or no bars on flanks.','Secondary growth, coastal scrub, mangroves, gardens and parks.','Laid single egg in the nest of Golden-bellied Gerygone.',16.0,16.0,'fst','brown/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',39,'Banded Bay Cuckoo','Cacomantis sonneratii','Matinak Takuwih','栗斑杜鹃','Non-rarity','R','Adult has rufescent upperparts with blackish bars, very fine barrings on entire of whitish underparts and broad white supercilium. Juvenile resembles adult but has whitish to pale buff bars on head-sides, crown and mantle.','Forest, forest edge, parks and gardens.','Known to brood parasite on Common Iora in Singapore.',23.0,24.0,'pnr/fst','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',40,'Plaintive Cuckoo','Cacomantis merulinus','Matinak Biasa','八声杜鹃','Non-rarity','R','Adult resembles Rusty-breasted Cuckoo but has greyish eyering, head, throat and upper breast with remaining underparts peachy-rufous throat. Juvenile resembles Rusty-breasted Cuckoo but has greyish eyering and finer blackish barrings on underparts.','Forest, forest edge, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Known to brood parasite on Ashy Tailorbirds in Singapore.',21.5,23.5,'pnr/fst','brown/black/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',41,'Rusty-breasted Cuckoo','Cacomantis sepulcralis','Matinak Dada Jingga Biasa','锈胸杜鹃','Non-rarity','R','Adult has greyish head, greyish brown upperparts, peachy-rufous throat and rest of underparts and yellowish eyering. Juvenile has rufescent upperparts with blackish bars, whitish underparts with blackish barrings and yellowish eyering. Female can also occur in a rare hepatic form which resembles juvenile.','Forest, forest edge, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Known to brood parasite on Malaysian Pied Fantail in Singapore.',21.5,24.0,'pnr/fst','brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',42,'Square-tailed Drongo-Cuckoo','Surniculus lugubris','Sewah Sawai Biasa','乌鹃','Non-rarity','M/R','Adult has glossy black overall plumage, slender, slightly downcurved bill and square-cut to slightly forked tail with white barrings on vent and undertail coverts. Juvenile resembles adult but is somewhat browner and has prominent white spots on body and wing-coverts.','The resident species are confined mainly to forest and forest edge but migrants can also be found in mangroves, parks and gardens.','Known to brood parasite on Pin-striped Tit-Babbler and Olive-winged Bulbul in Singapore.',24.5,24.5,'pnr/fst','blue/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',43,'Large Hawk-Cuckoo','Hierococcyx sparverioides','Sewah-Tekukur Besar','鹰鹃','Non-rarity','M','Adult is distinctively larger than the other two Hawk-Cuckoo species and has slaty-grey head, brownish-grey upperparts, rufous breast-patch, whitish rest of underparts with dark bars and long tail with broad dark tail-bands. Juvenile resembles adult but has darker brown upperparts with rufous bars, pale rufous nape with dark brown streaks and whitish underparts with bold dark brown drop-like streaks on breast.','Forest, forest edge, mangroves, parks and gardens.',NULL,38.0,41.5,'pnr/fst','brown/black/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',44,'Malaysian Hawk-Cuckoo','Hierococcyx fugax','Sewah-Tekukur Melayu','马来棕腹鹰鹃','Non-rarity','M/Vi','Both adult and juvenile resembles juvenile Hodgson''s Hawk-Cuckoo but has darker brown upperparts, generally whiter and cleaner underparts with dark-brownish spot-like streaks at breast, prominent whitish patch at nape and evenly spaced tail-bars.','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas and mangroves.','Known only to brood parasite on White-rumped Shama.',29.0,29.0,'fst','black/grey/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',45,'Hodgson''s Hawk-Cuckoo','Hierococcyx nisicolor','Sewah-Tekukur Cina Selatan','霍氏鹰鹃','Non-rarity','M','Adult has greyish upperparts, whitish underparts with rufous-washed breast and narrowest penultimate dark tail-band. Juvenile resembles adult but has brownish and obvious rufous-tinged upperparts and breast streaks. Told from similar Malaysian Hawk-Cuckoo by narrower penultimate tail band (Malaysian shows even-width tail bands).','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas, gardens and parks.',NULL,27.0,31.0,'pnr/fst','black/orange/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',46,'Indian Cuckoo','Cuculus micropterus','Sewah Biasa','四声杜鹃','Non-rarity','M','Male has greyish head, throat and upper breast, brownish tinge mantle, wings and tail, whitish rest of underparts with blackish bars and greyish-green eyering. Female resembles male but has rufescent wash across breast. Juvenile resembles adult but has browner crown and head-sides, prominent rufous to whitish feather-tips on upperparts and buffish underparts with broken dark bars.','Forest, forest edge, mangroves, parks and gardens.',NULL,31.0,33.0,'pnr/fst','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckoos (Cuculidae)',47,'Himalayan Cuckoo','Cuculus saturatus','Sewah Gunung Asia','中杜鹃','Rarity','M','Adult resembles Indian Cuckoo but has grey head, breast and upperparts, whitish underparts with prominent blackish bars and less obvious or no blackish bars on undertail-coverts. Hepatic female resembles hepatic female Plaintive and Rusty-breasted Cuckoo but has deeper orange upperparts and whiter underparts. It was formerly considered conspecific with Oriental Cuckoo (Cuculus optatus) which may but not confirmed to occur in Singapore. Based on current knowledge, it is impossible to separate Himalayan and Oriental Cuckoo in the field.','Forest, secondary growth and wooded areas.',NULL,29.0,29.0,'fst','grey/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',48,'Rock Dove','Columba livia','Merpati Biasa','原鸽','Non-rarity','I','Adult is typically grey with noticeable darker hood and breast, blackish tail-tip and paler wing-coverts with two broad blackish bars. May also be highly variable with patches of white and brown in plumage and some are entirely blackish.','Urban and open areas.','Forages ground.',33.0,33.0,'resd','black/grey/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',49,'Oriental Turtle Dove','Streptopelia orientalis','Tekukur Emas Asia','山斑鸠','Rarity','Va','Resemble Spotted Dove but larger, bulkier, and darker overall. Barred rather than spotted side of neck. Bluish-grey crown. Rufous fringes to lower mantle and wing coverts. Broader rufous fringes to scapulars. Bluish-slate rump and uppertail coverts.','Open forest, secondary growth, scrub and plantation.',NULL,31.0,33.0,'fst/open','grey/blue',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',50,'Red Collared Dove','Streptopelia tranquebarica','Tekukur Merah','火斑鸠','Non-rarity','I','Male has distinctive vinous-red plumage, greyish head and black hindneck-bar. Body and wing-coverts of female mostly brownish and has less grey on head. Juvenile resembles female but lacks the hindneck-bar.','Open habitats like grasslands and reclaimed lands.',NULL,23.0,24.5,'resd','red/brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',51,'Spotted Dove','Spilopelia chinensis','Tekukur Jerum Timur','珠颈斑鸠','Non-rarity','R','Adult has greyish-brown upperparts with blackish streaks on upperwings, prominent black collar with white spots at back of neck, greyish face and pale vinous-pink underparts. Juvenile looks darker and has less obvious collar at back of neck.','Open habitats like grasslands, reclaimed lands and urban areas.','Forages mostly ground for grass seeds and grains.',30.0,31.0,'resd','brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',52,'Common Emerald Dove','Chalcophaps indica','Punai-Tanah Biasa','绿翅金鸠','Non-rarity','R','Male has blue-grey crown and nape, unmistakable metallic green mantle and wings with white shoulder-patch, white forehead and eyebrow and red bill. Female resembles male but has less grey on head and no white on wings. Juvenile has speckly brown mantle with very light greenish wash on wings.','Forest, mangroves and coastal woodlands.','Forages ground along trails under tree cover.',23.0,27.0,'pnr/fst','brown/green','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',53,'Zebra Dove','Geopelia striata','Merbuk Biasa','斑姬地鸠','Non-rarity','R','Adult has pale bluish-grey forehead and face with light blue orbital skin, brownish-grey upperparts with dark bars and pinkish underparts with black and white barrings at hindneck, sides of neck and flanks. Juvenile looks duller and has less contrasting bars on hindneck.','Open habitats like grasslands, reclaimed lands and urban areas.','Feeds mostly on bare ground and short grass.',21.0,21.5,'resd','grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',54,'Cinnamon-headed Green Pigeon','Treron fulvicollis','Punai Bakau','棕头绿鸠','Rarity','Vi','Distinguished from male Pink-necked Green Pigeon by the rufous-chestnut hood and maroon wings. Female resembles Thick-billed Green Pigeon but bill and eyering distinctively narrower, thigh yellowish and undertail-coverts streaked instead of barred.','Freshwater swamp forest, coastal forest, mangroves, secondary growth and suitable wooded areas.','Little is known of the behaviour of this species.',25.5,26.0,'fst/wet','green/orange',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',55,'Little Green Pigeon','Treron olax','Punai Kecil','小绿鸠','Rarity','Vi','Male can be distinguished from other Green Pigeon species by a combination of small size, bluish-grey hood, maroon wings and broad orange patch on upper-breast. Female has dark grey crown, pale greyish throat, dark green upperparts, pale undertail-coverts with dark green streaks and no eyering.','Forest.',NULL,20.0,20.5,'fst','green/grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',56,'Pink-necked Green Pigeon','Treron vernans','Punai Kocok','红颈绿鸠','Non-rarity','R','Male has mostly green plumage with greyish head, pinkish nape, neck and upperbreast, orange central breast and dark chestnut undertail-coverts. Female lacks the pinkish and orange plumage of the male. Juvenile of both sexes resembles female but male will soon start to show patches of adult plumage.','Forests, mangroves, wooded areas, gardens and parks.','Arboreal, seldom come to the ground except to drink.',26.5,32.0,'pnr/fst','red/orange/green','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',57,'Orange-breasted Green Pigeon','Treron bicinctus','Punai Siam','橙胸绿鸠','Rarity','Vi','Male has green head, with a narrow band of pink on the upper breast and broader bright orange breast band below, and a blue-grey nape. A dark tail-bar is interrupted centrally and the broad pale grey terminal band can be observed in flight. Female lack the pink and orange breast patch, Differentiated from other female green pigeons by contrasting blue-grey nape, strong brownish cast to green of upperparts, lack of obvious eyering, and tail pattern of the male. The wingbars of both sexes are clear yellow (in contrast to the cream in Pink-necked Green Pigeon).','Forested area, secondary growth and sometimes coastal scrubs.','Often seen joining other frugivores at fruiting figs, foraging by slowly walking along branches. Diet consist mainly of fruits and seeds.',29.0,29.0,'fst/sea','green/orange/yellow','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',58,'Ashy-headed Green Pigeon','Treron phayrei','Punai Ara Indochina','灰头绿鸠','Rarity','Va','Both sexes are green overall with well-delineated grey forehead extending to crown, yellow rump, and green edges to flight feathers ending in dark tips. Male has maroon wings and mantle, orange patch on breast, and chestnut undertail coverts. Female resembles male but lacks the maroon, orange breast patch, and chestnut undertail coverts. Can be separated from similar looking Thick-billed Green Pigeon by the lack of thick bill and bluish-green orbital ring. Females look similar to other Treron species, and can be differentiated from female Cinnamon-headed Green Pigeon by lack of red base to bill, while female Pink-necked Green Pigeon lacks the grey forehead and crown. Female Orange-breasted Green Pigeon has a blue base to bill and grey nape, and lacks the grey forehead. Female Little Green Pigeon is much smaller and has light yellow irises compared to the dark pink irises of Ashy-headed Green Pigeon.','Lowland hills and forest.','Takes fruit and forages in trees, occasionally coming down for water. Often seen in association with other Treron species. In Singapore, the only record was seen congregating with Thick-billed Green Pigeons.',27.0,27.0,'fst','green/orange/red','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',59,'Thick-billed Green Pigeon','Treron curvirostra','Punai Ara Biasa','厚嘴绿鸠','Non-rarity','R/Vi','Male has thick pale greenish bill with red base, broad green eyering, grey crown, maroon wings, and mostly green underparts. Female resembles male but lacks the maroon wings. Juvenile of both sexes resembles female but young male will soon start to show patches of adult plumage.','Forest, wooded areas,matured gardens, and parks.','Frequents the canopy and mid-storey in small numbers.',25.5,27.5,'pnr/fst','green/yellow/red','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',60,'Jambu Fruit Dove','Ptilinopus jambu','Punai-Gading Jambu','粉头果鸠','Non-rarity','Vi','Male has greenish upperparts, crimson face, white eyering, white underparts with pink flush on foreneck and upperbreast. Female has mostly green overall plumage with greyish-purple face. Juvenile resembles female but has greenish face.','Forest, wooded areas and matured gardens and parks.',NULL,26.5,27.0,'pnr/fst','green/red','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',61,'Green Imperial Pigeon','Ducula aenea','Pergam Daun Biasa','绿皇鸠','Non-rarity','R','Adult has dark metallic green mantle and wings with vinous-tinged pale grey head, neck and underparts. Juvenile looks duller than adult.','Forests, mangroves, wooded areas and parks.','Gregarious and mostly sighted at coastal wooded areas with fruiting palms.',42.0,47.0,'pnr/fst','green/grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',62,'Mountain Imperial Pigeon','Ducula badia','Pergam Bukit Biasa','山皇鸠','Rarity','Vi','Adult has purplish-maroon mantle and wings, bluish-grey crown and face, red eyering, red bill with pale tip, white throat and vinous-tinged pale grey neck and underparts.','Forests and wooded areas','Frugivorous, feeding on a variety of fruits and berries.',43.0,51.0,'fst/pnr','grey/orange','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pigeons, Doves (Columbidae)',63,'Pied Imperial Pigeon','Ducula bicolor','Rawa Biasa','斑皇鸠','Non-rarity','I/R/Vi','Adult has white overall plumage with contrasting black primaries and secondaries and black tail. Juvenile resembles adult but white feathers have buffish tips.','Coastal forests, mangroves and gardens/parks with fruiting palms.','Wild population undertakes long flights from island to island in search of new food source.',38.0,41.0,'wet','white/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Finfoots (Heliornithidae)',64,'Masked Finfoot','Heliopais personatus','Pedendang Asia','亚洲鳍趾鷉','Rarity','Va','Male has thick yellow bill, grey hind neck and hindcrown, blackish throat and upper foreneck with white border, brownish rest of upperparts, mostly whitish underparts and bright green feet. Female resemble male but throat, upper foreneck and much of lores whitish and has less black on forecrown. Juvenile resembles female but somewhat browner above with no black on forecrown.','Rivers in broadleaved evergreen forest, mangroves, swamp forest and sometime pools and lakes away from forest.','Usually secretive. Head jerks back and forth when swimming.',52.0,54.5,'wet','grey/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',65,'Slaty-breasted Rail','Lewinia striata','Sintar Biasa','蓝胸秧鸡','Non-rarity','R','Adult has long reddish bill, chestnut crown and nape, slaty-grey breast and fine white barrings on dark upperparts, belly and vent. Juvenile resembles adult but has browner breast, duller crown and nape and less distinct barrings.','Freshwater wetlands','Skulks in thick vegetation, appearing briefly at the edge of reedbeds and grassy verges of road.',26.0,31.0,'wet','grey/brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',66,'Common Moorhen','Gallinula chloropus','Tiung-Air Biasa','黑水鸡','Rarity','R','Adult has overall dark plumage with contrasting white line along flanks and lateral undertail-coverts, yellow-tip red bill, distinctive red frontal shield and greenish-yellow legs/feet. Male is larger than female. Juvenile has duller overall plumage than adult and lacks any red on bill and frontal shield.','Freshwater wetlands.','Usually observed feeding while swimming.',30.0,35.0,'wet','white/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',67,'Grey-headed Swamphen','Porphyrio poliocephalus','Panglin Biasa','紫水鸡','Rarity','R','Distinguished from Common Moorhen by bigger size, dark purplish blue overall plumage, red stout bill, frontal shield and legs, whitish undertail-coverts and blackish-brown wings. Juvenile resembles adult but has paler plumage and duller frontal shield.','Freshwater wetlands.','Often seen feeding in the open by picking up food material while walking on floating vegetation.',28.0,29.0,'wet','blue/grey','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',68,'Ruddy-breasted Crake','Zapornia fusca','Sintar-Kecil Belacan Biasa','红胸田鸡','Non-rarity','R','Distinguished from Red-legged Crake by plain wings, cold dark olive-brown upperparts, deep reddish-chestnut underparts, indistinct whitish-and-blackish vent-bars and green-based dark bill. Juvenile resembles adult but has darker upperparts and brownish-grey bars/mottlings at underparts.','Freshwater wetlands and wet grasslands at the edge of ditches and canals.','Active mainly at dusk and in the early morning when they will forage at the edges of reedbeds and short distance from dense cover.',21.0,26.5,'wet','brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',69,'Band-bellied Crake','Zapornia paykullii','Sintar-Kecil Belacan Berbelang','斑胁田鸡','Rarity','Va','Resembles Ruddy-breasted Crake but has a stronger, thicker and shorter bill, some narrow whitish and dark bars on wing coverts and the black white bars between flanks and undertail-coverts are more distinctive. Juvenile has paler head-sides and breasts and browner legs than adult.','Freshwater wetlands.','Very skulking.',27.0,27.0,'wet','grey/brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',70,'Baillon''s Crake','Zapornia pusilla','Sintar-Kecil Biru Biasa','小田鸡','Non-rarity','M','Adult has rich brown upperparts with black streaks and black-edged white markings, pale grey head-sides and anterior underparts, black-and-white bars at posterior underparts and greenish bill and legs. Juvenile resembles adult but lack the pale grey plumage at head-sides and anterior underparts.','Marshes and grasslands with dense emergents, floating vegetation and shallow water.','Skulking, rarely seen away from reedbeds.',19.0,20.5,'pnr/wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',71,'Slaty-legged Crake','Rallina eurizonoides','Sintar-Merah Kaki Kelabu','白喉斑秧鸡','Rarity','M','Resembles Red-legged Crake but is larger and considerably larger-billed, has duller brown upperparts (except head and neck), more rufous-chestnut head, neck and breast, whitish throat that contrasts sharply with head-sides and dark slaty-grey legs. Juvenile resembles adult but has paler brown upperparts, head, neck and breast.','Streams and wet areas in forest and also freshwater wetlands and gardens on passage.','Often calls at night.',26.0,28.0,'wet','orange/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',72,'Red-legged Crake','Rallina fasciata','Sintar-Merah Kaki Api','红腿斑秧鸡','Non-rarity','M/R','Adult has chestnut-tinged brown upperparts, mostly dull chestnut head and breast, black-and-whitish bars on wing-coverts, distinctive bold black-and-whitish bars on lower breast to vent and red legs and feet. Juvenile resembles adult but has paler brown upperparts, head, neck and breast, underparts bars duller and much less distinct and brownish-yellow legs.','Streams and wet areas in forest, secondary growth, gardens and parks.','Forages by carefully walking through wet areas of secondary growth and forest, and picking up food items with its bill from the wet ground and leaf litter.',22.0,25.0,'wet/fst','brown/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',73,'White-browed Crake','Poliolimnas cinereus','Ruak-ruak Kening Putih','白眉苦恶鸟','Non-rarity','R','Adult is easily identified by a combination of small size, dark orbital area bordered above and below by broad white streak (resembling eye-brow), greyish crown, nape, breast and upper flanks, brownish upperparts, yellowish bill with some red at base and yellowish-green legs and feet. Juvenile resembles adult but the greyish parts are somewhat browner, facial features less distinct and lacks red at base of bill.','Well-vegetated freshwater wetlands.','Usually more active in the early morning and evening when they are fairly conspicuous when feeding in the open.',19.0,21.5,'wet','brown/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',74,'Watercock','Gallicrex cinerea','Ayam-ayam Tanduk','董鸡','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding male and female have buff brown plumage with bold dark streaks on the upperparts, narrow barrings on the underparts and yellowish-green bill and legs. Male is significantly larger and has thicker bill than female. Breeding male has black body with streaked buff-brown back, mostly yellowish bill and red frontal shield that extends over the head. Juvenile resembles female.','Freshwater wetlands, marshy grasslands and well vegetated ponds in parks/gardens.','Usually solitary and skulk in thick cover, occasionally coming out to feed in the open.',31.0,43.0,'wet/fst','black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rails, Crakes & Coots (Rallidae)',75,'White-breasted Waterhen','Amaurornis phoenicurus','Ruak-ruak Biasa','白胸苦恶鸟','Non-rarity','M/R','Adult has white face and underparts contrasting with dark slaty-grey upperparts, chestnut undertail-coverts and distinctive yellowish-green bill with red base. Juvenile has browner upperparts, dark spots on ear-coverts and less white over eye.','Various kinds of well-vegetated wetlands, pools and streams in open forest, mangroves and adjacent open areas, track, roadsides, gardens and parks.','Not shy and frequently forages in the open.',28.5,36.0,'pnr/wet','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Grebes (Podicipedidae)',76,'Little Grebe','Tachybaptus ruficollis','Tetimbul Kecil Biasa','小䴙䴘','Rarity','R','Small and duck-like. Adult has bright rufous-chestnut head-sides, throat and foreneck contrasting with dark brown crown, hindneck and upperside, yellow eyes and blackish bill with prominent yellow gape-skin. Juvenile has duller plumage, pinkish-orange bill, blackish head with vertical buffish stripes on head and neck.','Well vegetated marshes and disused quarry pools.','Seldom flies when alarmed, preferring to dive underwater before resurfacing a few meters away.',25.0,29.0,'wet','black/white/orange','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Buttonquail (Turnicidae)',77,'Barred Buttonquail','Turnix suscitator','Puyuh Biasa','棕三趾鹑','Non-rarity','R','Adult birds are distinguished from similar looking female King Quail by bold blackish bars across lower throat, breast and upper flanks and deep rufous-buff belly and vent. Female is bigger than male and has black patch on throat and centre of upper breast. Juvenile resemble male.','Dry grassy area and scrub.','It is the male that incubates the eggs and care for the young.',15.0,17.5,'pnr/fst','brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Stone-curlews, Thick-knees (Burhinidae)',78,'Beach Stone-curlew','Esacus magnirostris','Kedidi-Malam Besar Pantai','澳洲石鸻','Rarity','Vi','Large, thickset bird with medium long sturdy legs, heavy head, bulky bill and broad wings. Bustard-like appearance. Head marked with black, white and grey/brown stripes. In flight, upperwings show mostly grey secondaries and mostly white inner primaries. Underwings all white except for black-tipped secondaries and outer primaries.','Undisturbed sandy beach and sandflats often near mangroves.','Mostly crepuscular and nocturnal. Vocal at night.',53.0,57.0,'wet/sea','black/white/grey',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Stilts, Avocets (Recurvirostridae)',79,'Black-winged Stilt','Himantopus himantopus','Kedidi Kaki-Panjang Biasa','黑翅长脚鹬','Rarity','M/R','Male in non-breeding plumage has distinctive medium-long needle-like blackish bill, very long pinkish-red legs, mostly white head, neck and underparts with grey cap and hind neck and black ear-coverts, upper mantle and wings while non-breeding female is browner above. Breeding male has typically all white head and neck while breeding female is browner above and may show some grey on hindneck and head. Juveniles has brownish-grey crown/hindneck and greyish brown mantle with buffy fringes.','Borders of open wetlands, coastal pools, mudflats and marshy grasslands.','Feeds primarily on aquatic prey especially beetles, mayflies and spiders, although mollusks, crustaceans, earthworms and small fish, as well as water plants and their seeds.',37.5,37.5,'wet','white/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Stilts, Avocets (Recurvirostridae)',80,'Pied Stilt','Himantopus leucocephalus','Kedidi Kaki-Panjang Australasia','澳洲长脚鹬','Rarity','M/R','Adult resembles Black-winged Stilt but has long black "mane" at the back of the head and neck. Based on current knowledge, may not be possible to distinguish juvenile Pied Stilt with non-breeding and juvenile Black-winged Stilt.','Borders of open wetlands, coastal pools, mudflats and marshy grasslands.',NULL,35.0,35.0,'wet','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',81,'Grey-headed Lapwing','Vanellus cinereus','Ceriwit Kepala Kelabu','灰头麦鸡','Rarity','M','Adult has brownish upperparts, brownish-grey head, neck and upper breast with blackish breast-band, black-tipped yellowish bill, white belly and yellowish legs. Juvenile resembles adult but head, neck and breast more brownish and breast-band vague or absent.','Rice fields, swampy/marshy areas and mudflats.',NULL,34.0,37.0,'wet','grey','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',82,'Red-wattled Lapwing','Vanellus indicus','Ceriwit Duit-duit','肉垂麦鸡','Non-rarity','R','Black head and upper breast, red-bill with black tip, red facial skin, and white patch on ear coverts. Sandy greyish-brown upperparts with narrow white band across mantle, white underparts and long yellow legs.','Marshes, cultivated land, grassland, wasteland, margin of lakes, ponds and large rivers.','Usually found in pairs or family parties. Sharp, incessant vocalization when alarmed.',31.5,35.0,'wet','red/black/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',83,'Masked Lapwing','Vanellus miles','Ceriwit Berpial Australasia','白颈麦鸡','Non-rarity','I','A large, ground-dwelling bird with brown wings and back, and a black crown. Underparts are mainly white. Large yellow wattle across forehead and hanging over the bill, and a conspicuous black-tipped yellow spur on the carpal joint of each wing.','Edges of wetlands and in other moist, open environments, beaches and coastlines, urban parks, sporting fields, paddocks, riverbeds, and in Singapore, at golf courses.','Feed on insects and their larvae, and earthworms. Most food is obtained from just below the surface of the ground, but some may also be taken above the surface. Normally seen feeding alone, in pairs or in small groups.  During breeding season, nesting pair boldly defends their territory against all intruders by calling loudly, spreading their wings, and swooping fast and low, and at times striking at intruders with their feet, and attacking animals on the ground with their spurs. At other times, they act as though they have a broken wing in an attempt to lure the intruder away from the nest.',30.0,37.0,'wet/pnr/sea','brown/yellow/white','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',84,'Pacific Golden Plover','Pluvialis fulva','Kerinyut Biasa','金斑鸻','Non-rarity','M','In non-breeding plumage, can be confused with Grey Plover but is smaller, more golden overall and has shorter/thiner bill. In flight, underwings are drab, pale, brown and lack the black auxiliaries (armpits) present in Grey Plover. In breeding plumage, face and underparts all black with a broad white band that extends from the lore to behind the ear-coverts and down the breast-sides.','Mudflat, open fields and other coastal habitats.','Gregarious. Usually form large flocks in wintering grounds.',23.0,26.0,'pnr','white/black/brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',85,'Grey Plover','Pluvialis squatarola','Kerinyut Kelabu','灰斑鸻','Non-rarity','M','In non-breeding plumage, look similar to Pacific Golden Plover but larger, stockier and bigger-headed with stouter bill and relatively shorter legs, upperside more uniform and distinctly greyish. In flight, display prominent black auxiliaries (armpits) at underwing. In breeding plumage, face and underparts all black except vent which is white, with very broad white band extending from lore to behind ear-coverts and down the breast-sides.','Mudflat, sandflat and beaches.','Form small flocks with birds widely spaced apart unlike Pacific Golden Plovers which usually form large and rather "dense" flocks.',27.0,30.0,'oc','grey/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',86,'Common Ringed Plover','Charadrius hiaticula','Rapang Gelang Besar','剑鸻','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding adult resembles Little Ringed Plover but slightly larger and more robust, base of lower mandible dull orange, breast-band boarder and less even, legs and feet orange and shows prominent white bar across upperwing when in flight. Male and female in breeding plumage also resembles Little Ringed Plover but has distinctive orange bill with black tip, orange legs and no obvious yellow eyering. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult and difficult to separate from Little Ringed Plover except by size, lack of obvious eyering, orange-tinged legs and feet and white wing-bar (in flight).','Fringes of freshwater ponds and mudflats.',NULL,18.0,20.0,'wet','white/black/grey','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',87,'Little Ringed Plover','Charadrius dubius','Rapang Gelang Kecil','金眶鸻','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult has narrow pale yellow eyering, slender dark bill, greyish-brown upperparts, whitish forehead with indistinct supercilium, white collar, complete greyish-brown breast-band and yellowish legs and feet. Male in breeding plumage has black lores, ear-coverts and breast-band and white forehead and supercilium with prominent black band across forecrown. Female in breeding plumage has brownish-black ear-coverts and breast-band. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult.','Open grasslands, sandy shores, coastal breakwaters, fringes of freshwater ponds and mudflats.','Usually in small loose groups, feeding in typical plover fashion and often calling in flight.',14.0,17.0,'oc/wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',88,'Kentish Plover','Charadrius alexandrinus','Rapang Pantai Biasa','环颈鸻','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult can be distinguished from other plover species by the white nuchal collar, well defined lateral breast-band and plain greyish-brown upperparts including head which has little white on forehead. Male in breeding plumage has distinctive white forehead, black patch on midcrown, strongly rufous-washed remainder of crown and nape, broad blackish eye-stripe and black lateral breast-band. Non-breeding adult can be distinguished from the bigger and similar looking White-faced Plover by having less white on forehead and thicker/longer lateral breast-band while breeding male has a black eye-stripe which is lacking in breeding White-faced Plover.','Sandy beaches and suitable coastal habitats.','Have been observed wintering in Singapore and form flocks with White-faced Plovers and Lesser Sand Plovers.',15.0,15.0,'oc','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',89,'White-faced Plover','Charadrius dealbatus','Rapang Pantai Cina','白脸鸻','Rarity','M','Formerly considered a subspecies of Kentish Plover. Non-breeding adult resembles Kentish Plover but is bigger and has more white on forehead, shorter/narrower lateral breast-band and distinctively pinkish-toned legs. Breeding male is distinguished from breeding male Kentish Plover by the lack of black eye-stripe while breeding female resembles non-breeding adult but crown, lores, ear-coverts strongly rufous- to orange-toned.','Sandy beaches and suitable coastal habitats.','Have been observed wintering in Singapore and form flocks with Kentish Plovers and Lesser Sand Plovers.',16.0,16.0,'oc','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',90,'Javan Plover','Charadrius javanicus','Rapang Pantai Jawa','爪哇鸻','Rarity','R','From the similar looking common migrant, Kentish Plover, by warm buff ear-coverts, relatively heavier bill and longer legs. White-faced Plover will lack distinct facial markings, while Malaysian Plover has more mottled looking upperparts.','Mudflats, sandflats, and coastal wetlands.','Found along the coast as with many other plovers. Seems to be experiencing a rapid range expansion with recent sightings at previously undetected sites such as southern Sumatra, the western coast of Sulawesi and Singapore.',15.0,15.0,'wet','brown/white/black',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',91,'Malaysian Plover','Charadrius peronii','Rapang Pantai Melayu','马来鸻','Non-rarity','R','Male resembles breeding male Kentish Plover but upperparts and wing-coverts with prominent pale fringes (appear scaly or mottled) and black lateral breast-patches extend in complete band below white nuchal collar. Female looks similar to male but lateral breast-band is rufous-orange and lack black crown-patch. Juvenile appears duller than female.','Sandy beaches and suitable coastal habitats.','Usually solitary or in pairs and sometimes in very small groups.',14.0,16.0,'oc','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',92,'Lesser Sand Plover','Charadrius mongolus','Rapang-Sisir Kecil','蒙古沙鸻','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult can be distinguished from Kentish Plover by broad lateral breast-patches and lack of white nuchal collar. Best separated from very similar looking Greater Sand Plover by smaller size, shorter and blunter bill, tibia obviously shorter than tarsus and dark grey to greenish-grey legs and feet. Male in breeding plumage has black forehead, lores and ear-coverts, white throat and deep orange-rufous neck-sides and breast-band. Female in breeding plumage has less obvious black and orange-rufous plumage of the male.','Mudflats, sandy shores and coastal breakwaters.','Usually congregates in flocks of several hundred at low tide feeding grounds or at high tide roosts.',19.0,21.0,'oc/wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',93,'Greater Sand Plover','Charadrius leschenaultii','Rapang-Sisir Besar','铁嘴沙鸻','Rarity','M','Resembles Lesser Sand Plover in both breeding and non-breeding plumages but larger with broader head, thicker bill and proportionately longer and yellowish legs. Usually observed to be in full non-breeding plumage in Singapore at the start of autumn migration when the Lesser Sand Plovers still have traces of breeding plumage on them.','Mudflats and sandy shores.','Associates with other feeding shorebirds, especially Lesser Sand Plover.',22.0,25.0,'oc/wet','brown/white/grey','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Plovers (Charadriidae)',94,'Oriental Plover','Charadrius veredus','Rapang Padang Asia Timur','东方鸻','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding adult resembles Lesser and Greater Sand Plovers but larger and slimmer-looking with longer neck, legs and wings, more slender bill, upper breast buffish-brown, longer and more pronounced supercilium and yellowish-orange legs and feet. Male in breeding plumage has mostly whitish head and neck with distinctive rufous-chestnut breast-band and broad black lower border. Female in breeding plumage resembles non-breeding adult but with rufescent wash at upper breast.','Mudflats, sandy shores and open grasslands.','Associates with other feeding shorebirds, especially Lesser Sand Plover.',22.0,25.0,'oc/wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Painted-snipes (Rostratulidae)',95,'Greater Painted-snipe','Rostratula benghalensis','Meragi Biasa','彩鹬','Non-rarity','R','Differentiated from other snipe species by distinctive white spectacles, narrow buffish median stripe and bill that droops slightly at tip. Female has blackish crown, dark maroon-chestnut head, neck and upper breast, blackish breast band, white belly and white band around shoulder. Plumage of male is somewhat paler with greyish brown head-sides, neck, upper breast and rich buffish markings on wing-coverts. Juvenile resembles male but wing-coverts greyer.','Freshwater marshes and well-vegetated wetlands.','Quite secretive and mainly crepuscular.',23.0,26.0,'wet','brown/white/yellow','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Jacanas (Jacanidae)',96,'Pheasant-tailed Jacana','Hydrophasianus chirurgus','Burung-Teratai Ekor Panjang','水雉','Rarity','M','Non-breeding adult has drab brown upperparts, white underparts, short tail, yellow-buff supercilium/neck-side, dark crown and black eyestripe that leads to breast-band. Breeding adult has mostly blackish-brown body, white head/foreneck, yellow-buff hindneck, long black tail and mostly white wings. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has rufous-chestnut crown and weaker/brownish breast band.','Well-vegetated freshwater marshes and less suitable habitats on passage like mangroves, ponds, lakes and reservoirs.','It is the male that take care for the young.',29.0,31.5,'pnr/wet','brown/white/yellow','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',97,'Eurasian Whimbrel','Numenius phaeopus','Kendi Gajah Erasia','中杓鹬','Non-rarity','M','A fairly large greyish-brown bird with with a long, decurved bill witrh a kink. Prominent black lateral crown stripe and eyestripe. Broad whitish supercillium and buffish-white neck and breast with dark streaks. Legs and feet dull grey. Although large, it is considered mid-sized compared to other curlews. Compared to the larger curlews, it has a shorter bill.','Winters mainly along the coastline, coastal wetlands, mangroves, marshes and larger rivers.','A gregarious species that feed mainly on invertebrates by probing, and picking up occasional small crabs and similar prey.',40.0,46.0,'wet/sea','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',98,'Little Curlew','Numenius minutus','Kendi Kerdil Asia','小杓鹬','Rarity','Va','A small greyish brown curlew species that resembles the larger Eurasian Whimbrel. Smaller and finer billed than its larger relatives and pale supercillium contrast sharply with black eyestripe. Underparts also more buffish. Legs and feet yellowish to bluish-grey.','Found in open fields, grasslands, barren cultivation, margins of freshwater and also on coastal mudflats during migration.','Feeds mainly by picking.',29.0,32.0,'wet/open','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',99,'Far Eastern Curlew','Numenius madagascariensis','Kendi Besar Timur','大杓鹬','Rarity','Va','A large wader similar to the Eurasian Curlew, but larger and longer billed and appears more uniform with browner/buffier underparts. In flight shows uniform light brown back and rump and heavily marked underwings.','Mudflats and sandflats.','Generally congregates in large flocks to migrate or roost but may feed alone. Feeds mainly by probing for invertebrates from deep burrows.',60.0,66.0,'wet','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',100,'Eurasian Curlew','Numenius arquata','Kendi Besar Biasa','白腰杓鹬','Rarity','M','Adult resembles Whimbrel but is larger and has longer and gently down-curved bill and more uniform head with indistinct supercilium. Juvenile resembles adult but is smaller and has more buffish breast.','Mudflats, sandflats and coastal wetlands.',NULL,50.0,60.0,'wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',101,'Bar-tailed Godwit','Limosa lapponica','Kedidi-Raja Ekor Belang','斑尾塍鹬','Non-rarity','M','A fairly large wader with long blackish legs, rather long neck, a long, tapering, slightly upturned bi-coloured bill: pink at the base and black towards the tip. Breeding plumage is dark brick-red below (male) or chestnut to cinnamon (female); nonbreeding plumage is overall gray-brown with white belly. In flight shows rather plain upperwings with only a faint whitish wing stripe. White tail with blackish bars separate it from the Black-tailed Godwit.','Mudflats, sandflats, beaches and brackish coastal lagoons.','Feeds on open mud, sand and in shallower water by probing its long bill into the mud.',37.0,41.0,'wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',102,'Black-tailed Godwit','Limosa limosa','Kedidi-Raja Ekor Hitam','黑尾塍鹬','Rarity','M','A fairly large wader with long blackish legs, rather long neck, long straight bi-coloured bill: pink at the base and black towards the tip. Breeding plumage has bright reddish-rufous head and breast, dark barring on belly. Non-breeding plumage has plain grayish head, breast and upperparts, unlike the streaked breast and back of the Bar-tailed Godwit. In flight shows bold white upperwing bars, white rump and black tail.','Musflats, sandflats, coastal pools, sometimes wet paddy fields.','Usually found in flocks. Feeds mainly by wading in deeper water, probing with its long bill.',36.0,40.0,'wet','brown/white/black','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',103,'Ruddy Turnstone','Arenaria interpres','Kedidi-Kerikil Merah','翻石鹬','Non-rarity','M','A rather distinctive smallish, stocky shorebird with a short stout wedge-shaped blackish bill. It has short orange legs and feet. In breeding plumage it has reddish-brown upperparts and bold black-and-white pattern on head and neck. Nonbreeding and juveniles are duller brown but still boldly patterned, with black mottling and a dark head with little white.','Winters on coastlines. Prefers rocky and stony habitats, but also seen on beaches and mudflats.','LIkes to flip over rocks, shells, seaweed and other debris to catch invertebrates. Also observed digging holes for food, and scavenging as well.',21.0,24.0,'oc/wet','grey/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',104,'Great Knot','Calidris tenuirostris','Kedidi-Dian Besar','大滨鹬','Rarity','M','Adult in non-breeding plumage can be separated from other similar size waders by a combination of attenuated shape, longish, broad-based, slightly downward tapering blackish bill, shortish legs, greyish upperparts, indistinct supercilium, streaked greyish head to upperbreast, whitish belly and blackish spots on sides of breast and upper flanks. Adult in breeding plumage has bolder streaks and darker spots on head, breast and flanks. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has darker upperparts.','Mudflats and sandflats.','Gregarious and feeds mainly by probing.',28.5,29.5,'wet','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',105,'Red Knot','Calidris canutus','Kedidi-Dian Kecil','红腹滨鹬','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding adult resembles Great Knot but smaller and more compact with relatively larger head and shorter neck, more distinct dark loral stripe, better defined supercilium and has no black spots at underparts but faint V-shaped flank markings. Adult in breeding plumage has deep reddish-chestnut face and underparts. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but upperparts buffier with scaly patterns.','Mudflats and sandflats.','Probes and picks for food.',23.0,25.0,'wet','grey/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',106,'Ruff','Calidris pugnax','Kedidi Ropol','流苏鹬','Rarity','Va','Adult in non-breeding plumage (the form we get to see in the region) can be separated from similar size waders (Common Redshank, Common Greenshank and Great Knot) by a combination of upright stance, longish neck, relatively small head, shortish and straight bill which is slightly down-curved at tip and longish, usually orange to yellowish-green legs. Male is significantly bigger than female. Their feathers seem to “ruffle” more easily in the wind than other waders.','Marshes, grassy areas, coastal pools and mudflats.','Feeds mostly by surface pecking but often wades in fairly deep water.',22.0,32.0,'wet','grey/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',107,'Broad-billed Sandpiper','Calidris falcinellus','Kedidi Paruh Lebar','阔嘴鹬','Rarity','M','A small wader with short legs and a somewhat rounded appearance. In all plumages, can be distinguished from other waders by relatively long bill decurved at its tip and distinctive split supercilium. Slightly larger Curlew Sandpiper and Dunlin have a more evenly decurved bill, lack the split supercilium, and, when in non-breeding colors, display less contrasting upperpart plumage. Red-necked and Little Stint are smaller and have shorter bills which lack the decurved tip. In breeding plumage, Broad-billed Sandpipers show rufous fringes to upperpart feathers and a more contrasting supercilium.','Mudflats, sandflats, and brackish lagoons.','Walks slowly while feeding, scanning for prey from side to side; occasionally probes. Sometimes joins flocks of other waders.',16.0,18.0,'wet','brown/white/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',108,'Sharp-tailed Sandpiper','Calidris acuminata','Kedidi Ekor Tajam','尖尾滨鹬','Rarity','Va','A medium-sized sandpiper similar to the equally-rare Pectoral Sandpiper, recalls Long-toed Stint but ~50% larger. From Long-toed Stint, told by size, at least slight rufous tones on crown in all plumages, significantly longer legs giving taller appearance, and thicker bill. From Pectoral Sandpiper, distinguished by presence of streaking on flanks (versus clean flanks in that species), less distinct white supercilium, more warm tones on crown, and in breeding plumage, chevron-shaped (as opposed to pure streaked) markings on underparts; Pectoral also almost always shows pale tones on bill-base while Sharp-tailed often has all-dark bill.','Mudflats, sandflats, flooded grasslands, and brackish lagoons.','Typically feeds at water’s edge on insects, snails, and crustaceans.',17.0,21.0,'wet','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',109,'Curlew Sandpiper','Calidris ferruginea','Kedidi Paruh Lengkuk','弯嘴滨鹬','Non-rarity','M','Medium-sized sandpiper with long, downcurved bill. In non-breeding plumage, shows clear contrasting white supercilium (unlike Dunlin, which has a weak or indistinct supercilium). See Broad-billed Sandpiper for differences. In breeding plumage, head, neck, and underparts mostly rufous; upperparts washed with gray and rufous tones. Birds in early migratory season (July-August) often display patches of rufous on breast and upper belly.','Mudflats, sandflats, and brackish lagoons.','Picks prey from surface of mud, occasionally probing.',19.0,21.5,'oc/wet','brown/white/orange','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',110,'Long-toed Stint','Calidris subminuta','Kedidi-Kerdil Jari Panjang','长趾滨鹬','Rarity','M','A small wader that resembles Red-necked Stints and Little Stints but somewhat longer necked, finer billed, longer winged with a more slender-bodied appearance. Legs and feet are yellowish and distinctively long. Breeding plumaged adult and juvenile have rufous crown with dark streaks, upperparts and tertials broadly fringed rufous. Neck sides and breast washed creamy-buff and dark streaked. Underparts are white. They resemble the much larger Sharp-tailed Sandpipers in pattern and colour. Non-breeding adult rather plain mousy brown above, pale below.','Freshwater marshes, wet paddy fields, salt pans, coastal pools, rarely mudflats.','Often feeds amongst vegetation, probing the ground with its bill. It feeds on molluscs, crustaceans, amphibians, insects, other invertebrates and seeds.',14.0,16.0,'wet','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',111,'Spoon-billed Sandpiper','Calidris pygmaea','Kedidi Paruh Sudu','勺嘴鹬','Rarity','Va','A small wader that resembles the Red-necked Stint and Little Stint. Diagnotic feature is its spatulate bill. In breeding plumage the bird is reddish-brown around the head, breast and back. The breast has varying amounts of dark streaks extending towards the belly, which is white. Non-breeding adults lack the reddish colouration, but have pale brownish-grey upperparts with with a lightly streaked cap and back of the neck. The underparts, throat and forehead are white. The legs are black.','Mudflats, sandflats, sometimes sandy beaches, salt pans and prawn ponds.','Feeds in shallow waters and on soft wet mud. Feeding style consists of sweeping bill from side-to-side as the bird walks forward with its head down.',14.0,16.0,'wet','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',112,'Red-necked Stint','Calidris ruficollis','Kedidi-Kerdil Leher Merah','红颈滨鹬','Non-rarity','M','A small wader, very similar looking to Little Stint and Spoon-billed Sandpiper. Short, straight black bill. Breeding adult has unstreaked rufous-orange cheeks, ear coverts, lower throat and centre of upper breast. Rufous and gold tones in upperwing coverts. Nonbreeding adult gray above with dark shaft-streaks, pale below with distinct greyish lateral breast patch with slight dark streaking; juvenile similar but richer gray-brown above with neat pale feather edges in upperparts.','Mudflats, sandflats, salt pans, coastal pools and other inland wetlands.','Highly gregarious and will form flocks with other small Calidris waders, Feeds on insects and other small invertebrates, with rapid pecking action, sometimes probes.',14.0,16.0,'oc/wet','grey/white/brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',113,'Sanderling','Calidris alba','Kedidi Jari Tiga','三趾滨鹬','Rarity','M','A smallish wader but bigger than the typical stints. Shortish thicker straight black bill. Blackish legs and feet and lacks hind toe. Breeding plumage shows rusty tones on upperparts, often with a frosty appearance when fresh. Looks similar to the smaller Red-necked Stints. In non-breeding plumage, distinctive combination of pale grey ear coverts and upperside, and snowy white underside. Juveniles are similar to non-breeding adults but has darker streaks on crown and hindneck, blackish mantle and scapulars, boldly patterned with buffish-white and buff-washed breast with dark streaks on the side. Prominent bold white wing stripe in flight.','Sandflats, mudflats, sandy beaches, sometimes salt pans.  More infrequently, it may occur on rocky shores.','Running back-and-forth chasing waves and feeding actively in the sand by rapid probing and pecking.',18.0,21.0,'oc/wet','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',114,'Little Stint','Calidris minuta','Kedidi-Kerdil Perang','小滨鹬','Rarity','Va','Good views are required to differentiate this species from the very similar Red-necked Stint; compared to that species, Little has longer legs (with longer exposed tibia) and bill, distinct split supercilium (apparent in photographs), and darker central crown.','Mudflats and sandflats.','Similar to Red-necked, feeds by rapid probing and pecking.',14.0,15.5,'wet','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',115,'Pectoral Sandpiper','Calidris melanotos','Kedidi Dada Hitam','斑胸滨鹬','Rarity','Va','A medium-sized sandpiper, recalls Sharp-tailed Sandpiper, but differs from that species by sharply-demarcated white belly (clearly contrasting with brown patterning on breast), clean flanks, colder (less red) tones on crown, more distinct white supercilium, and usually pale-based bill. From the much smaller Long-toed Stint, told by stockier and taller appearance, and thicker bill. Wood Sandpiper is thinner-billed and slimmer.','Primarily occupies flooded grasslands, freshwater wetlands, and marshes.','Walks slowly and leisurely while feeding, unlike most smaller waders.',19.0,23.0,'wet','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',116,'Asian Dowitcher','Limnodromus semipalmatus','Kedidi-Tetiruk Asia','半蹼鹬','Rarity','M','In breeding plumage, shows orange-red head, breast, and upper belly, and orange-fringed upperpart feathers. Non-breeding-plumaged individuals (typically recorded in Singapore) may be confused with Black- and Bar-tailed Godwit, but can be differentiated from both these species by combination of mostly dark, straight, heavy-tipped bill, mostly brown rump and thinly-barred uppertail in flight.','Coastal mudflats and occasionally inland freshwater areas.','When feeding, probes deeply into soil; usually associates with similar-sized and larger waders.',34.0,36.0,'oc/wet','grey/white/brown','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',117,'Pin-tailed Snipe','Gallinago stenura','Berkik Ekor Jarum','针尾沙锥','Non-rarity','M','One of three difficult-to-identify Gallinago snipes in Singapore. From Common Snipe, most obviously differentiated by a lack of clear white trailing edge to the secondaries, shorter bill and larger-headed appearance (see that species for more differences). Apart from a long list of overlapping and weakly defined separation features, only truly differentiable from Swinhoe''s Snipe with a clear view of the spread tail (or measurements in the hand). This species has one (vs. more than one in Swinhoe''s) intermediate-width feather between the wide central tail feathers and the eight (or, less frequently, six, seven, or nine) pin-like feathers on the outer-tail. These feathers are referred to as "pins" as they are extremely narrow, less than 2 mm wide. On Swinhoe''s, only the outermost pair of tail feathers are narrow (varying from 2 to 4 mm wide), while the rest gradually increase in width towards the central feathers (giving the impression of at least two intermediate-width tail feathers outside the central few, while Pin-tailed shows only one when tail is fully spread).','Damp grasslands, edges of waterbodies, and muddy freshwater marshes.','Flushed Pin-tailed Snipes tend to vocalize more than flushed Swinhoe''s Snipes; a snipe that is silent when flushed is more likely Swinhoe''s than Pin-tailed, but this is only suggestive. Vocal differences between the two species are poorly understood and more study may reveal that differentiation by flight calls is possible.',25.0,27.0,'wet/fst','brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',118,'Swinhoe''s Snipe','Gallinago megala','Berkik Siberia Selatan','大沙锥','Rarity','M','The rarest of three Gallinago snipes in Singapore, but possibly overlooked due to difficulty in separation from Pin-tailed. From Common Snipe, most obviously differentiated by a lack of clear white trailing edge to the secondaries, shorter bill and larger-headed appearance (see that species for more differences). Apart from a series of overlapping and weakly defined separation features, only truly differentiable from Pin-tailed Snipe with a clear view of the spread tail (or measurements in the hand). On this species, only the outermost pair of tail feathers are narrow (varying from 2 to 4 mm wide), while the rest gradually increase in width towards the central feathers (giving the impression of at least two intermediate-width tail feathers outside the central few, while Pin-tailed shows one intermediate-width feather between the central tail feathers and the six to nine pin-like feathers on the outertail).','Damp grasslands, edges of waterbodies, and muddy freshwater marshes.','Flushed Swinhoe''s Snipes are often silent. A snipe that is silent when flushed is more likely Swinhoe''s than Pin-tailed, but this is only suggestive. Vocal differences between the two species are poorly understood and more study may reveal that differentiation by flight calls is possible.',27.0,29.0,'wet','brown/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',119,'Common Snipe','Gallinago gallinago','Berkik Kipas Erasia','扇尾沙锥','Non-rarity','M','The easiest to identify of the three snipes that winter locally; several distinctive features can be used to reliably tell this species apart from both Pin-tailed and Swinhoe''s. Structurally, Common is distinctly sleeker, smaller-headed, and longer-billed than both those species; in plumage, is obviously more "contrasty", especially evident on the facial feathers (loral line especially darker and more prominent in Common). Most easily distinguished in flight, where broad white trailing-edge to secondaries and uneven markings on underwing (unlike Pin-tailed and Swinhoe''s, which have evenly-barred underwing patterns) separate this species.','Damp grasslands with areas of tall grass and muddy freshwater marshes.','Alarm call, normally heard when flushed, is a sharp "skaap"; its zigzag flight when flushed can also be used, in combination with other features, to separate this species from the other snipes found locally.',25.0,27.0,'wet/fst','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',120,'Terek Sandpiper','Xenus cinereus','Kedidi Sereng','翘嘴鹬','Non-rarity','M','A short-legged sandpiper with distinctive upturned bill. While its orange-red legs recall Common Redshank, Terek shows much shorter legs and an upturned bill. In flight, lacks white wing-bar (unlike Common Sandpiper), and has prominent white trailing edge to wing.','Winters mostly on coastal mudflats and sandflats.','Often associates with Common Redshanks and other waders, especially at Sungei Buloh.',22.0,25.0,'oc','grey/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',121,'Red-necked Phalarope','Phalaropus lobatus','Kedidi-Jarum Leher Merah','红颈瓣蹼鹬','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding adult has mostly greyish upperparts, whitish underparts, isolated blackish mask and needle-like blackish bill. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has darker to blackish crown, upperparts and wing-coverts.','Open sea, marshes near the coast and mudflats.','Mostly winters at open sea.',17.0,19.0,'wet/fst','white/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',122,'Common Sandpiper','Actitis hypoleucos','Kedidi-Kelicap Biasa','矶鹬','Non-rarity','M','Small, short-legged sandpiper; clean white underparts apart from brownish breast patch forming a "bib" (rather than a strip across the breast as in Green Sandpiper). Grey-tailed Tattler is longer-billed, larger, and longer-legged.','A wide range of waterbodies –including canals, drains, mudflats, reservoirs, and small ponds.','Distinctive flight action consisting of sharp, stiff wing-beats. Often bobs tail up and down. Usually rather vocal, especially in flight.',19.0,21.0,'oc','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',123,'Green Sandpiper','Tringa ochropus','Kedidi-Hijau Erasia','白腰草鹬','Rarity','Va','A medium-sized sandpiper with dark upperparts and contrasting clean white underparts. Most likely to be confused with Common Sandpiper and Wood Sandpiper. Best told from Common Sandpiper by longer bill, significantly longer legs, and dark (rather than white) outer breast which forms a dark "strip" across the whole breast (while Common appears to show a "bib"). From Wood Sandpiper, told by noticeably darker upperparts with less pale spotting, much darker breast, and supercilium which does not extend behind the eye (or only faintly present behind the eye, at best).','Inland freshwater areas, such as canals and marshes; also intertidal areas on occasion.','Typically associates with Wood Sandpipers in freshwater habitat, where it is normally difficult to tell apart from that species. Stance and feeding action closer to Wood than to Common Sandpiper.',21.0,24.0,'wet','green/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',124,'Grey-tailed Tattler','Tringa brevipes','Kedidi-Kacau Asia','灰尾漂鹬','Rarity','M','A rather stockily-built sandpiper; in breeding plumage (which is sometimes retained until October or even later), shows grey upperparts, underparts white with wide, thin chevron-shaped markings across breast, flank and vent. In non-breeding plumage, white throat and brownish-grey wash over breast and upper belly; rest of underparts clean white. Differentiated from other similar species by combination of short yellow legs (compared to Common Redshank, Common Greenshank, Marsh Sandpiper, and all other Tringa sandpipers except Nordmann''s Greenshank, which have longer legs); short, blunt-tipped bill (compared to Terek Sandpiper and much rarer Nordmann''s Greenshank, which have upturned bills).','Intertidal mudflats, mangroves, occasionally inland wetlands.','Often associates with other waders — in the past, has been recorded with Common Redshanks at Sungei Buloh.',24.0,27.0,'oc/wet','grey','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',125,'Common Redshank','Tringa totanus','Kedidi Kaki Merah Biasa','红脚鹬','Non-rarity','M','A medium-sized wader with distinctive, bright orange-red legs. Similar to the much rarer Spotted Redshank, but much shorter- and thicker-billed with significantly less red on bill base; in flight, also shows extensive white on secondaries. Grey-tailed Tattler, which is greyer overall and shorter-legged, has yellow rather than red legs; Terek Sandpiper may show orange legs but has a highly distinctive upturned bill. Black spotting on breast, lower flanks, vent, and upperparts in breeding plumage fades in non-breeding season, but is still apparent on some individuals as late as August.','Mudflats, sandflats, and brackish lagoons.','Normally gregarious. Highly active while feeding, running to grab food, occasionally probing.',30.0,34.0,'oc/wet','brown/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',126,'Marsh Sandpiper','Tringa stagnatilis','Kedidi Paya','泽鹬','Non-rarity','M','A medium-sized wader with a distinctive pencil-thin bill and long legs. Like Common Greenshank, lightly spotted (breeding plumage) or clean white (non-breeding plumage) below, with greyish-brown upperparts and yellow legs. Differs, however, from that species by its thin and straight (rather than slightly upturned) bill; overall, Marsh is smaller-bodied and more elegant.','Mudflats, sandflats, and brackish lagoons.','Joins flocks of other waders; often found with Common Greenshanks. Normally wades in shallow water.',22.0,25.0,'oc/wet','grey/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',127,'Wood Sandpiper','Tringa glareola','Kedidi Sawah','林鹬','Non-rarity','M','A medium-sized wader with yellowish green legs. From the similar looking Common Sandpiper by its taller looking, more upright posture and more spotted upperparts. The similar but rare Green Sandpiper also has spotted upperparts, but typically has a more horizontal posture like the Common Sandpiper, and with supercilium that does not extend past the eye. The Grey-tailed Tattler, that is typically not found in the same habitat, has much cleaner upperparts, brighter green legs and thicker looking bill.','Freshwater marshes.','Often seen in small flocks together with Common Sandpipers and occasionally with Little Ringed Plovers.',18.5,21.0,'oc/wet','grey/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',128,'Spotted Redshank','Tringa erythropus','Kedidi Kaki Merah Hitam','鹤鹬','Rarity','Va','A medium-sized wader with distinctive, bright red legs. Breeding plumage (unexpected in Singapore) all black, very distinctive. Non-breeding plumage similar to the Common Redshank, but with brighter red legs and thinner, black bill with distinct red bill base on the lower mandible. Lacks white trailing edge on wings when seen in flight. Grey-tailed Tattler, which is greyer overall and shorter-legged, has yellow rather than red legs; Terek Sandpiper may show orange legs but has a highly distinctive upturned bill.','Mudflats, sandflats, brackish lagoons, freshwater marshes','Gregarious, prefers to feed in deep water.',29.0,32.0,'wet','brown/white/red','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',129,'Common Greenshank','Tringa nebularia','Kedidi Kaki Hijau Biasa','青脚鹬','Non-rarity','M','A medium-sized wader with dirty green legs. Similar to the very rare Nordmann''s Greenshank, but with thinner and duller bill, duller legs and darker looking upperparts. Distinguished from the uncommon Marsh Sandpiper by its bigger size and thicker bill with greenish bill base.','Mudflats, sandflats and brackish lagoons.','Gregarious, though they do not seem to associate with Common Redshanks locally.',27.0,29.0,'oc/wet','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sandpipers, Snipes (Scolopacidae)',130,'Nordmann''s Greenshank','Tringa guttifer','Kedidi Kaki Hijau Berbintik','小青脚鹬','Rarity','Va','Adult resembles Common Greenshank but has thicker, distinctively bi-coloured and slightly upturned bill, faintly streaked crown, nape and sides of breast, plainer upperparts without obvious dark markings on wing-coverts and shorter, yellowish legs. Shows all white uppertail-coverts when in flight and toes do not extend beyond tail-tip.','Mudflats and sandflats.',NULL,29.0,32.0,'wet','grey/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Coursers, Pratincoles (Glareolidae)',131,'Oriental Pratincole','Glareola maldivarum','Kedidi-Padang Biasa','普通燕鸻','Non-rarity','M','A medium-sized greyish bird with very distinct facial and throat markings. It''s shape is somewhat similar to a tern, both when perches and in flight with its long, slender and pointed wings. Underwings coverts are bright red. The similar and very rare Small Pratincole is much more compact in shape, lacks facial markings and has black underwing coverts.','Freshwater marshes, open country, coastal lagoons','Often observed migrating in the day during October to November in flocks exceeding 100 birds. Single birds occasionally found in freshwater puddles.',23.0,24.0,'wet','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Coursers, Pratincoles (Glareolidae)',132,'Small Pratincole','Glareola lactea','Kedidi-Padang Kecil','灰燕鸻','Rarity','Va','Adult can be distinguished from Oriental Pratincole by smaller size, greyer upperparts, paler throat with no dark border and buffish grey breast. Juvenile resembles adult but throat bordered by brownish spots/streaks.','Open country near water.',NULL,16.0,19.0,'oc','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',133,'Brown-headed Gull','Chroicocephalus brunnicephalus','Camar-Topeng Asia','棕头鸥','Rarity','Va','Breeding/non-breeding adult and juvenile resembles Black-headed Gull but is larger, bulkier and thicker-billed with pale eyes. In flight, shows distinctive broadly black-tipped outer primaries.','Mudflat and other coastal habitats.','Rests on mudflats with Black-headed Gull as well as terns and other shorebirds. Often rests buoyantly on the sea.',42.0,46.0,'oc/wet','grey/white/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',134,'Black-headed Gull','Chroicocephalus ridibundus','Camar-Topeng Erasia','红嘴鸥','Rarity','M','Non-breeding adult has mostly white head with prominent dark ear spots, white nape and underparts, pale grey mantle, dark eyes, reddish bill with black tip and dark red legs/feet. Breeding adult has dark brown hood with broken white eyering and darker red bill. First winter bird resembles non-breeding adult but has duller bill and legs, buff-brown markings on upperwings and blackish subterminal tail-band.','Mudflat and other coastal habitats.','Feeds on varied food items such as aquatic and terrestrial insects, earthworms, marine invertebrates, some fish, grains and berries.',35.0,39.0,'oc/wet','grey/white/black','fly/fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',135,'Gull-billed Tern','Gelochelidon nilotica','Camar Paruh Tebal Biasa','鸥嘴噪鸥','Rarity','M','Non-breeding adult resembles Whiskered Tern but much larger and thicker-billed, has white head with blackish ear-coverts, pale silvery-grey rump and shallow forked tail. Breeding adult has black forehead to nape.','Open seas and mudflat.','Has a broad diet and does not depend on fish like other tern species, feeding on insects, small crabs and other prey snatched from the ground, air, or even bushes.',34.5,37.5,'oc/wet','white/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',136,'Caspian Tern','Hydroprogne caspia','Camar Raya','红嘴巨鸥','Rarity','Va','The largest of the tern species. Non-breeding adult has diagnostic thick red bill, mostly black crown, nape and mask with whiter, dark-mottled forecrown and black subterminal marking on bill-tip. Breeding adult has all black forehead to nape and mask. First winter bird resembles non-breeding adult but has darker secondaries, primary upperwing-coverts and tail.','Coastal pools, mudflats and sandflats.','Forages by hovering over shallow waters and plunge-dives when a fish is spotted.',48.0,55.0,'oc/wet','white/black/red','fly/fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',137,'Greater Crested Tern','Thalasseus bergii','Camar Berjambul Besar','大凤头燕鸥','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult has distinctive long, thick cold yellow bill, darkish grey upperparts, white face and forecrown, blackish hindcrown with whitish streaks and blackish nape. Breeding adult has bright yellow bill, black crown to nape with shaggy crest and white extreme forehead. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has duller bill and brownish feathers with whitish fringes on mantle and back.','Open seas, sea-coasts, mudflats and sandflats.','Feeds mostly at sea by plunge diving or by dipping from the surface. Food is usually swallowed in mid-air.',45.0,49.0,'oc/wet','grey/white','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',138,'Lesser Crested Tern','Thalasseus bengalensis','Camar Berjambul Kecil','小凤头燕鸥','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult resembles Greater Crested Tern but is smaller and has orange bill. Breeding adult has black crown and nape (including extreme forehead) and brighter orange bill. Juvenile distinguished from juvenile Greater Crested Tern by orange bill.','Open seas, sea-coasts, mudflats and sandflats.','Feeds by plunge-diving for fish.',35.0,40.0,'oc/wet','grey/white/black','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',139,'Little Tern','Sternula albifrons','Camar Kecil Biasa','白额燕鸥','Non-rarity','M/R','Easily distinguished from Whiskered and White-wing Terns that share same habitat by small size and short-tailed appearance. Non-breeding adult has dark bill, legs and feet, white lores and forecrown, blackish hindcrown with whitish streaks and black nape. Breeding adult has yellow bill with black tip, black crown, nape, eyestripe and well defined white forehead. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has dark subterminal markings on mantle, scapulars, tertials and wing-coverts.','Open seas, coastal habitats, mudflats, marshes and reservoirs.','Forages by hovering over water surface before diving in with body rarely becomes fully submerged.',22.0,25.0,'oc','white/black','fly/fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',140,'Aleutian Tern','Onychoprion aleuticus','Camar Batu Kelabu','白腰燕鸥','Non-rarity','M','A medium-size tern with greyish upperparts, white rump and long deeply, forked tail, discontinuous dark band on under trailing edge and all black pointed bill. When in breeding plumage, white forehead contrasts with black eyestripe, hindcrown and nape. Crown of non-breeding bird mostly white with blackish ear-coverts and nape. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has dark brown subterminal markings on upperparts.','Open seas.','Feeds by plunge-diving. Often perches on floating objects and debris.',32.0,34.0,'oc','grey/black/white','branch/fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',141,'Bridled Tern','Onychoprion anaethetus','Camar Batu Biasa','褐翅燕鸥','Non-rarity','M/R','Non-breeding adult has dark brownish-grey upper side, thin whitish nuchal band, whitish forehead-patch, blackish crown, nape and mask, deeply forked tail and blackish bill, legs and feet. Breeding adult has clean white forehead and short eyebrow contrast with black eyestripe, crown and nape. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has whitish tips and dark subterminal bars on upperparts and wing-coverts.','Open seas.','Seldom dives, preferring to pick up food material from the water surface. Feeds in the open seas, rarely coming to coastal waters.',37.0,42.0,'oc','grey/black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',142,'Black-naped Tern','Sterna sumatrana','Camar Tengkuk Hitam','黑枕燕鸥','Non-rarity','R','Adult has white head, neck, breast and underparts with narrow black band from eyes to hindnape, dark pinkish legs and feet which appeared blackish from far, all black bill and whitish-grey mantle and upperwings. Juvenile resembles adult but has blackish subterminal markings on mantle feathers, scapulars and tertials .','Sea-coasts and open seas.','Nest is a scrape on ground or eggs laid on bare rock.',30.0,35.0,'oc','white/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',143,'Common Tern','Sterna hirundo','Camar Siput','普通燕鸥','Rarity','M','Non-breeding adult has slender, pointed blackish bill, dark red legs and feet, white forehead and lores, blackish mask and nape, greyish mantle and long deeply forked tail (at rest, tail same length with tips of folded wings). Breeding adult has orange-red bill with black tip, black forehead to nape and long tail-streamers. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has blackish leading edge to upperwing.','Open seas, coastal habitats, mudflats, marshes and reservoirs.','Fishes by plunging steeply into water.',33.0,37.0,'oc/wet','grey/brown/white','swim/fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',144,'Whiskered Tern','Chlidonias hybrida','Camar Tasik Bermisai Biasa','须浮鸥','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult has relatively short, blackish bill, mask, hindcrown and nape, white crown with dark streaks at rear, dark reddish legs/feet, shortish shallow forked tail and uniform grey upperside. Breeding adult has dark red bill/legs/feet and black forehead to nape. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has buff-brown markings on scapulars and back.','Open seas, coastal habitats, mudflats, marshes and reservoirs.','Usually seen with White-winged and Little Terns. Feeds largely by skimming low over water surface.',24.0,28.0,'oc/wet','grey/black/white','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gulls, Terns, Skimmers (Laridae)',145,'White-winged Tern','Chlidonias leucopterus','Camar Tasik Sayap Putih','白翅浮鸥','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult resembles Whiskered Tern but has finer bill, distinctive isolated roundish ear-patch (headphones) and whitish rump/uppertail-coverts. Breeding adult has all black head, body and underwing-coverts. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has buff-brown markings on scapulars and back.','Open seas, coastal habitats, mudflats, marshes and reservoirs.','Gathers in small loose flocks, feeding by wheeling and skimming low over water surface.',20.0,24.0,'oc/wet','white/black','fly/fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Skuas (Stercorariidae)',146,'Pomarine Jaeger','Stercorarius pomarinus','Camar-Lanun Ekor Sudu','中贼鸥','Rarity','Va','The biggest of the three jaegers. Has distinct twisted central tail feathers in the adult breeding plumage. In all plumages, the white feather bases to the primaries and primary coverts gives a "double flash" impression.','Open seas.','A pelagic species often observed engaging in kleptoparasitism, a behaviour where they snatch food from other less aggressive pelagic birds such as terns.',47.0,61.5,'sea','brown/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Skuas (Stercorariidae)',147,'Parasitic Jaeger','Stercorarius parasiticus','Camar-Lanun Paruh Lampai','短尾贼鸥','Rarity','M','Smaller than the similar looking Pomarine Jaeger. Lacks the twisted central tail feathers in the adult breeding plumage unlike the Pomarine Jaeger. In all plumages, the white feather bases to the primaries gives a "single flash" impression.','Open seas.','A pelagic species often observed engaging in kleptoparasitism, a behaviour where they snatch food from other less aggressive pelagic birds such as terns.',42.0,54.5,'sea','black/brown/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Skuas (Stercorariidae)',148,'Long-tailed Jaeger','Stercorarius longicaudus','Camar-Lanun Ekor Panjang','长尾贼鸥','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding adult resembles Pomarine and Parasitic Jaeger but is more slender looking and has no whitish flash on primaries especially the underwing. Breeding adult can be separated from the other two Jaeger species by its long pointed central tail-feathers, mostly whitish underparts with no breast-band, greyish belly and vent, two-tone upperwing where the coverts are paler than the secondaries and uniform all dark underwing.','Open seas',NULL,47.0,67.5,'oc','grey/black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Tropicbirds (Phaethontidae)',149,'White-tailed Tropicbird','Phaethon lepturus','Camar-Pita Paruh Kuning','白尾鹲','Rarity','Va','Adult is distinctively looking with whitish overall plumage, very long central tail feathers, diagonal black band across upperwing coverts, blackish patch at outer primaries, black mask and yellowish bill. Ssp. fulvus which breeds on Christmas Island has a golden wash to its white plumage and is also known as the Golden Bosunbird. Juvenile lacks the central tail feathers and black diagonal band and has black bars/scales on mantle.','Open seas.','Wanders widely outside breeding season.',38.0,41.0,'oc','white/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Northern Storm Petrels (Hydrobatidae)',150,'Swinhoe''s Storm Petrel','Hydrobates monorhis','Lelayang-Laut Kelam Asia','黑叉尾海燕','Non-rarity','M','Small size, forked tail and overall sooty brown plumage with contrasting paler diagonal bar across upperwing-coverts.','Open seas.','Usually observed in small groups during migration, flying and gliding just above the water surface.',20.0,20.0,'oc','grey/brown/black','fly/swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Petrels, Shearwaters, Diving Petrels (Procellariidae)',151,'Wedge-tailed Shearwater','Ardenna pacifica','Itik-itik Dahi Putih','楔尾鹱','Rarity','Va','Dark morph with dark brown plumage throughout, distinguished from Short-tailed Shearwater by longer toe extension past tail and proportionally longer bill to head ratio. Pale morph with dark brown upperparts, from regionally expected (but still unrecorded) Streaked Shearwater by lack of white on face and presence of black borders on leading edge of the underwing.','Open seas.','Flight direct, consisting of rapid wing beats interspersed between long glides.',38.0,47.0,'oc','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Petrels, Shearwaters, Diving Petrels (Procellariidae)',152,'Short-tailed Shearwater','Ardenna tenuirostris','Itik-itik Ekor Pendek Pasifik','短尾鹱','Rarity','M','Overall dark sooty-brown plumage with pale chin, slightly paler breast and belly, prominent whitish area at the centre of underwing and toes extend beyond tip of short tail when in flight.','Open seas','Flight direct, consisting of a flapping rise followed by a long downward glide.',41.0,43.0,'oc','grey/brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Petrels, Shearwaters, Diving Petrels (Procellariidae)',153,'Bulwer''s Petrel','Bulweria bulwerii','Tekukur-Laut Biasa','褐燕鹱','Rarity','Va','Resembles Swinhoe’s Storm-Petrel but larger, with longer wings and distinctive long, graduated tail. Can be distinguished from similar looking Short-tailed Shearwater from its smaller size and the pale diagonal band across its upperwing-coverts.','Open seas','Flight buoyant and usually close to the water surface.',26.0,27.0,'sea','brown','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Storks (Ciconiidae)',154,'Milky Stork','Mycteria cinerea','Upih Bakau','白鹮鹳','Non-rarity','I','Only similar species recorded locally is Painted Stork, with which this species interbreeds extensively. Differentiated from Painted by three main traits, which must all be present in combination: a clean white breast (Painted has a black breast-band); no pink flush on the tertials, inner secondaries, and wing-coverts; and clean white upperwing-coverts (Painted has black-and-white spotting on the upperwing-coverts). Individuals which lack any of these features cannot be identified as pure Milky Storks.','Mangroves, mudflats, and coasts.','Gregarious, joining flocks with Painted Storks and hybrid Milky x Painted Storks.',95.0,100.0,'wet/sea','white/black','swim/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Storks (Ciconiidae)',155,'Painted Stork','Mycteria leucocephala','Upih Sawah','彩鹳','Non-rarity','I','Only similar species recorded locally is Milky Stork, with which this species interbreeds extensively. Differentiated from Milky by three main traits, which must all be present in combination: a distinct and complete black breast-band with white barring (Milky has a clean white breast, while hybrids may show an indistinct or weak breastband); a clear pink flush on the tertials, inner secondaries, and wing-coverts; and black-and-white spotting on the upperwing-coverts (Milky has clean white upperwing-coverts). Individuals which lack any of these features cannot be identified as pure Painted Storks.','Mangroves, mudflats, and coasts.','Gregarious, joining flocks with Milky Storks and hybrid Milky x Painted Storks.',93.0,102.0,'wet/sea','white/black/red','swim/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Storks (Ciconiidae)',156,'Asian Openbill','Anastomus oscitans','Upih-Siput Asia','钳嘴鹳','Rarity','Va','Adult has diagnostic dull yellowish-grey bill with open spaces between mandibles and long pinkish-grey legs. Body is mostly greyish-white with contrasting glossy black flight feathers and tail. Juvenile likes adult but body more brownish grey and bill has no spaces between mandibles.','Freshwater marshes, flooded fields and padi fields.','A small flock of 6 adults were observed feeding on Golden Apple Snails (an introduced species) at a flooded field along West Camp Road.',68.0,81.0,'wet','grey/black',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Storks (Ciconiidae)',157,'Lesser Adjutant','Leptoptilos javanicus','Burung-Botak Kecil','秃鹳','Non-rarity','R','Large bird with mostly horn-coloured bill, pale forehead, vinous-tinged head-sides (redder when breeding), yellowish neck, glossy black upperparts, white underparts and dark greyish legs. Shows all blackish wings with white patch on inner underwing coverts in flight.','Freshwater wetlands, mangroves and sometimes mudflats.','Feeds mainly on fish, frogs, reptiles and large invertebrates. Usually solitary except during breeding season when they form loose colonies.',122.5,129.0,'wet','black/white/yellow','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Frigatebirds (Fregatidae)',158,'Lesser Frigatebird','Fregata ariel','Simbang Kecil','白斑军舰鸟','Rarity','Va','Male has overall blackish plumage with prominent whitish patches extending from side of body to inner underwing-coverts and red gular pouch. Female has black hood and belly with white on the rest of underparts, extending in axillary spur onto inner underwing-coverts. Juvenile resembles female but has rufous to brownish white head, white belly and black breast-band. Apart from size, difficult to distinguish from juvenile Christmas Frigatebird but possibly has narrower black breast-band.','Open seas','Catches flying fish in mid-flight and harasses other sea birds to force them to disgorge their catch which is then caught in mid-air.',71.0,81.0,'oc','black/white/yellow','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gannets, Boobies (Sulidae)',159,'Red-footed Booby','Sula sula','Angsa-Laut Kaki Merah','红脚鲣鸟','Rarity','Va','Occurs in a variety of colour morphs but all have feet of the distinctive red color which gives them their name. Adult white morph has mostly white plumage with contrasting black flight feathers while the brown form has dark greyish brown plumage with darker flight feathers and light bluish-grey bill/facial skin. Adult of the intermediate form resembles white morph but has brown mantle, back and wing-coverts. Juvenile brown morph resembles adult but has dark grey bill and purplish facial skin. Immature white morph often shows diffuse darker breast-band and untidy whitish area on wing coverts.','Open seas and sometimes coastal waters.','Strong flyers that feed by diving vertically into the water. Once in the water, the birds use their webbed feet to aid swimming.',68.0,72.5,'sea','brown/white/red','fly/swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Gannets, Boobies (Sulidae)',160,'Brown Booby','Sula leucogaster','Angsa-Laut Biasa','褐鲣鸟','Rarity','Va','Adult has distinctive dark chocolate-brown plumage with contrasting white lower breast to vent and mostly white underwing-coverts. Female is slight larger than male. Juvenile has somewhat paler brown plumage and washed dusky-brownish lower breast.','Open seas and sometimes coastal waters.','More regularly sighted over shallow inshore waters than other Booby species.',73.0,83.0,'sea','brown/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Anhingas, Darters (Anhingidae)',161,'Oriental Darter','Anhinga melanogaster','Kosa-Ular Asia','黑腹蛇鹈','Non-rarity','Vi','Distinguished from Cormorant species by the longish slender pointed bill, long thin neck and relatively long tail. Body glossy black with bold white streaks on upper mantle, scapulars and coverts. Head and neck brownish with pale throat and long whitish stripe extending from eye down to neck-side.','Lakes, marshes, large rivers and quarry ponds.','Hunt for fishes with body fully submerged and only head above water.',85.0,97.0,'wet/pnr','black/grey/white','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ibises, Spoonbills (Threskiornithidae)',162,'Glossy Ibis','Plegadis falcinellus','Sekendi Kilat Biasa','彩鹮','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding adult has mostly uniform dark brownish plumage, white streaks on head and neck, green gloss on scapulars and upperwing-coverts and long down-curved bill. Adult in breeding plumage has glossed green forecrown and deep chestnut head, neck and body with no streaks. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but duller.','Mudflats and marshy wetlands.','Forages mostly by wading in shallow water, probing in soft mud for food.',55.0,65.0,'wet','brown/green','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',163,'Yellow Bittern','Ixobrychus sinensis','Gelam Kuning','黄苇鳽','Non-rarity','M/R','Male has blackish crown and uppertail-coverts, pale brownish mantle, yellowish-buff underparts with light streaks down foreneck and upper breast and blackish flight feathers that contrast sharply with pale buff wing coverts. Female resembles male but has reddish brown crown. Juvenile resembles female but has bolder streaks on crown, upperparts and underparts.','Grasslands and marshes near freshwater wetlands, well-vegetated ponds and mangroves.',NULL,36.0,38.0,'wet/pnr','brown/white/yellow','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',164,'Von Schrenck''s Bittern','Ixobrychus eurhythmus','Gelam Belakang Coklat','紫背苇鳽','Non-rarity','M','Male has dark chestnut upperparts contrasting strongly with mostly buffish underparts and wing-coverts. Female and juvenile resembles Cinnamon Bittern but has the distinctive black median crown stripe and much bolder white to buff speckling and spotting on upperparts and upperwing-coverts.','Freshwater marshes, forest streams, well-vegetated ponds and mangroves.','Similar to other bitterns where it perches motionless for long periods before feeding.',39.0,42.0,'wet/pnr','Buff/brown','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',165,'Cinnamon Bittern','Ixobrychus cinnamomeus','Gelam Bendang','栗苇鳽','Non-rarity','M/R','Male has distinctive uniform bright cinnamon-rufous wings and upperparts while female has slightly darker upperparts with vague buffish speckling on scapulars and upperwing-coverts. Juvenile resembles female but has buffish streaks on sides of head and dense buffish speckling on upperparts and upperwing-coverts.','Grasslands and marshes near freshwater wetlands and occasionally mangroves.','Often seen in flight. Sometimes perches motionless for long periods before feeding.',38.0,41.0,'wet/pnr','Buff/brown/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',166,'Black Bittern','Ixobrychus flavicollis','Gelam Hitam','黑鳽','Non-rarity','M','Male has black upperparts, whitish throat, whitish breast with dense dark streaks, and yellow neck-patch. Female resembles male but has darker brown upperparts and more rufescent breast-streaks. Juvenile resemble female but feathers of the crown and upperside have narrow rufous fringes, giving a scaly appearance.','Marshes, reedbeds in ponds, and mangroves.','Often secretive, hiding in reeds for long periods of time.',54.0,61.0,'wet/pnr','grey/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',167,'Malayan Night Heron','Gorsachius melanolophus','Pucung-Harimau Ubun Hitam','黑冠鳽','Non-rarity','M','Adult has deep rufous head-sides and neck with black crown and long crest, chestnut-tinged brown upperparts, wings-coverts and upper-breast and densely marked blackish and whitish belly/vent. Juvenile is duller than adults and has densed irregular whitish to buffish and greyish bars and vermiculations on underparts and wings-coverts.','Forest, forest edge, gardens, parks and wooded areas.',NULL,48.0,51.0,'pnr/resd','brown/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',168,'Black-crowned Night Heron','Nycticorax nycticorax','Pucung-Kuak Biasa','夜鹭','Non-rarity','R','Non-breeding adult has greyish-white overall plumage with contrasting black crown, mantle and scapulars, yellow legs/feet, whitish nape-plumes and mostly blackish bill. Breeding adult has glossed bluish-green mantle/scapulars and reddish legs. Juvenile is duller brown overall with white-spotted upperparts and streaked crown, head-sides and underparts.','Marshes, mangroves and waterbodies near parks/gardens.','Highly gregarious and mostly seen at dawn and dusk.',58.0,65.0,'wet/pnr','white/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',169,'Striated Heron','Butorides striata','Pucung-Bakau Biasa','绿鹭','Non-rarity','M/R','Adult has mostly slaty grey plumage with blackish crown and long black nape-plumes, blackish bill with yellow base at lower mandible and yellowish-orange legs. Juvenile resembles Black-crowned Night Heron but has darker brown overall plumage, dark brownish crown and longer and slimmer bill.','Marshes, mangroves, waterbodies near parks/gardens and coastal areas.',NULL,40.0,48.0,'wet/pnr','blue','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',170,'Indian Pond Heron','Ardeola grayii','Pucung-Padi Kelabu','印度池鹭','Rarity','M','Indistinguishable from other pond-heron species when in non-breeding and juvenile plumage. Adult in breeding plumage has distinctive brownish-buff head, neck and breast with long white head-plumes, whitish throat and dark brownish-maroon mantle and scapulars.','Various wetlands like streams, marshes, ponds and open wooded areas.','Diet comprises fish, frogs, crustaceans and insects.',45.0,45.0,'wet','grey/blue','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',171,'Chinese Pond Heron','Ardeola bacchus','Pucung-Padi Cina','池鹭','Non-rarity','M','Indistinguishable from other pond-heron species when in non-breeding and juvenile plumage. Adult in breeding plumage has distinctive chestnut-maroon head, head-plumes, neck and upperbreast, white underparts and blacklish-slate mantle and scapulars.','Various wetlands like streams, marshes, ponds and open fields.','Diet comprises fish, frogs, crustaceans and insects.',45.0,52.0,'wet','red/black/white','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',172,'Javan Pond Heron','Ardeola speciosa','Pucung-Padi Emas','爪哇池鹭','Rarity','M','Indistinguishable from other pond-heron species when in non-breeding and juvenile plumage. Adult in breeding plumage has distinctive pale brownish-buff to creamy-whitish head and neck with white head-plumes, deep cinnamon-rufous breast, white belly and blacklish-slate mantle and scapulars.','Various wetlands like streams, marshes, ponds and open fields.','Diet comprises fish, frogs, crustaceans and insects.',45.0,45.0,'wet','white/brown/grey','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',173,'Eastern Cattle Egret','Bubulcus coromandus','Bangau Pendek Timur','牛背鹭','Non-rarity','I/M','Non-breeding adult resembles other white egret species but smaller, stockier with short and relatively thick neck, short yellowish bill and blackish legs and feet. Adult in breeding plumage has extensive rufous-buff on head/neck/breast/back, reddish bill with yellow tip, purplish lores and reddish legs. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult.','Grasslands, various wetland habitats and sometimes mudflats.','Gregarious and often feeds near cattle.',48.0,53.0,'wet','white/brown','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',174,'Grey Heron','Ardea cinerea','Pucung Seriap Biasa','苍鹭','Non-rarity','R','Non-breeding adult has grey upperparts, mostly white head and neck with prominent broad black head-stripes and blackish streaks down centre of foreneck, black nape-plumes, whitish underparts, black shoulder-patch and dull yellowish bill. Breeding adult has bright orange-yellow bill, legs and feet. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but is duller and has less contrasting head and neck pattern and much shorter head-plumes.','Mangroves and various inland and coastal wetlands.','Feeds on large fish.',90.0,98.0,'wet','white/grey/black','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',175,'Great-billed Heron','Ardea sumatrana','Pucung Seriap Lembu','大嘴鹭','Non-rarity','R','Non-breeding adult resembles a large and long-necked heron with dusky grey overall plumage and long stout dagger shaped bill. Adult in breeding plumage has distinct white-tipped greyish plumes on scapulars and breast. Plumage of juvenile appears warmer-tinged than non-breeding adult.','Mudflats and other coastal habitats.','Usually solitary, stalking prey at the edge of mudflats or estuaries.',114.0,115.0,'wet/oc','black','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',176,'Purple Heron','Ardea purpurea','Pucung Serandau','草鹭','Non-rarity','R','Adult has black crown, black nape-plumes, rufous-chestnut neck with bold black lines down head-sides and neck, dark chestnut-maroon belly/flanks/vent/underwing-coverts, greyish upperparts and mostly yellowish-orange bill/legs/feet. Juvenile resembles adult but has brownish-orange overall plumage and lacks the bold black lines down head-sides/neck.','Well-vegetated freshwater wetlands, marshes, lakes and occasionally coastal wetlands and mangroves.','Often stays hidden in reedbeds or dense vegetation for long periods of time.',78.0,90.0,'wet/pnr','black/blue/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',177,'Great Egret','Ardea alba','Bangau Besar','大白鹭','Non-rarity','M','Plumage of non-breeding adult is all white with heavy yellow bill and black legs. Breeding adult has red legs and black bill. Distinguished from other white Egret species by longer and strongly kinked neck and pointed extension of facial skin (gape line) which extends beyond eye. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult.','Various inland and coastal wetlands, mangroves and mudflats.','Feeds on mostly fish, but will also take amphibians (frogs), aquatic invertebrates (insects, crayfish), and reptiles (snakes).',85.0,102.0,'wet','white/yellow','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',178,'Intermediate Egret','Ardea intermedia','Bangau Sederhana','中白鹭','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult is distinguished from similar looking Great Egret by smaller size, considerably shorter bill, shorter and less distinctly kinked neck. Also resembles Eastern Cattle Egret but much larger, has thinner neck and longer/darker legs. Breeding adult has longish plumes at back and breast, yellowish bill sometimes with black on tip and ridge of upper mandible. Juvenile resemble non-breeding adult.','Various inland freshwater habitats, marshy grasslands and occasionally mangroves and mudflats.','Often hunts and roosts with other egrets species and herons.',65.0,72.0,'wet/pnr','white/brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',179,'Little Egret','Egretta garzetta','Bangau Kecil','白鹭','Non-rarity','M/Vi','Non-breeding adult shows all-white plumage, black legs (with yellow feet for garzetta) and mostly blackish bill. In transition to breeding plumage, has white plumes behind head. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but has greenish legs.','Various freshwater and coastal wetlands.','Less active feeder than Chinese Egret.',55.0,65.0,'wet','white/black','fly/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',180,'Pacific Reef Heron','Egretta sacra','Bangau Batu Pasifik','岩鹭','Non-rarity','R','Adult dark morph has diagnostic overall dark greyish plumage and greenish legs while adult white morph resembles Chinese Egret but has shorter legs, somewhat thicker, less pointed and mostly yellowish bill.','Rocky shores, islets, beaches, sometimes mudflats and even canals.','Usually solitary or found in pairs. Exclusively coastal in habit preference.',58.0,58.0,'wet','brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Herons, Bitterns (Ardeidae)',181,'Chinese Egret','Egretta eulophotes','Bangau Cina','黄嘴白鹭','Rarity','M','Non-breeding adult resembles other egret species but can be distinguished by greenish legs and yellowish-orange lower mandible. Breeding adult has all yellowish-orange bill, shaggy nuchal crest, blue facial skin, blackish legs with yellowish-orange feet.','Mudflats and other coastal habitats','Feeds actively. Often runs, flies and darts across mudflats in search of food',68.0,68.0,'wet/oc','white/yellow','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ospreys (Pandionidae)',182,'Western Osprey','Pandion haliaetus','Helang-Tiram Biasa','鹗','Non-rarity','M/Vi','A large, white raptor with dark greyish-brown upperparts and a distinct thick eye stripe. Its long and slender wings often look bent around the carpal joints, especially when it is flapping. Adults of the local White-bellied Sea Eagle has much broader wings with solid black trailing edge and lacks the facial pattern. The smaller Black-winged Kites also lack the facial pattern, have a more pointed looking wing, with lighter grey upperparts. Juvenile Rufous-bellied Eagle is similar with its all white underparts and facial pattern, but has shorter and rounder looking wings.','Coastal areas.','This species is almost exclusively fish-eating; it is often observed fish along coastal sites for prolonged periods of time.',55.0,63.0,'wet/pnr','grey/white/black','fish/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',183,'Black-winged Kite','Elanus caeruleus','Helang-Tikus Biasa','黑翅鸢','Non-rarity','R','A white raptor with light grey upperparts and black shoulders. The adults have distinct red iris. The Western Osprey has darker greyish-brown upperparts, a distinct thick black eye stripe with longer and more slender looking wings. The White-bellied Sea Eagle is much bigger in general, with a proportionally larger looking bill, and has broader wings. Juvenile Rufous-bellied Eagle is similar with its all white underparts, but has shorter and rounder looking wings.','Grasslands and open country.','Frequently seen hovering when in search for prey. Nests quite visibly on trees found in open habitat. When the juveniles fledge, the adults are often observed passing food to the young mid-air.',31.0,35.0,'fst/pnr','grey/black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',184,'Crested Honey Buzzard','Pernis ptilorhynchus','Helang-Lebah Asia','凤头蜂鹰','Non-rarity','M/Vi','A vary variable species with plumage colours ranging from white, rufous to black. Has a small pigeon-like head distinct both when perched and in flight. The local torquatus race has a distinct crest. Often confused with the Changeable Hawk-eagle, from which it can be told apart by its smaller head, less rounded (longer and more rectangular) wings, longer tail, and unfeathered tarsus (hard to see when perched). Common and Eastern Buzzard likewise rounder body, proportionally shorter tail and rounder wings as well.','Woodland.','One of the commonest migrants in Singapore and often seen travelling in a convoy. This species has a unique behaviour of raiding bee and hornet hives in search for food, especially larvae. The regional subspecies torquatus, which could potentially be split as a full species in the near future, is sometimes seen in Singapore too, though less frequently.',55.0,65.0,'wet/pnr','black/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',185,'Jerdon''s Baza','Aviceda jerdoni','Helang-Gerigi Perang','褐冠鹃隼','Non-rarity','M','Pale brown underparts with dense dark brown barring, darker brown upperparts, with distinct crest typically seen when perched. Underwing coverts strongly marked dark brown. Combination of plumage features and distinct paddle-like wing shape rules out all other species locally.','Woodland.','Much less common than the congeneric Black Baza, but the small numbers that winter in Singapore tend to form groups as well.',46.0,46.0,'fst/pnr','white/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',186,'Black Baza','Aviceda leuphotes','Helang-Gerigi Hitam','黑冠鹃隼','Non-rarity','M','Distinct black and white hawk with chestnut on the wings (hard to see in flight). Pale Pied Harrier has black restricted to the head and wing tips.','Woodland.','Often observed migrating in big numbers, forming tight, neatly arranged flocks when gliding. Typically arrives in Singapore later than the sparrowhawks and honey buzzards. Also frequently seen roosting in groups, especially (?) at wooded areas with high density of Acacia trees.',31.5,33.0,'fst/pnr','black/red/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',187,'Himalayan Vulture','Gyps himalayensis','Hering Himalaya','高山兀鹫','Rarity','Va','Juvenile when seen in flight has distinctive long, broad wings, short wedge-shaped tail, whitish streaks on brownish mantle and scapulars, broader, more prominent whitish streaks on brownish underparts and underwing coverts contrasting with blackish flight feathers and tail.','Open country',NULL,115.0,125.0,'open','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',188,'Cinereous Vulture','Aegypius monachus','Hering Hitam','秃鹫','Rarity','Va','Large, sooty vulture, with hefty bi-coloured bill and wedge-shaped tail. Head has dark down feathers with blueish-grey patches of bare skin. Juveniles have blacker plumage, with bare skin pinkish instead of blueish-grey. Told apart from Himalayan Vulture by darker plumage, larger bill, and presence of dark down feathers on head.','Hill/mountain forests, scrub, meadows and grasslands.','Feeds on carrion, likely to hunt mainly by vision.',100.0,120.0,'fst/open','black/grey','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',189,'Crested Serpent Eagle','Spilornis cheela','Helang-Kuik Biasa','蛇雕','Non-rarity','R/Vi','Adult has mostly dark brownish plumage, black tail with broad white central band, prominent yellow cere, facial skin and eyes, short blackish crest and small whitish spots/bars on lower breasts and belly. Broad white band across underwing contrasting with broad black trailing edge very prominent when seen in flight from below. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller upperparts with whitish fringes and whitish underparts with dark streaks.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded area, mangroves, gardens and parks.','Feeds primarily on reptiles like snakes, lizards and frogs.',56.0,74.0,'fst/pnr','brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',190,'Short-toed Snake Eagle','Circaetus gallicus','Helang-Ular Utara','短趾雕','Rarity','Va','Pale morph adult has greyish-brown upperparts, rounded brownish head, yellowish eyes, pale underparts with faint dark markings, whitish underwing with some dark barring and pale tail with three dark bands. Dark morph individual resembles pale morph but has distinctive dark hood.','Reclaimed land, wooded grassland, open country and forest.','Usually observed soaring and circling at great heights.',62.0,67.0,'fst/pnr','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',191,'Bat Hawk','Macheiramphus alcinus','Helang Malam','食蝠鸢','Rarity','Vi','A falcon-like bird with yellowish eyes, overall blackish-brown plumage with contrasting whitish throat and center of upper breast and pale legs.','Open areas in or near forest and vicinity of bat caves.','Crepuscular. Diet comprises mainly bats.',46.0,46.0,'fst/open','black',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',192,'Changeable Hawk-Eagle','Nisaetus cirrhatus','Helang-Hindik Biasa','凤头鹰雕','Non-rarity','R','Comes in a dark and pale morph. The latter has dark streaks on its underparts with strongly marked underwings. Juvenile dark morphs are typically similar to adults, while juvenile pale morphs can be told apart by their very plain white underparts. Often confused with Crested Honey Buzzard, from which it can be told apart by its proportionally bigger head, rounder wings, shorter tail and feathered tarsus (if visible).','Woodland.','Frequently heard in various wooded area across Singapore, but beware as some of the sounds heard might turn out to be vocal mimicry by the Greater Racket-tailed Drongo. Previously rare in Singapore but population size has increased tremendously.',61.0,75.0,'fst/pnr','white/brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',193,'Rufous-bellied Eagle','Lophotriorchis kienerii','Helang Perut Merah','棕腹隼雕','Rarity','Vi','Adult has slight crest, blackish head-sides/upperparts, whitish throat/upperbreast and rufous-chestnut belly/vent. In flight shows mostly rufous-chestnut wing-coverts. Juvenile has browner upperparts, whitish head-sides with blackish eyeline and mostly whitish underparts/wing coverts.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth and suitable wooded areas.','Usually glides and soars with wings held level.',53.0,61.0,'fst/pnr','black/white/brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',194,'Greater Spotted Eagle','Clanga clanga','Helang-Bintik Besar','乌雕','Non-rarity','M','Adult can be separated from Eastern Imperial Eagle and Steppe Eagle by darker brown plumage, relatively shorter wings, smallish bill, shortish tail and rather uniformly dark underwing pattern with distinctive whitish patch at base of outer primaries. Juvenile resembles adult but has blackish plumage with distinctive whitish spots on upperwing-coverts and buffish streaks on belly and thighs. This species also has a rare fulvescens morph with mostly buffish to rufous body and wing coverts and contrasting black flight feathers and tail.','Reclaimed land and open country.','Takes carrion.',65.0,72.0,'resd','black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',195,'Booted Eagle','Hieraaetus pennatus','Helang Junam Kecil','靴隼雕','Rarity','M','This is a small crestless raptor with long square-cut tail and diagnostic pale shoulder spots (headlights) on the upperwing which occurs in two morph phases. Dark morph bird has uniform dark brown head and body, blackish flight feathers and pale brown underwing coverts. Pale morph bird has mostly whitish underparts with fine brownish streaks, blackish flight feathers and whitish underwing converts.','Reclaimed land, open country and wooded areas.','Usually solitary, circling and soaring on thermals.',50.0,57.0,'fst/pnr','black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',196,'Steppe Eagle','Aquila nipalensis','Helang Gurun','草原雕','Rarity','Va','Adult resembles Eastern Imperial Eagle but slightly duller, lacks the prominent white markings on upper scapulars and has a small rufous-buff neck patch, paler throat and dark undertail-coverts. Juvenile also resembles juvenile Eastern Imperial Eagle but lacks the dark streaks on nape, neck, breast and wing coverts. Underwing flight pattern of juvenile also shows broad whitish wingbar between coverts and flight feathers.','Reclaimed land and open country.','Takes carrion.',76.0,80.0,'open','brown/black',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',197,'Eastern Imperial Eagle','Aquila heliaca','Helang Tengkuk Kuning Biasa','白肩雕','Rarity','Va','Adult has blackish brown plumage with large head and bill, golden buff supercilium, ear-coverts, nape and hind neck, prominent white markings on upper scapulars and pale undertail-coverts. Juvenile has buffish plumage with distinctive dark streaks on nape, neck, breast and wing coverts (above and below) and dark flight feathers.','Reclaimed land and open country near the coasts.','Takes carrion.',72.0,83.0,'sea','brown/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',198,'Crested Goshawk','Accipiter trivirgatus','Helang-Sewah Besar Berjambul','凤头鹰','Non-rarity','R','This is the only resident and also the largest accipiter species found in Singapore. Adult has short crest, slaty crown and sides of head, brownish-grey upperparts, dark mesial streak, streaked breast and barred belly. Female is larger than male and has browner-tinged crown and head-sides. Juvenile resembles adult but has browner head/upperparts and belly marked with bold dark spots instead of bars.','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas and parks/gardens.','Frequents the canopy and middle storey, usually keeping to thick foliage from which it hunts.',40.0,46.0,'fst/pnr','brown/black/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',199,'Shikra','Accipiter badius','Helang-Sewah Pudar','褐耳鹰','Rarity','Va','Adult male distinct with red iris, strong orange barrings on underparts, greyish upperparts with black wing tips. Female similar, with slightly browner uppersides and yellow iris. Juveniles has brownish upperparts, with tear drop shaped underparts. As with all Accipiters the shape of the bird in flight is very useful in identification. Shikras show five "fingers", a proportionally longer tail compared to all other local Accipiters (except Eurasian Sparrowhawk, which has six "finger" instead).','Woodland.',NULL,30.0,36.0,'fst','brown/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',200,'Chinese Sparrowhawk','Accipiter soloensis','Helang-Sewah Cina','赤腹鹰','Non-rarity','M','Adult Chinese Sparrowhawk can be easily separated from other accipiter species by its dark greyish upperparts, prominent orange-yellow cere, virtually unmarked underwing-coverts and black-tipped primaries. Male has dark red eyes and pink-washed breast while female has yellowish eyes and more rufous-washed breast. Juvenile resembles juvenile Japanaese Sparrowhawk but has very little to moderate markings on underwing-coverts and no yellowish eyering. Both adult and juvenile shows four prominent fingers in flight.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded areas, open country, parks and gardens.',NULL,29.0,35.0,'fst/pnr','grey/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',201,'Japanese Sparrowhawk','Accipiter gularis','Helang-Sewah Jepun','日本松雀鹰','Non-rarity','M','Male has dark greyish-blue upperparts, pinkish-rufous barrings on underparts, reddish eyes with yellow eyering, yellow cere and faint or no mesial streak. Female resembles male but larger and has distinctly browner upperparts, yellowish eyes, more prominent mesial streak and all barred underparts. Juvenile resembles female but has darker brown upperparts, streaked breast and flanks/belly marked with broken bars. Both adult and juvenile shows five prominent fingers in flight.','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas and open country.',NULL,25.0,31.0,'fst/open','grey/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',202,'Besra','Accipiter virgatus','Helang-Sewah Gunung Asia','松雀鹰','Rarity','M','Both sexes and juvenile resemble Japanese Sparrowhawk but has more prominent dark mesial streak and even-width dark and pale tail-bands. Male can be separated from Japanese Sparrowhawk by darker upperparts, blackish breast-streaks and broader rufous-chestnut bars on underparts. Female and juvenile is very similar to juvenile Japanese Sparrowhawk but has blacker breast-streaks and bars on underparts (resembling adult Crested Goshawk).','Open habitat, reclaimed land and offshore island.',NULL,26.0,32.0,'sea','brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',203,'Eurasian Sparrowhawk','Accipiter nisus','Helang-Sewah Erasia','雀鹰','Rarity','Va','Male has slaty-grey upperparts, faint narriow supercilium, orange-rufous head-sides, faint orange-rufous bars on whitish underparts and long slender tail. Female resembles male but much bigger and has brown-tinged upperparts, more prominent whitish supercilium and no orange-rufous head-sides. Juvenile can be best separated from other accipiter species from the relatively larger size, rufous-chestnut to blackish barred underparts and whitish supercilium. Both adult and juvenile appears long-winged and long-tailed in flight, showing six prominent fingers.','Wooded and open areas.','The female is up to 25% larger than the male – one of the largest differences between the sexes in any bird species.',28.0,38.0,'fst/open','orange/white/grey',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',204,'Eastern Marsh Harrier','Circus spilonotus','Helang-Sawah Biasa','白腹鹞','Non-rarity','M','Male resembles Pied Harrier but has black streaks on neck and breast and lacks large white patches on upperwing-coverts. Female resembles Pied Harrier but has dull rufous belly and thigh. Juvenile also resembles Pied Harrier but has darker brown body and pale head.','Open country, reclaimed land, grasslands and marshes.','Usually flies low over open country with short flaps interspersed by long glides.',48.0,56.0,'fst/open','black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',205,'Pied Harrier','Circus melanoleucos','Helang-Sawah Hitam-Putih','鹊鹞','Rarity','M','Male is distinctive looking with all black head, breast, upper body and median coverts, large whitish patch on lesser coverts, whitish rest of underparts and black outer primaries contrasting with whitish wings in flight. Female resembles Eastern Marsh Harrier but has small whitish patch along upper edge of lesser coverts and almost unmarked whitish thighs and vent. Juvenile also resembles Eastern Marsh Harrier but has more rufous brown body and wing coverts, indistinct paler bands across blackish secondaries and darkish bars at greyish primaries.','Open country, reclaimed land, grasslands and marshes.',NULL,43.0,46.0,'wet/pnr','black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',206,'Black Kite','Milvus migrans','Helang-Kembara Hitam','黑鸢','Non-rarity','M','Adult resembles juvenile Brahminy Kite but has darker overall plumage, distinctive forked tail that appears almost square-cut when broadly fanned in flight and conspicuous whitish patch on the base of primaries. Juvenile resembles adult but has prominent whitish streaks on breast and belly.','Open country, reclaimed land, coastal habitat and forest.',NULL,61.0,66.0,'fst/pnr','brown/black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',207,'Brahminy Kite','Haliastur indus','Helang-Tembikar Merah','栗鸢','Non-rarity','R','Adult superficially resembles the globally famous Bald Eagle with bright rufous underparts, with white head and belly. Juveniles have variably brownish underparts depending on age. In flight easily identified by their "m" shaped wings when soaring. The similar looking Black Kite has a distinct square cut tail and a distinct small white flash on the base of the primary coverts.','Coastal areas.','Feeds on fish but also a scavenger. Has a rather funny sounding call, sounding like a whining baby.',44.0,52.0,'fst/pnr','white/brown','fish/fly/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',208,'White-bellied Sea Eagle','Haliaeetus leucogaster','Helang-Laut Putih','白腹海雕','Non-rarity','R','Adults have all white underparts with black flight feathers, sub-adults variably greyish-brown underparts depending on age. Easily identified in flight when the wings are lifted upwards to form a shallow "v" when soaring. Sub-adults distinguished from the Grey-headed Fish Eagle by having a uniformly brown to white underparts, as opposed to having a contrasting white vent and undertail coverts.','Coastal areas and inland waterbodies.','Heaviest resident bird in Singapore. Feeds primarily on fish. Has a spectacular aerial display where two birds will cling on to each other in the air with their feet and somersault downwards, letting go before they hit the ground. Loud honking call sounds almost like a duck.',70.0,85.0,'fst/sea','black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',209,'Grey-headed Fish Eagle','Haliaeetus ichthyaetus','Helang-Kanguk Besar','灰头渔雕','Non-rarity','R','Adults with prominent greyish head, brown belly, brownish upperparts. Sub-adut browner with less distinct contrast. Distinguished from sub-adult White-bellied Sea Eagle by the presence of the distinct white vent and undertail coverts. Told apart the extirpated and highly unexpected Lesser Fish Eagle (a species that still resides in Johor that is reliant on pristine forest and big streams) by its bigger size and the presence of a white tail base.','Woodland adjacent to waterbodies','Has a loud barking call and a haunting owl-like call that is often heard at dawn and dusk. Diet primarily consists of fish and is frequently observed hunting at various waterbodies across Singapore. Also along coastal area but with density much less than White-bellied Sea Eagles and Brahminy Kites.',69.0,74.0,'wet','white/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',210,'Grey-faced Buzzard','Butastur indicus','Helang-Rintik Utara','灰脸鵟鹰','Non-rarity','M','Adult has mostly plain greyish-brown upperparts and upperbreast, whitish throat with distinctive black mesial stripes, greyish-brown rest of underparts with whitish barrings, pale underwing with dark wing-tips and three dark tail-bands. Juvenile has browner upperparts, broad whitish supercilium and dull whitish underparts with bold dark streaks.','Open country, lightly wooded areas and reclaimed land',NULL,41.0,49.0,'fst/open','grey/white','fly/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',211,'Eastern Buzzard','Buteo japonicus','Helang-Gempal Biasa','普通鵟','Rarity','M','Buteo buzzards have a roundish body and in flight, is disitnct with roung wings and a proportionally short tail. In Singapore very difficult to distinguish from the Common Buzzard, but Buteo buzzards with primarily white base colour on the underparts with strongly contrasting black carpal patch are thought to be of this species.','Open country.','Taxonomy of the Buteo buzzards very confused, with various authors treating this and the Common Buzzard differently. Usually found in open country, though not very frequently observed wintering in Singapore. When hunting, it has a habit of soaring against the wind and staying completely stationary in the air, looking downwards to search for its prey. This behaviour however is almost never observed in Singapore due to the lack of suitable habitats.',51.0,57.0,'resd','white/brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kites, Hawks, Eagles (Accipitridae)',212,'Common Buzzard','Buteo buteo','Helang-Gempal Erasia','欧亚鵟','Rarity','M','The Buteo buzzards present a stocky body, broad wings and a tail when in flight. Difficult to distinguish from Eastern Buzzard, but said to be darker brown overall, with dark carpal patch not contrasting with the rest of the wing as strongly. Can come in three distinct morphs: brown, rufous and dark. Brown morph with solid, brown wing lining and often possessing a pale breast ''belt'' that separates the dark plumage of the belly from the strong upper breast streaking; tail also strongly barred. Rufous morph has dark brown underparts of previous morph replaced by warm rufous brown and less distinct tail barring. Dark morph has blackish-brown body plumage with pale flight feathers and a dark trailing edge to the wing.','Open country.','Often seen while flying across on migration. Rarely overwinters in Singapore. Elsewhere sits on prominent perch and soars low.',39.0,47.0,'resd/fst','white/brown','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Barn Owls (Tytonidae)',213,'Eastern Barn Owl','Tyto javanica','Serak Biasa','仓鸮','Non-rarity','R','A medium-sized owl with distinctive, white facial disk and pale underparts. Proportionally large head, lacking ear tufts with relatively small, heart-shaped, dark-coloured eyes. Legs notably long with only sparsely feathered feet. Female is larger than the male with typically darker plumage.','Urban structures, including under bridges, abandoned buildings, and in natural open-country habitats','Normally solitary. Presence often detected by harsh shrieking call.',34.0,36.0,'resd/fst','white/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',214,'Northern Boobook','Ninox japonica','Pungguk Betemak Utara','北鹰鸮','Rarity','M','Similar to Brown Hawk-owl. Overall brown colouration with large, yellow eyes and small, white patch above bill. Field identification from Brown Hawk-owl is tricky with this bird possessing more elongated, teardrop-shaped streaking compared to the rounder, more heart-shaped streaks of the local subspecies of the Brown Hawk-owl. This bird also possesses proportionally longer wings than the resident species, however, this is hard to make out in the field.','While on migration will make use of any habitat with trees, including scrubland and other areas outside of the closed forests that characterise our central reserves.','Long-distance migrant from eastern Asia. Vocalisations are highly distinct from local Brown Hawk-owl, but calls rarely in its wintering grounds.',30.0,31.0,'fst','white/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',215,'Brown Hawk-Owl','Ninox scutulata','Pungguk Betemak Biasa','鹰鸮','Non-rarity','R','Larger than the local scops owls with a proportionally smaller head. Overall brown colouration with large, yellow eyes and small, white patch above bill. Field identification from Northern Hawk-owl is tricky with the local subspecies generally presenting more heart-shaped brown streaking on its white underparts compared to the more teardrop-shaped streaking of the migrant Northern.','Secondary and primary forest habitats. It can be seen in many nature parks adjacent to the central nature reserves.','This species along with many other hawk-owls often duets in pairs.',30.0,31.0,'fst','white/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',216,'Oriental Scops Owl','Otus sunia','Jampuk Kecil Asia','红角鸮','Rarity','M','Adult greyish morph resembles Sunda Scops Owl but is smaller and has greyish-brown upperparts and head, bold dark streaks on whitish underparts, yellowish eyes and blackish bill. Adult rufous morph resembles greyish morph but has orange-rufous upperparts and head.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded areas, parks and gardens.','Feeds mainly on insects and spiders.',19.0,19.0,'fst/pnr','white/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',217,'Sunda Scops Owl','Otus lempiji','Jampuk Biasa','巽他领角鸮','Non-rarity','R','Adult resembles Oriental Scops Owl but is bigger and has dark eyes, dusky-yellowish bill, brownish vermiculated upperparts and pale sandy-buffish underparts with fine blackish streaks. Juvenile resembles adult but has paler overall plumage.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded area, mangroves, parks and gardens.',NULL,23.0,23.0,'fst/pnr','brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',218,'Short-eared Owl','Asio flammeus','Burung-Hantu Telinga-Pendek Biasa','短耳鸮','Rarity','Va','In Singapore, adult may be confused with Buffy Fish Owl but has pale greyish-white facial disc with conspicuous white eyebrows, dark circles around yellow eyes creating a "black-eye" effect, broader and denser breast streaks and no obvious ear-tuffs. This species can be distinguished from the Long-eared Owl by having yellow iris instead of orange, white trailing edge on the wings and black primary tips in flight.','Grassland, marshes and open areas.','Only flies in daylight.',37.0,39.0,'wet/open','brown/white',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',219,'Barred Eagle-Owl','Bubo sumatranus','Burung-Hantu Bertanduk Belang Melayu','马来雕鸮','Rarity','R','Adult has brown-and-buff bars on its upperparts, blackish-and-whitish bars on its underparts, dark eyes and very distinctive outward facing ear tufts. Head and body of juvenile whitish with narrower bars.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth and plantation.','Diet includes grasshoppers, beetles, rodents, birds and snakes. Had been observed to prey on Long-tailed Macaque.',45.5,46.5,'fst','brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',220,'Buffy Fish Owl','Ketupa ketupu','Tumbuk-Ketampi Biasa','马来渔鸮','Non-rarity','R','A medium-sized owl with buff facial disc, striking white eyebrows and yellow eyes. Distinct ear tufts. Upperparts are buff based, streaked with darker feathers and have pale rufous edges. Underparts have a buff background with thin, dark streaks. Legs are unfeathered and vary from grey to blackish.','Most areas in close proximity to waterways including coastal areas. Can be found in urban canals with large fish.','Normally solitary. Most active at dawn and dusk where it can be seen next to waterbodies where it fishes.',45.5,47.0,'resd/fst','brown/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',221,'Spotted Wood Owl','Strix seloputo','Carik-Kafan Berbintik Asia','点斑林鸮','Non-rarity','R','A medium-sized owl with orange facial disc, dark eyes and no ear tufts. Back dark brown, entire upperparts are covered in white spots. Head blackish, barred white. Underparts are white and thickly barred with thin dark brown stripes, breast has rusty wash. Distinguished from Brown Wood Owl by orange facial disc and much darker, bolder barring on underparts.','Forest edge, wooded areas and parks.','Most common large owl in Singapore after Buffy Fish Owl. Quite urban-adapted and can be found in parks in close proximity to built up areas.',44.5,48.0,'fst/pnr','brown/black/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Owls (Strigidae)',222,'Brown Wood Owl','Strix leptogrammica','Carik-Kafan Coklat','褐林鸮','Rarity','R','Distinguished from Spotted Wood Owl by buffy-brown facial disc with dark border around face and eyes, dark-brown mantle, buffy underparts with brownish bars and dark brown breast. Juvenile has mostly whitish-buff body with dark border around eyes.','Forest, forest edge or any suitable wooded area.','Diet consists of rodents, lizards, large insects and birds.',47.0,53.0,'fst','white/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Hornbills (Bucerotidae)',223,'Oriental Pied Hornbill','Anthracoceros albirostris','Kelingking Biasa','冠斑犀鸟','Non-rarity','I/R','A medium-sized hornbill with white belly and trailing edge to wings. Upperparts and wings dark. Pale yellow bill with black tipped casque. Female has smaller casque than male with black on bill tip. Juvenile less glossy plumage, smaller casque and all yellow bill.','Wooded areas, forest edges, gardens and parks.','Large, conspicuous hornbill. Found in most open vegetation on the island, often found in urban areas bordering green spaces.',68.0,70.0,'fst/pnr','black/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Hornbills (Bucerotidae)',224,'Black Hornbill','Anthracoceros malayanus','Kelingking Hitam','黑斑犀鸟','Rarity','Vi','Adult has all black plumage with broadly white-tipped outertail and unmarked yellowish-white bill and casque. Female resembles male but has blackish bill/casque and pinkish orbital skin. Juvenile has pale greenish-yellow bill and underdeveloped casque.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth and wooded area.','Usually found in pairs or small flocks.',76.0,76.0,'fst','black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Rollers (Coraciidae)',225,'Oriental Dollarbird','Eurystomus orientalis','Tiung-Batu Biasa','三宝鸟','Non-rarity','M/R','Distinct silhouette with a stout body and chunky head with red bill. Greyish to blackish plumage, glossed blue. In flight, long wings with white wing patches diagnostic. Often perches conspicuously uttering a ‘chak’ call.','Frequents open areas','Often perches on bare branches or man-made structures',27.5,31.5,'fst/pnr','black/blue','fly/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',226,'Stork-billed Kingfisher','Pelargopsis capensis','Pekaka-Emas Biasa','鹳嘴翡翠','Non-rarity','R','Adult has huge red bill, dull brownish crown and headsides, greenish-blue mantle, wings and tail and mostly warm buff-orange nuchal collar and underparts.','Waterbodies in or near forests, parks, gardens, open woodlands and mangroves.','Catches medium size fishes by plunging into the water from perches around 2-4 meters above the water.',37.5,41.0,'wet/pnr','yellow/brown/blue','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',227,'Ruddy Kingfisher','Halcyon coromanda','Pekaka Belacan','赤翡翠','Non-rarity','M/Vi','Adult has bright rufescent plumage, violet-tinged upperside, bluish-white patch on lower back and rump and bright red bill. Juvenile has browner upperparts, brilliant blue (less whitish) lower back and rump, narrow dark brown bars on underparts and brownish orange bill.','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas and mangroves.','Feeds on fish, crustaceans, and large insects. When in habitat with less running water, they are known to take frogs and other amphibians.',26.5,27.0,'fst','red/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',228,'White-throated Kingfisher','Halcyon smyrnensis','Pekaka Rengkung Putih','白胸翡翠','Non-rarity','R','Adult has dark chestnut head, flanks and belly with contrasting whitish throat and centre of breast, mostly turquoise-blue mantle, wings and tail, dark chestnut/blackish wing-coverts and reddish bill. Juvenile has duller upperparts, browner bill and dark vermiculations on throat and breast.','Parks, gardens and wooded areas near open grass patches, water-bodies, canals, rivers and mangroves.','Feeds on fish, lizards, insects and small amphibians.',27.5,29.5,'wet/pnr','brown/blue/white','fish/ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',229,'Black-capped Kingfisher','Halcyon pileata','Pekaka Ubun Hitam','蓝翡翠','Non-rarity','M','Adult has black crown and head-sides, white collar, throat and upper-breast, dull rufous rest of underparts, thick red bill and deep blue upperparts with mostly black wing-coverts. Shows large white patch on primaries when seen in flight. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller blue upperparts and dark vermiculations on sides of throat and breast.','Mangroves, various coastal and inland wetlands., gardens and wooded areas','Diet consists mostly of fish, lizard, frog and large insects.',29.0,31.5,'wet/pnr','brown/blue/black','fish/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',230,'Collared Kingfisher','Todiramphus chloris','Pekaka Bakau Biasa','白领翡翠','Non-rarity','R','Adult has rich blue upperparts, distinctive white collar and underparts and black bill with pale pinkish-white lower mandible. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller/greener-tinged upperparts and dark vermiculations on collar and breast.','Waterbodies in or near forests edge, parks, gardens, open woodlands, grasslands and mangroves.','Feeds on fish, lizards, insects, and small amphibians.',24.0,26.0,'wet/pnr','white/blue','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',231,'Blue-eared Kingfisher','Alcedo meninting','Rajaudang Meninting','蓝耳翠鸟','Non-rarity','R','Resembles Common Kingfisher but smaller and has deeper blue upperparts (without turquoise blue tinge) and blue ear-coverts. Male has all black bill while female has reddish lower mandible. Juvenile has rufous ear-coverts and mostly red bill.','Streams, ponds and suitable water bodies in or near forest and wooded areas.','Nest in tunnel excavated at bank of forest streams.',15.5,16.5,'wet/pnr','orange/blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',232,'Common Kingfisher','Alcedo atthis','Rajaudang Cicit','普通翠鸟','Non-rarity','M','Male has pale rufous underparts with a white-tinged throat, rufous ear-coverts, turquoise blue upperparts and mostly black bill. Female resembles male but base or most of lower mandible orange-reddish. Juvenile has duller underparts with dusky wash across breast.','Various inland and coastal wetlands.','Diet consists mostly of fish but occasionally hunts for lizard, frog and insects.',16.0,18.0,'wet','brown/blue/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',233,'Oriental Dwarf Kingfisher','Ceyx erithaca','Rajaudang-Api Biasa','三趾翠鸟','Non-rarity','M/Vi','Very distinctive looking with a combination of rufous-yellow underparts, lilac-tinged crown with blue patches at rear of ear-coverts, reddish bill, whitish throat, dark bluish upper back and scapulars, blackish wings and bright lilac rump/uppertail-coverts.','Forest, gardens, parks, wooded areas and mangroves.','Feeds on insect, lizard, fish, and amphibian. Often visits forest streams at dusk to bath.',12.5,14.0,'fst','blue/orange','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Kingfishers (Alcedinidae)',234,'Pied Kingfisher','Ceryle rudis','Pekaka-Berjambul Biasa','斑鱼狗','Rarity','Va','Only kingfisher in range with black and white plumage. Black crown and crest, upperparts and wings black with white edgings, white wing patch on wing coverts. Male has a two black breastbands while female only possesses one.','Elsewhere generally found on the edges and banks of large, open water bodies, including lakes, reservoirs, estuaries, dams, and mangroves.','Elsewhere seen catching fish by hovering almost motionless above water before diving in to capture prey.',25.0,30.5,'wet','black/white','fish');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bee-eaters (Meropidae)',235,'Blue-tailed Bee-eater','Merops philippinus','Berek-berek Zaitun Asia','栗喉蜂虎','Non-rarity','M','Adult quite distinctive and is green overall with orange-chestnut lower throat, black eyestripe that gets thinner closer to the bill and bluish rump/tail. Also shows the typical shape of a bee-eater — long and slightly downcurved bill with long tail-streamers. Juvenile has duller lower throat and lacks tail-streamers.','Open and urban areas, marshes, grasslands and forests.','Feeds in flight on a variety of flying insects including dragonflies, bees and large flies.',23.0,24.0,'resd/wet','blue/green/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bee-eaters (Meropidae)',236,'Blue-throated Bee-eater','Merops viridis','Berek-berek Rengkung Biru','蓝喉蜂虎','Non-rarity','R','Adult has mostly bluish-green body with dark chestnut crown and mantle, black eyestripe and bluish tail (with streamers) and throat. Juvenile is greener overall and lacks chestnut crown/mantle and tail streamers.','Open and urban areas, marshes, grasslands and forests.','Feeds in flight on a variety of flying insects including dragonflies, bees, and large flies.',22.5,23.5,'resd/wet','blue/green/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Asian Barbets (Megalaimidae)',237,'Lineated Barbet','Psilopogon lineatus','Takur Kutub Timur','斑头绿拟啄木鸟','Non-rarity','I','Adult has distinctive yellowish bill, broad yellow orbital skin, mostly brown head and breast with broad whitish streaks, green wings and tail. Juvenile looks similar to adult.','Wooded area, forest edge, gardens and parks.','Nest in excavated tree-hole 3-12 meters above ground.',27.0,28.0,'fst/pnr','grey/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Asian Barbets (Megalaimidae)',238,'Red-crowned Barbet','Psilopogon rafflesii','Takur Ubun Merah','花彩拟啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Adult has all green body with large black bill, red crown, blue throat, blue supercilium, black eye-stripe, small yellow neck-patch and small red patch on side of upper breast. Juvenile looks duller with less defined head pattern.','Forest and forest edge.','Slow-moving and often found in canopy where difficult to observe.',25.0,27.0,'fst','blue/green/red','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Asian Barbets (Megalaimidae)',239,'Coppersmith Barbet','Psilopogon haemacephalus','Takur Tukang Biasa','赤胸拟啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Adult has stout blackish bill, reddish legs, bright green uppeparts, greenish-white underparts with green streaks, yellow face and throat with black eye-stripe, reddish forecrown and small red patch at upper breast. Juvenile looks duller and lacks the reddish parts of the adult.','Gardens, parks, mangroves and suitable wooded areas but not forest.','Its call sounds like a coppersmith hitting copper sheets.',17.0,17.0,'pnr','green/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',240,'Sunda Pygmy Woodpecker','Yungipicus moluccensis','Belatuk-Belacan Kecil Biasa','巽他啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has brownish crown and ear-covers, well defined submoustachial stripe, red streak on side of hindcrown, white-barred brownish upperside and dark streaked underparts. Female resembles male but lacks the red streak. Juvenile is duller overall and has less distinct streaks.','Parks, gardens, mangroves and coastal areas.','Usually found singly or in pairs, unobtrusive and drums softly.',12.5,13.0,'wet/pnr','grey/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',241,'White-bellied Woodpecker','Dryocopus javensis','Belatuk-Hitam Perut Putih','白腹黑啄木鸟','Rarity','Vi','Male has black overall plumage with white belly and red crown, crest and submoustachial band. Female resembles male but has black crown and lacks the red submoustachial band. Juvenile has duller plumage and paler throat than adult.','Forests.','Frequents the canopy and middle storey solitarily or in pairs.',37.5,43.0,'fst','blue/red/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',242,'Banded Woodpecker','Chrysophlegma miniaceum','Belatuk-Hijau Merah','红翅绿背啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has mostly red upperparts with lightly scaled olive mantle, yellow nape, red-rufous ear-coverts, barred underparts and rufous wash on throat and breast. Female resembles male but has significantly less yellow on nape, duller face, and white-speckled ear-coverts. Juvenile has less red on face, duller mantle with less defined scales and fainter bars on underparts.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, gardens and parks.',NULL,25.5,27.0,'fst/pnr','red/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',243,'Crimson-winged Woodpecker','Picus puniceus','Belatuk-Hijau Paruh Kuning','红翅绿啄木鸟','Rarity','Vi','Large olive-green woodpecker with red wings, red crown with yellow crest, yellowish rump, white barring on flanks, blue orbital skin, largely yellow bill, and black tail.','Primary and mature secondary forest with closed canopy.','Elsewhere seen singly or in pairs, often associating with mixed flocks.',25.0,25.0,'fst','green/red/yellow',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',244,'Laced Woodpecker','Picus vittatus','Belatuk-Hijau Bakau','花腹绿啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has olive-green upperparts, red crown to nape, black submoustachial stripe with fine whitish streaks, grey ear-coverts and faintly scaled belly to vent. Female resembles male but has black crown to nape. Juvenile is duller with more scaled appearance on belly.','Forest edge, secondary growth, wooded area, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Usually solitary or in pairs.',27.0,33.0,'fst/pnr','green/white/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',245,'Common Flameback','Dinopium javanense','Belatuk-Pinang Biasa','金背三趾啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has mostly golden upperparts, crimson rump, reddish crown with pointed crest, blackish hindneck, eye-stripe and submoustachial stripe and scaled underparts that are dense at the breast and gradually grow more disparate towards the vent. Female resembles male but has white-streaked blackish crown. Juvenile has blacker breast with less scaling on lower belly.','Forest edge, secondary growth, gardens, parks, mangroves and wooded areas.',NULL,28.0,30.0,'fst/pnr','yellow/brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',246,'Rufous Woodpecker','Micropternus brachyurus','Belatuk Biji Nangka','栗啄木鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has rich rufous overall plumage with blackish bars on upperside and belly, speckled throat and small red cheek-patch. Female resembles male but lacks the red cheek-patch.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded areas, parks and gardens.',NULL,25.0,25.0,'fst/pnr','brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',247,'Buff-rumped Woodpecker','Meiglyptes tristis','Belatuk-Batu Biasa','黄腰斑啄木鸟','Rarity','Vi','A densely barred woodpecker with a slight nuchal crest and whitish-buff rump. Female has no red submoustachial.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth and other suitable wooded area.','Usually forages at the canopy level and generally unobtrusive.',17.0,17.0,'fst','black/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Woodpeckers (Picidae)',248,'Great Slaty Woodpecker','Mulleripicus pulverulentus','Belatuk-Kelabu Besar','大灰啄木鸟','Rarity','Vi','Unmistakable from its large size, longish neck, dark slaty-grey overall plumage with whitish spots on nape and neck, yellowish-white bill and golden-buff throat. Male has red submoustachial stripe.','Broadleaved forest and mangroves.','Usually frequents the canopy in small parties. Very noisy and conspicuous.',45.0,51.0,'fst/wet','grey/orange',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Caracaras, Falcons (Falconidae)',249,'Black-thighed Falconet','Microhierax fringillarius','Rajawali-Belalang Melayu','黑腿小隼','Rarity','Vi','Adult has blackish crown, ear-covert patch, nape and upperparts, whitish forehead, narrow down-curving supercilium, throat and upper-breast and chestnut rest of underparts. Juvenile resembles adult but has pale chestnut supercilium','Forest, forest edge and suitable wooded areas.','Frequently darts out rapidly from a perch to capture flying insects. Will also attack small birds.',15.0,17.0,'fst','brown/black/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Caracaras, Falcons (Falconidae)',250,'Lesser Kestrel','Falco naumanni','Rajawali-Padang Cakar Pudar','黄爪隼','Rarity','Va','Male resembles Common Kestrel but has plain bluish grey crown/nape/head-sides, plain rufous-chestnut mantle and median coverts and plainer vinous-tinged warm buff underparts with fewer, rounder markings. Female also resembles Common Kestrel but has indistinct moustachial/cheek stripe and no dark line behind eye. Subadult male resembles adult male but may show some dark bars on upperwing coverts and uppertail.','Open country, reclaimed land and grasslands.',NULL,29.0,32.0,'pnr/resd','brown/black','trees/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Caracaras, Falcons (Falconidae)',251,'Common Kestrel','Falco tinnunculus','Rajawali-Padang Biasa','红隼','Rarity','M','Male has slaty-grey crown, nape, rump to uppertail, broad black subterminal tail-band, rufous rest of upperparts and wing-coverts with blackish markings, dark moustachial/cheek stripe and pale buffish underparts with dark streaks/spots on breast, belly and flanks. Female resembles male but has dark-streaked warm brown crown/nape and duller rufous upperparts with dark bars.','Open country, reclaimed land and grasslands.',NULL,30.0,34.0,'pnr/resd','brown/black','trees/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Caracaras, Falcons (Falconidae)',252,'Amur Falcon','Falco amurensis','Rajawali Kaki Merah Timur','红脚隼','Rarity','Va','Male resembles adult Peregrine Falcon but is smaller and has diagnostic red eyering, cere and feet, pale grey underparts and rufous-chestnut vent. Female resembles male but has dark streaked underparts, barred uppertail-coverts and buffy-white vent. Juvenile resembles female but has pale yellow eyering and cere.','Reclaimed land and open habitats near the coast.','Often hunts and catches insects on the wing. Sometimes hovers while hunting.',28.0,31.0,'sea','black/white','branch/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Caracaras, Falcons (Falconidae)',253,'Eurasian Hobby','Falco subbuteo','Rajawali Tongkeng Merah Utara','燕隼','Rarity','Va','Adult resembles juvenile Peregrine Falcon but is significantly smaller and has darker crown, narrower moustachial stripe, unbarred uppertail, heavily streaked breast/belly and reddish-rufous vent. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller crown/upperparts and buffish vent.','Open country, reclaimed land and wooded areas.',NULL,30.0,36.0,'fst/resd','brown/black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Caracaras, Falcons (Falconidae)',254,'Peregrine Falcon','Falco peregrinus','Rajawali Kembara','游隼','Non-rarity','M/Vi','The migrant subspecies has slaty-grey upperparts, broad blackish moustachial streak and whitish underparts with dark bars on flanks, belly to undertail coverts. Juvenile resembles adult but has warmer brown upperparts and buffish underparts with dark streaks. Subspecies ernesti is smaller and has darker upperparts and solid blackish head-sides.','Open country, secondary growth, farmland, mangroves and urban areas.',NULL,38.0,48.0,'resd/wet','black/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cockatoos (Cacatuidae)',255,'Tanimbar Corella','Cacatua goffiniana','Kakaktua Tanimbar','戈氏凤头鹦鹉','Non-rarity','I','All white cockatoo with short crest and white eye ring. Grey legs and bill with light pink feathers around base of bill. Separated from Yellow-crested Cockatoo by lack of yellow crest and more compact build.','Lightly wooded habitats in Singapore, although often found foraging away from forests, even around housing estates.','Presence given away by loud, raucous screeches.',32.0,32.0,'resd/pnr','white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('African & New World Parrots (Psittacidae)',256,'Monk Parakeet','Myiopsitta monachus','Bayan-Ranting Biasa','灰胸鹦哥','Non-rarity','I','Distinct from other resident and introduced parrot species. Green overall, with grey face, throat, and breast.','Found in urban and open habitats in introduced range.','Builds large stick nests, does not nest in cavities unlike other parrot species. Nests in tall trees or artificial structures, individuals in Singapore have been observed nesting on stadium lights.',29.0,29.0,'resd/open','green/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Parrots (Psittaculidae)',257,'Blue-rumped Parrot','Psittinus cyanurus','Nuri Puling','蓝腰短尾鹦鹉','Non-rarity','R','Male has mostly greyish-blue head, throat and upperbreast, reddish bill with brownish lower mandible, dark purplish-blue mantle and yellowish fringing on green wing-coverts. Female resembles male but has brownish head and bill, bluish back and mostly green underparts. Juvenile resembles female but has greenish head. Shows prominent red coverts and blackish underwing when in flight.','Forest, forest edge, parks and gardens.',NULL,18.5,19.5,'fst/pnr','blue/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Parrots (Psittaculidae)',258,'Red-breasted Parakeet','Psittacula alexandri','Bayan Dada Merah','绯胸鹦鹉','Non-rarity','I','Male has overall green plumage with distinct pink breast and belly, grey head, blue uppertail, green tail tip and red upper bill. Female is similar to male but has duller pink underparts and black upper bill. Immature birds have grey head and pink underparts green. Distinguished from both Long-tailed Parakeet and Rose-ringed Parakeet by pink underparts and grey head.','Forages in parks and other open woodland habitats.','Well-adapted to urban environments and from massive roost flocks in HDB estates.',33.0,37.0,'fst/pnr','green/orange/grey','trees/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Parrots (Psittaculidae)',259,'Long-tailed Parakeet','Psittacula longicauda','Bayan Melayu','长尾鹦鹉','Non-rarity','R','Male has mostly green overall plumage with long purplish-blue tail-streamers, bright red bill, reddish-pink head-sides and nape, deep green crown and broad black malar band. Female resembles male but has shorter tail-streamers, brownish bill, greenish nape, dark green malar band and reddish-pink supercilium. Juvenile resembles female but has less red on head, indistinct malar band and no tail-streamers.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, parks and gardens.',NULL,40.0,42.0,'fst/pnr','blue/green','branch/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Parrots (Psittaculidae)',260,'Rose-ringed Parakeet','Psittacula krameri','Bayan Gelang Biasa','红领绿鹦鹉','Non-rarity','I','Plumage almost entirely yellowish-green. Upper bill red with black tip. Male has pink collar, topped by indistinct pale blue line across back of neck. Female lacks pink collar. Juveniles are similar to females but slightly yellower. All-green plumage serves to distinguish this species from Red-breasted and Long-tailed Parakeet.','Parks and other lightly wooded areas.','Loud species that is often found in green spaces bordering residential areas.',40.0,42.0,'fst/pnr','green','branch/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Parrots (Psittaculidae)',261,'Coconut Lorikeet','Trichoglossus haematodus','Bayan-Madu Pelangi Biasa','椰果鹦鹉','Non-rarity','I','Both sexes similar. Bill red, head dark blue, nape yellow-green, rest of upperparts and tail green. Underparts generally green with undertail coverts yellow and underwings bright red. Breast is barred with red and blue. Call is thinner, brighter and more shrill compared to the other parakeets in Singapore.','Species most frequently encountered in open woodland habitat such as parks. Generally avoids closed forest but has been recorded on the outskirts of the nature reserves.','Seen most frequently in small flocks. This species is unique amongst our local parrots in being especially specialised at consuming nectar.',25.0,30.0,'fst/pnr','red/yellow/black','trees/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Parrots (Psittaculidae)',262,'Blue-crowned Hanging Parrot','Loriculus galgulus','Serindit Melayu','蓝顶短尾鹦鹉','Non-rarity','R','Male has bright green overall plumage with dark blue crown patch, reddish breast patch, small yellow patch on mantle just below the nape, yellow band on rump, reddish uppertail-coverts, blackish bill and dark eyes. Female resembles male but is duller and lacks the reddish breast patch. Juvenile resembles female but has dusky-yellowish bill.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, parks and gardens.',NULL,12.0,14.5,'fst/pnr','green/red','trees/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Typical Broadbills (Eurylaimidae)',263,'Black-and-red Broadbill','Cymbirhynchus macrorhynchos','Hujan-hujan Merah','黑红阔嘴鸟','Rarity','Vi','Adult is distinctive looking with blackish chin, cheeks and upperparts with long white streak along scapulars, dark maroon-red rump and underparts with narrow black breast-band and brightly coloured bill with turquoise-blue upper mandible and yellowish lower mandible. Juvenile resembles adult but has browner overall plumage.','Forest, forest edge, freshwater swamp forest and mangroves.','Unobtrusive, often sitting still for long periods usually near water.',21.0,24.0,'fst/wet','black/red','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('African & Green Broadbills (Calyptomenidae)',264,'Green Broadbill','Calyptomena viridis','Seluwit Biasa','绿阔嘴鸟','Rarity','Vi','Male has bright deep green overall plumage with broad tuft of feathers on top of bill, blackish patch on rear of ear-coverts and broad black bars on wing-coverts. Female resembles male but duller with no black markings. Juvenile resembles female but has paler breast and greenish-white vent.','Usually found in forest but also wooded areas and gardens in Singapore.','Frequents the middle and lower storeys.',NULL,NULL,'fst/pnr','green/black',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pittas (Pittidae)',265,'Blue-winged Pitta','Pitta moluccensis','Burung-Pacat Sayap Biru','蓝翅八色鸫','Non-rarity','M/R','Adult has blackish head with buff crown-sides/supercilium, black eyestripe, white throat with a small blackish chin patch just below the bill, green upperparts, violet-blue upperwing coverts and plain buff underparts with red vent. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller overall plumage.','Parks, gardens, forests, wooded areas and mangroves.',NULL,18.0,20.5,'fst/pnr','blue/green/orange','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pittas (Pittidae)',266,'Mangrove Pitta','Pitta megarhyncha','Burung-Pacat Bakau','红树八色鸫','Non-rarity','R','Adult resembles Blue-winged Pitta but bill much longer, crown drabber and more uniform brown almost lacking the black line at the center, underparts slightly duller and has whitish chin.','Mangroves.',NULL,18.0,21.0,'wet','orange/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pittas (Pittidae)',267,'Hooded Pitta','Pitta sordida','Burung-Pacat Hijau','绿胸八色鸫','Non-rarity','M','Adult has black head with dark brown crown, green body and red vent. Juvenile has brownish overall plumage and whitish throat.','Parks, gardens, forests and wooded areas.',NULL,16.5,19.0,'pnr','black/green/brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Pittas (Pittidae)',268,'Fairy Pitta','Pitta nympha','Burung-Pacat Utara','仙八色鸫','Rarity','Va','Adult resembles Blue-winged Pitta but is smaller in size and has rufous-brown head-sides, narrow whitish-buff supercilium, paler buff underparts and less blue on wing-coverts.','Broadleaved evergreen forest.',NULL,16.0,19.5,'fst','white/green/red','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Australasian Warblers (Acanthizidae)',269,'Golden-bellied Gerygone','Gerygone sulphurea','Kelicap-Perepat Asia','黄胸噪刺莺','Non-rarity','R','Sexes similar. Yellow underparts, greyish brown above. Dark cheeks and ear coverts strongly contrast with the yellowish throat giving it a strong ''hooded'' appearance. Song consists of a series of high-pitched, rising and falling notes that have a bright, pausing cadence.','Occurs in most habitats with trees, including highly urbanised landscapes.','Sticks high to the canopy where it is often more often heard than seen. This species is a known host of the Little Bronze Cuckoo.',10.0,10.5,'fst/pnr','brown/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Vangas & Allies (Vangidae)',270,'Black-winged Flycatcher-shrike','Hemipus hirundinaceus','Rembah Sayap Hitam','黑翅鹟鵙','Rarity','Vi','Similar to Pied Triller but easily separated by smaller size and lack of white wing-patch and supercilium. Male has uniform black upperparts and white underparts. Female has browner upperparts. Juvenile resembles female and has browner wash across upper breast.','Forest, forest edge, freshwater swamp forest and mangroves.','Flies short sorties to snap prey out of the air and returning to the same, typically exposed perch.',13.5,14.5,'fst/wet','brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Vangas & Allies (Vangidae)',271,'Large Woodshrike','Tephrodornis virgatus','Rembah-Rimba Besar','钩嘴林鵙','Rarity','Vi','Male has uniform slaty-grey upperparts with contrasting whitish underparts, strong bill, broad blackish eye line and whitish rump-band. Female resembles male but has browner upperparts and eye line. Juvenile is browner than female and has whitish shafts, tips and bars on upperparts.','Broadleaved forest, forest edge, secondary growth and mangroves.','Frequents the canopy in small flocks.',18.5,22.5,'fst/pnr','brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ioras (Aegithinidae)',272,'Common Iora','Aegithina tiphia','Kunyit-Kecil Biasa','黑翅雀鹎','Non-rarity','R','Breeding plumage in male; black cap, wings and tail. Underparts lemon-yellow. Two striking white wing bars present. Upperparts generally black but flecked with some yellow. Female plumage lacks black cap and upperparts of breeding male and is instead yellowish green in these areas, underparts lemon-yellow, wings black with white edging to feathers. Non-breeding males are similar to females apart from more black on wings and retaining the black on uppertail coverts and tail.','Favour open wooded habitat. Seen in most parks, not seen in closed forest.','Prefers foraging for insects at higher levels of the canopy, often seen search on the undersides of leaves for prey',12.0,14.5,'pnr','black/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckooshrikes (Campephagidae)',273,'Scarlet Minivet','Pericrocotus speciosus','Burung-Matahari Besar Biasa','赤红山椒鸟','Rarity','Vi','Unmistakable bird. Male is scarlet with black cap and upper back. Upperwings black, greater coverts red-tipped, broad band of red on remiges, distinct patch of red on tertials. Female is similar to male but red replaced with bright yellow, black on upper back and hindcrown replaced with grey and forehead and supraloral line yellow.','Generally only occurs in closed forest with a highly-developed canopy.','Forages in small flocks, almost ''bouncing'' from treetop to treetop. Highly distinctive vocalisations, colouration and behaviour make it hard to miss when it is present.',17.0,21.5,'fst','black/red/yellow',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckooshrikes (Campephagidae)',274,'Ashy Minivet','Pericrocotus divaricatus','Burung-Matahari Kelabu Biasa','灰山椒鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has black hindcrown, ear coverts that extends over nape. Rest of head and the narrow half collar white, underparts white, and upperparts generally light slate-grey, edges of remiges and greater coversts darker grey. Female has body plumage similar to male except slightly paler. Female plumage on head differs from male replacing all black with grey, except on lores and forehead.','Migrant that is often seen in foraging in more open woodland habitat in Singapore, regularly sighted in parks.','Typically perches high on tree canopy. Observers usually alerted to its presence by its trilling calls.',18.5,20.0,'fst/pnr','grey/white','trees/fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckooshrikes (Campephagidae)',275,'Pied Triller','Lalage nigra','Selancang Melayu','黑鸣鹃鵙','Non-rarity','R','Male has foreheard, crown, nape, mantle glossy black, supercilium white, lores black. Wing mainly black apart from white median, greater coverts and white fringed secondaries, underparts white. Female has black on body of males replaced by grey, white edges and margins on wing feathers narrower than in male, underparts washed buff with narrow scaling.','Frequents open woodland, especially parks.','Forages at most levels of trees, but prefers canopy. Known to consume both insects and small fruit.',17.0,18.0,'fst/pnr','black/white/grey','trees/ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cuckooshrikes (Campephagidae)',276,'Lesser Cuckooshrike','Lalage fimbriata','Selancang-Kelabu Melayu','缨鹃鵙','Rarity','Vi','Male has dark grey upperparts with lighter grey underparts and belly. Lores and ear coverts darker grey than rest of body, with black wings. Female similar, with barred underparts.','Forest.',NULL,19.0,20.5,'fst/pnr','black/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Whistlers & Allies (Pachycephalidae)',277,'Mangrove Whistler','Pachycephala cinerea','Murai-Siul Bakau','红树啸鹟','Rarity','R/Vi','Told apart from other similarly sized flycatchers by thick black bill, no obvious head/wing markings or rufous tones in plumage. Drab brown upperparts with slaty grey crown, white underparts with duller throat and greyish washed breast. Song is distinct.','Mangroves and adjacent coastal vegetation. Also local plantations and wooded gardens, island forest, local freshwater swamp forest and similar vegetation inland.','Unobtrusive and rather inactive. Sits still for long period amongst foliage.',15.5,17.0,'wet/fst','brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Shrikes (Laniidae)',278,'Tiger Shrike','Lanius tigrinus','Tirjup Harimau','虎纹伯劳','Non-rarity','M','Adult males (rare in Singapore) have white underparts, thick eyestripe, scaly chestnut lower back that contrasts strongly with slate-grey upper mantle, nape, and crown. Females like males but have scaly underparts and overall duller plumage. Immatures and juveniles are very scaly overall. Birds of all ages show a “clean”, unscaled and rufous tail.','Well-wooded areas, secondary growth and forest edge.','Feeds on insects, lizards, small birds and rodents.',17.0,18.5,'fst','brown/white/grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Shrikes (Laniidae)',279,'Brown Shrike','Lanius cristatus','Tirjup Biasa','红尾伯劳','Non-rarity','M','Individuals of subspecies confusus are brown overall, have chestnut-wash flanks, dark black eye-stripe and thin white supercilium. L. cristatus lucionensis shows a slate-grey supercilium and crown with a dark black eye-stripe. L. c. superciliosus shows a brownish-red nape and mantle, thicker and white supercilium and a very strongly contrasting black eyestripe. L. c. cristatus is very similar to confusus.','Open and non-forest habitats like parks and grasslands.','Feeds on insects, reptiles, small birds and rodents. Prefers more open habitats while Tiger Shrike prefers more wooded areas.',19.0,20.5,'fst/pnr','brown/yellow/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Shrikes (Laniidae)',280,'Long-tailed Shrike','Lanius schach','Tirjup Ekor Panjang Asia','棕背伯劳','Non-rarity','R','Adults show variable amount of rich rufous on flanks and vent, have a thick black eyestripe, no supercilium (differentiating them from Brown Shrike), white throat, slaty grey crown and mantle and black bill, wings and tail. Juveniles are duller.','Parks, grasslands and other open habitats with posts and fence-lines as look-out perches.','Feeds on insects, lizards, small birds and mammals.',25.0,28.0,'pnr','black/grey/orange','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Vireos, Greenlets, Shrike-babblers (Vireonidae)',281,'White-bellied Erpornis','Erpornis zantholeuca','Kelicap-Berjambul','白腹凤鹛','Rarity','Vi','Yellowish olive-green above. Greyish white underparts. Conspicuous dark eye in otherwise pale and unmarked face. Slight crested appearance.','Broadleaved evergreen and deciduous woodland to 2,650 m elevation.','Forages for invertebrates in the canopy and mid-storey. Often in groups and regularly joins mixed species feeding flocks.',13.5,13.5,'fst','yellow/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Figbirds, Orioles, Turnagra (Oriolidae)',282,'Black-naped Oriole','Oriolus chinensis','Kunyit Besar','黑枕黄鹂','Non-rarity','M/R','Golden-yellow medium-sized bird with a broad black band across eye and hindcrown. Iris reddish, bill pink. Most of wings black. Subspecies diffusus told apart from nominate race as tertials and inner secondaries yellow on outer edge rather than black.','Widespread. Urban parks, scrub, degraded forests, forests, mangroves.','Omnivorous, feeding on a wide range of food such as fruits and insects. Sometimes joins mixed flocks in fruiting trees.',24.5,27.5,'fst','yellow/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Drongos (Dicruridae)',283,'Crow-billed Drongo','Dicrurus annectens','Cecawi Paruh Tebal','鸦嘴卷尾','Non-rarity','M','Medium-sized drongo with thick bill, flared but shallowly forked tail, with outer tail feathers curving outwards. Feathers glossy. Juveniles may show some white spotting on breast and belly. Differs from Black Drongo (D. macrocercus) as feathers of Crow-billed Drongo glossier, tail less forked, bill thicker and longer, no white loral spot. Juvenile Crow-billed Drongos have white spotting on breast and belly whereas Black Drongo does not. They also occur in different habitats; differs from Square-tailed Drongo-Cuckoo as crow-billed drongo tail is more forked, differs from Greater Racket-tailed Drongo with no tail extensions, tail more deeply and widely forked, glossier underparts.','Forest, secondary forest.','Usually occurs singly, perches in low and mid-storey in shade. May join mixed flocks',27.0,32.0,'fst','black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Drongos (Dicruridae)',284,'Greater Racket-tailed Drongo','Dicrurus paradiseus','Cecawi Anting-anting Besar','大盘尾','Non-rarity','R','Large drongo with two twisted pendant-like tail extensions. Glossy feathers, with backward-curving tuft on forehead. Differs from Crow-billed Drongo by tail extensions. Where extensions are missing, this species can be told apart from Crow-billed Drongo by forehead tuft, and more linear tail fork. Told apart from Black Drongo as both species are found in different habitats. Greater Racket-tailed Drongos are also glossier, with tail distinctly less forked.','Forest, secondary forest','Calls loudly and often from perch, with a wide range of vocalizations. Calls told from other species it mimics by more metallic tinge. Often found in mixed-flocks. Reported to exhibit food kleptoparasitism.',33.0,35.5,'fst/pnr','black/green','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Drongos (Dicruridae)',285,'Hair-crested Drongo','Dicrurus hottentottus','Cecawi Berambut','发冠卷尾','Rarity','Va','Potential for confusion with other drongos – see links below – but Hair-crested has a longer, more slender, and slightly downcurved bill. The tips of the outer tail feathers are curled upwards and inwards.','Mixed woodland and open country, mostly lowlands, sometimes parks and gardens on migration','A typical drongo: a sit-and-wait predator watching from a high perch and then flying out to capture prey (invertebrates, small reptiles) on the wing or on the ground',NULL,NULL,'fst/pnr','black/green','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Drongos (Dicruridae)',286,'Ashy Drongo','Dicrurus leucophaeus','Cecawi Kelabu','灰卷尾','Rarity','M','Uniform ashy-grey drongo with darker lores and chin. Thin, long, linear tail lacking curl at tail tips.','Forest, forest edge, open forest','Singly, often perched on high, open perches, such as bare canopy branches, at forest edges. Sallies to take insects from canopy or close to ground.',25.5,29.0,'fst/pnr','grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Drongos (Dicruridae)',287,'Black Drongo','Dicrurus macrocercus','Cecawi Sawah','黑卷尾','Rarity','M','Medium-sized drongo with sleek, uniform black plumage. Long, deeply forked tail. Told from crow-billed drongo by smaller, slimmer bill and more deeply forked tail.','Open country and cultivation.','Prefers open perches such as wooden poles, fences or scrub.',27.0,28.5,'pnr','black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Fantails (Rhipiduridae)',288,'Malaysian Pied Fantail','Rhipidura javanica','Murai-Gila Biasa','斑扇尾鹟','Non-rarity','R','Small bird with dark upperparts and face, white supercilium and throat, cream-coloured belly.','Widespread, in places such as gardens, forests, scrubland, mangroves.','In pairs or mixed flocks, often found in understorey foraging for insects',17.5,19.5,'fst/pnr','white/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Monarchs (Monarchidae)',289,'Black-naped Monarch','Hypothymis azurea','Murai-Ranting Biasa','黑枕王鹟','Rarity','R/Vi','Male has distinctive all blue upperparts and breast, white belly and black nuchal tuft and breast band. Female has a dull bluish head, greyish breast, brownish upperparts and whitish belly. Juvenile resembles female.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth near forest.','Diet consist presumably of small insects which are usually snatched when flushed.',16.0,17.5,'fst','blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Monarchs (Monarchidae)',290,'Indian Paradise Flycatcher','Terpsiphone paradisi','Murai-Gading India','印缅寿带','Rarity','Va','All ages, sexes and morph types resemble Blyth’s Paradise Flycatcher and Amur Paradise Flycatcher but can be easily separated from these similar looking species by its long, pointed and fully erected crest.','Inhabit thick forests and well-wooded habitats in its breeding range.','Feed on a variety of insects taken in sallies from a perch or snatched as they flush. Usually forage high up the canopy.',NULL,NULL,'fst','brown/blue/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Monarchs (Monarchidae)',291,'Blyth''s Paradise Flycatcher','Terpsiphone affinis','Murai-Gading Biasa','中南寿带','Non-rarity','M','For female and first-winter/sub-adult birds, bright rufous-chestnut upperparts and tail, head, throat and breast slaty-grey, crown black and crested. Between the two subspecies, grey hind-collar prominent in indochinensis versus usually incomplete in affinis. The tail of adult males can extend up to 27 cm or more but is rarely seen in Singapore. Adult males of the three paradise flycatcher species found in Singapore (Amur, Blyth’s and Indian) occur as a white as well as a brown morph. However, white birds (rare in Singapore) with nearly all white plumage and glossy black head could not be conclusively identified as either Amur or Blyth’s Paradise Flycatcher.','Any wooded habitat ranging from broadleaved evergreen forest to secondary growth, mangroves, parks, gardens and offshore islands.','Feed on a variety of insects taken in sallies from a perch or snatched as they flush. Usually forage high up the canopy.',20.0,22.0,'fst/pnr','black/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Monarchs (Monarchidae)',292,'Amur Paradise Flycatcher','Terpsiphone incei','Murai-Gading Utara','寿带','Non-rarity','M','For female and first-winter/sub-adult birds, deeper maroon-chestnut upperparts and tail, black hood (crown, face and throat) contrast markedly with the greyish upperbreast. The tail of adult males can extend up to 27 cm or more but is rarely seen in Singapore. Adult males of the three paradise flycatcher species found in Singapore (Amur, Blyth’s and Indian) occur as a white as well as a brown morph. However, white birds (rare in Singapore) with nearly all white plumage and glossy black head could not be conclusively identified as either Amur or Blyth’s Paradise Flycatcher.','Any wooded habitat ranging from broadleaved evergreen forest to secondary growth, mangroves, parks, gardens and offshore islands.','Feed on a variety of insects taken in sallies from a perch or snatched as they flush. Usually forage high up the canopy.',20.0,22.0,'fst/pnr','black/orange/blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Monarchs (Monarchidae)',293,'Japanese Paradise Flycatcher','Terpsiphone atrocaudata','Murai-Gading Ungu','紫寿带','Non-rarity','M','Male resembles Amur and Oriental Paradise Flycatcher but head and breast all black, mantle glossy dark purple, belly whitish, and tail can extend up to 23 cm or more. Female very similar to Oriental Paradise Flycatcher but upperbreast more brownish tinted, belly more white, upperparts duller (never distinctly bright rufous-chestnut). The margin between the breast and belly resembles an inverted “U”.','Any wooded habitat ranging from broadleaved evergreen forest to secondary growth, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Feed on a variety of insects taken in sallies from a perch or snatched as they flush. Usually forage high up the canopy.',18.0,20.0,'pnr','yellow/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Crows, Jays (Corvidae)',294,'Malayan Black Magpie','Platysmurus leucopterus','Burung-Kambing Barat','白翅鹊','Rarity','Vi','All black with band of white along greater coverts and tertials. Long, broad tail.','Forest edge of mature or well-grown secondary growth.','Often found foraging at upper or mid-canopy level. Presence often given away by raucous, distinctive call.',NULL,NULL,'fst','black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Crows, Jays (Corvidae)',295,'House Crow','Corvus splendens','Gagak Rumah','家鸦','Non-rarity','I','Blackish plumage with greyish collar consisting of nape, mantle, neck and breast.','Widespread, including urban areas, gardens, scrubland, mangroves.','Noisy, roosts communally in large numbers.',40.0,43.0,'pnr/resd','black/grey/blue','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Crows, Jays (Corvidae)',296,'Large-billed Crow','Corvus macrorhynchos','Gagak Paruh Besar','大嘴乌鸦','Non-rarity','R','Large crow with blackish plumage. Told apart from House Crow by lack of greyish collar, larger bill and steep forehead.','Open forest and woodlands.','Less adapted to urban environments than house crow.',48.0,59.0,'resd','black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Tits, Chickadees (Paridae)',297,'Japanese Tit','Parus minor','Seserai Asia Timur','远东山雀','Rarity','Va','Large tit with black head and white face patch. Pale yellow underparts with black ventral line down the middle. Upperparts yellowish-green, with greyish-blue tinge on wing coverts. Tail similarly greyish-blue.','Forests, parks, secondary growth, shrub.',NULL,12.5,15.0,'fst/pnr','black/white/yellow',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Larks (Alaudidae)',298,'Eurasian Skylark','Alauda arvensis','Seriayu Erasia','云雀','Rarity','Va','Sparrow-like songbird, with heavily streaked brownish upperparts, short crest. Face unstreaked with pale supercilium, dark ear coverts. Dark streaks across breast, pale underparts with faintly streaked flanks.','Grasslands','Runs on ground in a mouse-like fashion.',16.0,19.0,'open','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',299,'Buff-vented Bulbul','Iole crypta','Merbah-Riang Biasa','棕臀短脚鹎','Rarity','Vi','Adult has brownish upperparts, greyish underparts, blackish crown streaks, pale supercilium, silvery-white eyes, long heavy bill and buffish undertail-coverts. Juvenile resembles adult but has light brown eyes.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.','A generalist feeder, searching foliage for arthropods and also sallies after insects passing in flight. The fruit part of the diet include figs.',20.0,20.5,'fst','brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',300,'Cinereous Bulbul','Hemixos cinereus','Merbah-Kelabu Biasa','灰黑短脚鹎','Non-rarity','Vi','Adult has brownish upperparts, streaked crown with short crest, black mask, brown ear-coverts, whitish throat and pale greyish breast.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded areas, parks and gardens.','Gregarious and congregates at fruiting trees with other bulbuls.',20.5,21.0,'pnr','black/grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',301,'Streaked Bulbul','Ixos malaccensis','Bebarau-Bukit Melayu','纹羽鹎','Rarity','Vi','Adult has olive upperparts and distinctive whitish streaks on greyish-brown throat and breast. Juvenile resembles adult but has warmer brown upperparts and plainer breast.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.',NULL,23.0,23.0,'fst','green/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',302,'Black-and-white Bulbul','Microtarsus melanoleucos','Merbah Bahu Putih','黑白鹎','Rarity','Vi','Male has overall blackish-brown plumage with contrasting white upper- and underwing-coverts. Female is somewhat browner than male and has less white on upperwing-coverts. Juvenile is paler and browner (especially the underparts) and lacks white on upperwing-coverts.','Forest and forest edge.','Nomadic. Often frequents the canopy which make observations difficult.',18.0,18.0,'fst','black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',303,'Black-headed Bulbul','Brachypodius melanocephalos','Merbah Siam','黑头鹎','Non-rarity','R','Adult has mostly yellowish-green plumage, black crestless head, blue eyering and broad black subterminal tail-band. Juvenile is generally duller than adult.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.',NULL,18.0,18.0,'fst','black/blue/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',304,'Black-crested Bulbul','Rubigula flaviventris','Merbah-Kunyit Jambul Biasa','黑冠黄鹎','Non-rarity','I','Adult has glossy black head with tall erect crest, white eyes, bright yellow underparts and rather uniform greenish-olive upperparts. Juvenile has duller head.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.',NULL,18.5,19.5,'fst','black/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',305,'Cream-vented Bulbul','Pycnonotus simplex','Merbah Mata Putih Biasa','白眼褐鹎','Non-rarity','R','Adult has striking whitish eyes, cold brown uppperparts, washed greyish-brown breast and flanks, creamy-whitish throat, belly and vent. Juvenile resembles adult but has pale brown eyes.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.',NULL,18.0,18.0,'fst','brown/grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',306,'Olive-winged Bulbul','Pycnonotus plumosus','Merbah Telinga Lorek Melayu','橄榄褐鹎','Non-rarity','R','Adult has whitish streaks on ear-coverts, brownish upperparts with distinctive yellowish-olive flight feathers, pale brownish underparts, dark red eyes, all-dark bill and dark buffish undertail-coverts. Juvenile resembles adult but has brownish eyes and duller flight feathers.','Forest, forest edge, secondary growth, wooded area and mangroves.',NULL,20.0,20.5,'fst/wet','brown/yellow/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',307,'Asian Red-eyed Bulbul','Pycnonotus brunneus','Merbah Mata Merah Biasa','红眼褐鹎','Non-rarity','R','Adult has prominent red eyes, warm-brownish uppperparts and pale brownish underparts. Juvenile resembles adult but has pale brown eyes. Juvenile resembles adult but has brownish eyes.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.',NULL,19.0,19.0,'fst','brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',308,'Straw-headed Bulbul','Pycnonotus zeylanicus','Barau-barau Raya','黄冠鹎','Non-rarity','I/R','Largest bulbul species in Singapore with strong bill, yellowish-orange crown and ear coverts, blackish eye and submoustachial stripes, whitish throat, bold whitish streaks on brownish breast and olive-green wings and uppertail coverts. Juvenile has duller and browner head.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.','Very vocal especially at dawn and before dusk. Gregarious and often perches on low branches overlooking water.',29.0,29.0,'fst','brown/orange','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',309,'Red-whiskered Bulbul','Pycnonotus jocosus','Merbah Telinga Merah','红耳鹎','Non-rarity','I','Adult has earthly brown upperparts contrasting with white underparts, tall erect black crest, prominent white cheek and throat with black moustachial stripe, small red ear patch and reddish vent. Juvenile resembles adult but duller overall, lacks the red face patch and has brownish crest.','Open terrain, wooded area, gardens and parks.',NULL,18.0,20.5,'pnr','white/black/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',310,'Yellow-vented Bulbul','Pycnonotus goiavier','Merbah Kapur','白眉黄臀鹎','Non-rarity','R','Adult has brown upperparts, dark crown and loral stripe, broad white supercilium, white throat, whitish underparts with vague streaks and yellow vent.','Mangroves, secondary growth, wooded areas, gardens and parks.',NULL,20.0,20.5,'pnr/wet','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Bulbuls (Pycnonotidae)',311,'Sooty-headed Bulbul','Pycnonotus aurigaster','Merbah Ubun Hitam Selatan','白喉红臀鹎','Non-rarity','I','Adult has black head, chin and nape with short crest, brown upperparts with white rump, white underparts and orange-red vent. Juvenile resembles adult but has browner head and paler vent.','Open wooded area.',NULL,19.0,21.0,'pnr','white/black/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swallows, Martins (Hirundinidae)',312,'Sand Martin','Riparia riparia','Layang-layang Perang Belang Biasa','崖沙燕','Rarity','M','Adult resembles Barn Swallow and Asian House Martin but has all brown upperparts, contrasting whitish underparts with broad brown breast-band and shallow forked tail. Juvenile resembles adult but has less distinct breast-band.','Lakes, rivers, reservoirs and coastal areas.',NULL,11.5,13.0,'wet','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swallows, Martins (Hirundinidae)',313,'Pacific Swallow','Hirundo tahitica','Layang-layang Biasa','洋斑燕','Non-rarity','R','Forked tail with dark upperparts and dark blue gloss. Rufous forehead, throat, upper breast. Underparts grey.','Found extensively throughout Singapore.','Told apart from other airborne birds by flying by folding wings back.',13.0,14.0,'wet/pnr','orange/blue/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swallows, Martins (Hirundinidae)',314,'Barn Swallow','Hirundo rustica','Layang-layang Hijrah','家燕','Non-rarity','M','Forehead rufous chestnut, upperparts steel blue, pale or rufous underparts, variable depending on subspecies. Told apart from Pacific Swallow by presence of steel-blue breastband. Told apart from sand martin by more deeply forked tail.','Widespread.','Told apart from other airborne birds by flying by sweeping wings backwards.',15.0,15.0,'pnr/resd','white/black/blue','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swallows, Martins (Hirundinidae)',315,'Siberian House Martin','Delichon lagopodum','Layang-layang Gunung Timur','白腹毛脚燕','Rarity','Va','Can be distinguished from Asian House Martin by its extensive white rump (with white uppertail coverts) that extends onto the lower back, a deeper tail fork, and dusky underwing coverts.','Open areas','Insectivorous, forages with other aerial insectivores, has a slow flight.',13.0,14.0,'open','brown/white','feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swallows, Martins (Hirundinidae)',316,'Asian House Martin','Delichon dasypus','Layang-layang Gunung Asia','烟腹毛脚燕','Non-rarity','M','Adult resembles Barn Swallow but has all darkish-blue head and upperparts with broad greyish-white rump and underparts, darkish underwing-coverts and shallow forked tail.','Forest and open areas.',NULL,12.0,13.0,'fst/pnr','black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Swallows, Martins (Hirundinidae)',317,'Red-rumped Swallow','Cecropis daurica','Layang-layang Api Utara','金腰燕','Non-rarity','M','Long-winged and long, deeply-forked tail. Glossy dark upperparts, streaked underparts, rufous rump.','Aerial, widespread.',NULL,16.0,17.0,'pnr/resd','brown/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leaf Warblers & Allies (Phylloscopidae)',318,'Yellow-browed Warbler','Phylloscopus inornatus','Cekup-Daun Kecil Biasa','黄眉柳莺','Non-rarity','M','Adult resembles Arctic Warbler and Eastern Crowned Warbler but is smaller and has broad yellowish-white supercilium, two broad yellowish-white wing bars and whitish tips on blackish tertials.','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas, parks and gardens.','Frequents the canopy.',11.0,11.5,'fst/pnr','yellow/green','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leaf Warblers & Allies (Phylloscopidae)',319,'Dusky Warbler','Phylloscopus fuscatus','Cekup-Daun Perang Rawa','褐柳莺','Rarity','Va','Adult resembles Arctic Warbler but has dark to greyish-brown uppperparts without any pale wing bars, dirty-whitish underparts and buffish wash on breast-sides, flanks and undertail-coverts.','Open areas and often in wetter habitats than other Phylloscopus warblers.','Frequents low bushes and small trees, usually within the vicinity of water.',12.0,12.5,'wet','brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leaf Warblers & Allies (Phylloscopidae)',320,'Eastern Crowned Warbler','Phylloscopus coronatus','Cekup-Daun Raja Timur','冕柳莺','Non-rarity','M','Resembles Arctic Warbler and Sakhalin Leaf Warbler but has well-defined pale median coronal stripe on darker crown (which is more distinct at the rear often not reaching the fore-crown), longer bill with dark upper mandible and pale lower mandible (with no dark tip), yellower-green upperparts, whiter underparts and pale yellow undertail-coverts.','Forests, mangroves, gardens, parks and suitable wooded areas.','Frequents the canopy where it forages in the foliage.',12.5,13.0,'wet/pnr','green/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leaf Warblers & Allies (Phylloscopidae)',321,'Sakhalin Leaf Warbler','Phylloscopus borealoides','Cekup-Daun Kaki Pudar Jepun','库页岛柳莺','Rarity','M','Adult resembles Arctic Warbler but has dark greyish crown contrasting with olive-greenish mantle, warmish olive-brown rump and pale greyish pink legs and feet. Indistinguishable from the very similar looking Pale-legged Leaf Warbler visually (or oftentimes even in hand), and in the field it can only be told apart by its call (~5Khz instead of ~6Khz) or characteristic song.','Forest.','Usually forages for insects on the forest floor, sometimes climbing up low shrubs and vines to glean prey. May also be found in the mid-storey to canopy levels.',11.5,11.5,'fst','green/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leaf Warblers & Allies (Phylloscopidae)',322,'Pale-legged Leaf Warbler','Phylloscopus tenellipes','Cekup-Daun Kaki Pudar Barat','淡脚柳莺','Rarity','Va','Adult resembles Arctic Warbler but has dark greyish crown contrasting with olive-greenish mantle, warmish olive-brown rump and pale greyish pink legs and feet. Indistinguishable from the very similar looking Sakhalin Leaf Warbler visually (or oftentimes even in hand), and in the field it can only be told apart by its call (~6Khz instead of ~5Khz) or characteristic song.','Forest.','Usually forages for insects on the forest floor, sometimes climbing up low shrubs and vines to glean prey. May also be found in the mid-storey to canopy levels.',NULL,NULL,'fst','brown/green/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leaf Warblers & Allies (Phylloscopidae)',323,'Arctic Warbler','Phylloscopus borealis','Cekup-Daun Artik','极北柳莺','Non-rarity','M','Adult has long yellowish-white supercilium, olive-green crown and upperparts with two narrow wing bars (indistinct when worn), whitish grey underparts, dark tip at lower mandible and yellowish-orange legs.','Forest, forest edge, wooded areas, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Frequents the canopy.',12.5,13.0,'fst/pnr','green/white/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Reed Warblers & Allies (Acrocephalidae)',324,'Oriental Reed Warbler','Acrocephalus orientalis','Cekup-Paya Besar Biasa','东方大苇莺','Non-rarity','M','Adult has prominent whitish supercilium, warm olive-brown upperparts and whitish underparts with warm buffish wash on flanks.','Reedbeds, scrubs and wet grasslands.','Skulks in thick vegetation.',18.0,20.0,'wet','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Reed Warblers & Allies (Acrocephalidae)',325,'Black-browed Reed Warbler','Acrocephalus bistrigiceps','Cekup-Paya Kecil Biasa','黑眉苇莺','Non-rarity','M','Adult has long broad pale buff supercilium bordered above by prominent black lateral crown-stripe, warm olive-brown upperparts with slightly more rufescent rump and whitish underparts with warm buff breast-sides and flanks.','Reedbed and grassland near water.','Skulks in reedbeeds and tall dense waterside vegetation.',13.5,14.0,'wet','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Reed Warblers & Allies (Acrocephalidae)',326,'Booted Warbler','Iduna caligata','Cekup-Pokok Kecil Utara','靴篱莺','Rarity','Va','Resembles Black-browed Reed Warbler but is significantly smaller, lacks the black lateral crown-stripes, has a short faint supercilium, paler brown upperparts and pinkish legs.','Open country among bushes and tall vegetation.','Forages among trees and other tall vegetation instead of reed-beds and grassland.',11.0,12.5,'pnr','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Grassbirds & Allies (Locustellidae)',327,'Pallas''s Grasshopper Warbler','Helopsaltes certhiola','Cekup-Tikus Berjalur Biasa','小蝗莺','Non-rarity','M','Resembles Lanceolated Warbler but larger with more rufescent upperparts, streaked crown/nape, bold black stripes on mantle and lacks dark streaks on flanks and undertail-coverts. Juvenile like adult but has faint streaks at lower throat.','Tall reeds, grass and other vegetation near freshwater wetlands.','Call is markedly different from Lanceolated Warbler, consisting of rapidly delivered, well-structured musical warbling phrases.',14.0,15.0,'pnr/wet','brown/white/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Grassbirds & Allies (Locustellidae)',328,'Lanceolated Warbler','Locustella lanceolata','Cekup-Tikus Berjalur Kecil','矛斑蝗莺','Non-rarity','M','Resembles Pallas’s Grasshopper Warbler but smaller and shows prominent streaking on crown, mantle, rump, lower throat, breast, flanks and undertail-coverts and lacks the pronounced rufescent plumage tones. Juvenile is somewhat less heavily/boldly streaked.','Grass, weeds and scrub.','Very skulking, forages on or near ground and difficult to flush.',12.0,13.5,'fst/pnr','brown/white/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cisticolas & Allies (Cisticolidae)',329,'Zitting Cisticola','Cisticola juncidis','Cak-Tinting Kecil Biasa','棕扇尾莺','Non-rarity','R','Resembles Pallas’s Grasshopper Warbler and Lanceolated Warbler but much smaller. Adult has buffish-brown upperparts with blackish streaks, rufous rump and whitish underparts with rufous-buff wash on flanks.','Grasslands, marshes and open habitats.','Usually skulks in long grass. During breeding season, male will hover and circle in the air.',10.5,12.0,'pnr/wet','brown/white/orange','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cisticolas & Allies (Cisticolidae)',330,'Yellow-bellied Prinia','Prinia flaviventris','Perenjak-Padi Biasa','黄腹山鹪莺','Non-rarity','R','Adult has slaty-grey crown, head-sides and nape, olive-green rest of upperparts, narrow white supercilium in front of eye, whitish throat and upperbreast, bright yellow belly and long pinkish legs. Juvenile resembles adult but has duller head.','Grasslands and open habitats.','Skulky. Usually sings from the top of a reed stalk or grass stem.',12.0,14.5,'pnr','grey/yellow/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cisticolas & Allies (Cisticolidae)',331,'Common Tailorbird','Orthotomus sutorius','Perenjak-Pisang Biasa','长尾缝叶莺','Non-rarity','R','Greenish upperparts and greyish underparts with pale bill. Rufous forehead and lores, legs pinkish. Told apart from Dark-necked Tailorbird by lack of yellow vent.','Scrub, degraded forests, forests, mangroves.','Skulky, flitting inbetween bushes.',10.5,13.0,'fst/pnr','grey/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cisticolas & Allies (Cisticolidae)',332,'Dark-necked Tailorbird','Orthotomus atrogularis','Perenjak-Pisang Leher Hitam','黑喉缝叶莺','Non-rarity','R','Rufous crown, greyish underparts, black streaks on upper breast, olive upperparts. Told apart from Common Tailorbird by presence of yellow vent.','Forests, secondary growth, scrub, degraded forests.','Skulky, flitting inbetween bushes.',10.5,12.0,'fst/pnr','green/orange/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cisticolas & Allies (Cisticolidae)',333,'Rufous-tailed Tailorbird','Orthotomus sericeus','Perenjak-Pisang Ekor Merah','红头缝叶莺','Non-rarity','R','Bright chestnut hood, with white throat and rufous tail. Greyish upperparts with whitisih underparts, sometimes streaked with grey.','Forests, secondary forests, forest edges.',NULL,12.0,14.0,'fst/pnr','black/green/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Cisticolas & Allies (Cisticolidae)',334,'Ashy Tailorbird','Orthotomus ruficeps','Perenjak-Pisang Kelabu Biasa','灰缝叶莺','Non-rarity','R','Grey tailorbird with rufous forehead, crown, lores and eye area.','Coastal forests, mangroves, but also secondary forests and gardens.','Skulky, calls often.',11.0,11.5,'pnr','brown/orange/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('White-eyes (Zosteropidae)',335,'Swinhoe''s White-eye','Zosterops simplex','Kelicap Kacamata Biasa','暗绿绣眼鸟','Non-rarity','I','Olive-green upperparts with white eye-ring. Throat, upperbreast and forehead yellow. Lower breast and belly pale grey with yellow undertail coverts. Yellow ventral stripe that extend to the belly for native subspecies erwini that is lacking in introduced simplex.','Occurs in secondary forests, forest edge, old plantation, scrub, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Highly gregarious. Usually seen in small flocks gathered to feed at flowering trees.',10.5,11.0,'fst/pnr','green/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Babblers, Scimitar Babblers (Timaliidae)',336,'Pin-striped Tit-Babbler','Mixornis gularis','Kekicau-Berjalur Biasa','纹胸巨鹛','Non-rarity','R','Adult has rufous crown, wings and tail, olive-brown back/mantle and yellowish head-sides and underparts with broad streaks at throat and breast. Juvenile looks plainer/paler than adult.','Forest and wooded area.','Gregarious and forages near the ground.',12.5,14.0,'fst/pnr','brown/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Babblers, Scimitar Babblers (Timaliidae)',337,'Chestnut-winged Babbler','Cyanoderma erythropterum','Kekicau-Kantan Kelip','红翅穗鹛','Non-rarity','R','Adult has chestnut brown crown, mantle, wings and tail, greyish head-sides/breast and blue orbital skin. Juvenile resembles adult but has paler plumage and duller orbital skin.','Forest','Forages in small groups, methodically foliage-gleaning in the middle and lower storey.',12.5,13.5,'fst','grey/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ground Babblers (Pellorneidae)',338,'Moustached Babbler','Malacopteron magnirostre','Kekicau-Cangkuk Bermisai','须树鹛','Rarity','Ex','Adult has rather uniform olive-brown crown and mantle, greyish head-sides, distinctive dark moustachial stripe, whitish underparts with vague streaking across breast and strongly rufescent tail. Juvenile has indistinct moustachial and pinkish lower mandible.','Forest','Forages at the lower mid-stratum and understorey of forests.',16.5,18.0,'fst','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ground Babblers (Pellorneidae)',339,'Short-tailed Babbler','Pellorneum malaccense','Kekicau Ekor Pendek Biasa','短尾雅鹛','Non-rarity','R','Adult has short tail, black moustachial, grey ear-coverts, white throat and long pink feet. Juvenile resembles adult but has browner head-sides.','Tropical moist lowland forests.','Forages in the understory and on the forest floor for insects.',13.5,15.5,'fst','brown/orange/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ground Babblers (Pellorneidae)',340,'White-chested Babbler','Pellorneum rostratum','Kekicau-Telunjuk Dada Putih','白胸雅鹛','Rarity','R','Adult has narrow bill, cold brown upperparts and clean white underparts with grey-washed breast-side. Juvenile looks similar to adult.','Forest, swamp forest and mangroves.','Feeds on small invertebrates taken from the forest floor, mainly in wet areas.',15.0,16.5,'fst/wet','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Ground Babblers (Pellorneidae)',341,'Abbott''s Babbler','Malacocincla abbotti','Kekicau-Belukar Biasa','阿氏雅鹛','Non-rarity','R','Rufous-tailed Tailorbird','Forest, secondary growth and suitable wooded areas.','Usually seen singly or in pairs foraging near the ground for insects and small invertebrates.',15.0,16.5,'fst/pnr','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Laughingthrushes & Allies (Leiothrichidae)',342,'Chinese Hwamei','Garrulax canorus','Kekicau-Raya Cina','画眉','Non-rarity','I','Medium-sized laughingthrush, brown overall with white eyering and white eyestripe extending behind eye.','Woodland, scrub vegetation.','Forages on ground. Males have a rich song that can be variable, capable of mimicking sounds.',21.0,24.0,'fst','brown/white','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Laughingthrushes & Allies (Leiothrichidae)',343,'White-crested Laughingthrush','Garrulax leucolophus','Kekicau-Raya Berjambul Biasa','白冠噪鹛','Non-rarity','I','Large laughingthrush with white head and breast, black mask and brown body.','Woodland, secondary forest.','Gregarious, largely forages on ground, often noisy when in groups.',26.0,31.0,'pnr/resd','brown/white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Fairy-bluebirds (Irenidae)',344,'Asian Fairy-bluebird','Irena puella','Murai-Gajah Biasa','和平鸟','Non-rarity','R','Bulky and distinctive, male is mostly black with shinning deep blue upperparts and vent while female is duller turquoise-blue overall. Bright red irises are present in both genders.','Forest and forest edge.','Often observed feeding on fig trees with green-pigeons and migratory thrushes.',24.5,26.5,'fst','blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Nuthatches (Sittidae)',345,'Velvet-fronted Nuthatch','Sitta frontalis','Pepatuk Biasa','绒额䴓','Rarity','Vi','Bright blue upperparts, pale underparts, with black forehead and bright red legs and bill quite unlike any other species in Singapore. Bill colour is paler in juveniles.','Healthy Forest','Often observed foraging along the barks and branches of trees alone or in pairs, frequently running upside down. Also observed in mixed flocks elsewhere in its range.',12.0,13.5,'fst','blue/black/red','branch/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',346,'Asian Glossy Starling','Aplonis panayensis','Perling-Kilat Asia','亚洲辉椋鸟','Non-rarity','R','Adults have overall glossy blackish-green plumage, black bill and legs, and diagnostic red eyes. Juveniles have greyish-brown upperparts and dull buffish-white underparts with bold dark streaks.','Forest, wooded areas, mangroves, parks and gardens.','Feeds on insects and fruits. Gregarious when foraging and may form big flocks at roosting sites.',22.0,25.0,'fst/pnr','black/blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',347,'Common Hill Myna','Gracula religiosa','Tiung-Emas Biasa','鹩哥','Non-rarity','R','Large glossy myna with distinctive orange-yellow wattles on face, bill a deep vivid orange, legs yellow.','Parkland, forest edges, tropical forests.','Calls loud and variable, sometimes seen in groups, feeds largely on fruit but also takes other food, including other small invertebrates and vertebrates.',27.0,31.0,'fst/pnr','blue/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',348,'Javan Myna','Acridotheres javanicus','Gembala-Kerbau Sawah Jawa','爪哇八哥','Non-rarity','I','Dark grey overall with whitish or pale yellow iris and yellow bill. Undertail coverts are white, with yellow legs. Prominent white base to primaries visible in flight. Compared to Common Myna, much greyer in appearance and lacks the bare patch of yellow skin around its eyes.','Open habitat, scrub vegetation, forest edge.','Omnivorous, forages on ground and sometimes trees, often associated with humans in urban habitats. Roosts in large groups in trees.',24.0,25.0,'pnr/resd','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',349,'Common Myna','Acridotheres tristis','Gembala-Kerbau Rumah','家八哥','Non-rarity','I/R','Brownish overall with constrasting black head, yellow bare patch around the eye, yellow bill and legs. Undertail coverts are white,  and prominent white base to primaries visible in flight. The similar looking Javan Myna is darker overall and lacks the yellow eye patch.','Open country, villages','Population in Singapore originated from introduced escaped individuals around the mid 1930s. A massive range expansion of this species occured through the Peninsula in the past century while the locally introduced population was expanding massively. This self-introduced population eventually reached Singapore some time after the 1980s to merge with the local (introduced) population. The current population in Singapore hence has a mixture of introduced and self-introduced ancestry. This species has also been introduced to various places globally and is listed in "100 of the World''s Worst Invasive Alien Species" by the IUCN.',24.5,27.0,'pnr/resd','brown/white/black','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',350,'Red-billed Starling','Spodiopsar sericeus','Perling Paruh Merah','丝光椋鸟','Rarity','Va','Medium-sized starling with red bill, sometimes tipped black. Males have a white head, greyish body. Females are brownish. Both sexes have black wings, with white wing patches; black tails; yellowish legs.','Gardens, parks, fields and scrub.',NULL,21.0,24.0,'pnr/open','white/grey/brown',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',351,'White-cheeked Starling','Spodiopsar cineraceus','Perling Pipi Putih','灰椋鸟','Rarity','Va','Rather uniform brownish-grey body with conspicuous white ear coverts and forehead. Pale belly and vent with white rump. Bill and legs yellow to orange.','Open habitat.','Gregarious, mostly forages on ground.',22.0,24.0,'open','white/grey','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',352,'Daurian Starling','Agropsar sturninus','Perling Ubun Ungu','北椋鸟','Non-rarity','M','Male has pale greyish head and underparts, glossy dark purplish nape-patch and upperparts, glossy dark upperwings with two whitish wingbars and black tail. Female and juvenile look similar to male but glossy dark plumage replaced with brown.','Forest, wooded areas, gardens, parks, open and coastal habitats.','Highly gregarious. Can form huge flock of up to a thousand birds on passage.',17.0,19.0,'fst/pnr/oc','green/black/white','fly');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',353,'Chestnut-cheeked Starling','Agropsar philippensis','Perling Pipi Coklat','紫背椋鸟','Rarity','Va','Male resembles Daurian Starling but has diagnostic chestnut patch on ear-coverts and neck-side. Female without chestnut patch and difficult to separate from female Daurian Starling but when in flight, lacks whitish tips to scapulars, greater coverts and tertials.','Wooded areas and open habitats.','Feed on insects and fruits.',16.5,17.0,'fst/pnr','black/white/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',354,'White-shouldered Starling','Sturnia sinensis','Perling Bahu Putih','灰背椋鸟','Non-rarity','M','Male displays mostly grey plumage with black wing and tail contrasting with a large white shoulder patch formed by upperwing-coverts and scapulars. Also has whiter rump and uppertail-coverts, mostly bluish-grey bill and white iris. White shoulder patch smaller for female and lacking in juvenile.','Coastal habitat and open areas with scattered trees.','Gregarious. Attracted to small-fruited, mass-cropping banyan figs, and also observed foraging in the crowns of casuarinas.',18.5,20.5,'oc/wet','grey/white/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',355,'Brahminy Starling','Sturnia pagodarum','Perling Ubun Hitam','黑冠椋鸟','Rarity','Va','Distinctive plumage, with black crown, light iris, sandy-grey upperparts, cinnamon-rufous underparts and bicoloured bill that is yellow and blue.','Open habitats, including forest, scrubland, and fields.','Omnivorous, prefers foraging on ground. Status of bird has been debated (escapee vs genuine vagrant) but increasing records of this species in Indochina, especially Thailand and Singapore, suggests that this species could be a semi-regular vagrant during the winter months (Soe Naing et al., 2016).',20.0,20.0,'fst/open','grey/orange/black','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',356,'Rosy Starling','Pastor roseus','Perling Jambu','粉红椋鸟','Rarity','Va','A myna-size starling with pinkish plumage, blackish head, wings, tail and vent. Juvenile has pale sandy greyish-brown upperparts with darker wings and tail, paler underparts and yellowish bill.','Coastal habitats, parks and gardens.','Observed to flock with Common Myna and Asian Glossy Starling.',21.0,24.0,'pnr/sea','brown/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Starlings, Rhabdornis (Sturnidae)',357,'Common Starling','Sturnus vulgaris','Perling Bintang','紫翅椋鸟','Rarity','Va','Adults have a long bill, pointed wings and short tail both with buff margins. Breeding adults are overall dark with purple and green iridescence. Non-breeding adults are distinct in their speckly appearance due to pale feather tips. Sexes similar with adult females showing less glossy plumage. Bill is yellow in breeding adults with the base pale blue in males but pale pink in females. Juveniles are a uniform grey-brown with varying amounts of pale-tipped dark feathers depending on progress of moult into the adult plumage. Compared to Asian Glossy Starling in breeding plumage, lacks red eye and has yellow bill and reddish legs. Compared to Chinese Blackbird in breeding plumage, smaller, shorter-tailed, lacks yellow eyering and uniform upperparts.','Wide range of open habitats e.g. fields, agricultural, seashore.','Roosts in staggering numbers and forming murmurations. A very adaptable species, as seen from the sweeping colonisation of North America from a single introduction locality. Moults by wear; pale feather tips acquired in non-breeding plumage wears away in spring to produce the glossy blackish breeding plumage.',20.0,23.0,'open/sea','black/white/brown',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Thrushes (Turdidae)',358,'Siberian Thrush','Geokichla sibirica','Murai-Tanah Kelabu Tua','白眉地鸫','Rarity','M','Male has overall dark slaty plumage, broad white supercilium and white vent dark-scaled undertail-coverts. Female has mainly plain brown upperparts, prominent buffy-whitish supercilium (curved round behind ear-coverts), buffy-whitish underparts with brown scales/molting on breast and flanks. First-winter male shows mixed character of male and female.','Forest and suitable wooded area.','Very shy. Feed mainly on small, soft, fleshy berries but also take insects.',21.5,23.5,'fst','black/blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Thrushes (Turdidae)',359,'Orange-headed Thrush','Geokichla citrina','Murai-Tanah Jingga Asia','橙头地鸫','Non-rarity','M','Subspecies innotata has distinctive orange head and underparts with bluish-grey upperparts. Subspecies gibsonhilli looks similar but has white median covert tips (wingbar) and blackish line across eyes and behind ear-coverts.','Forest and wooded areas.','Forages ground for insects but also feeds on fruits.',20.5,23.5,'fst','orange/blue','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Thrushes (Turdidae)',360,'Chinese Blackbird','Turdus mandarinus','Murai-Belanda Hitam Cina','乌鸫','Rarity','Va','As the name suggests, male is all black with orange-yellow bill and eyering; female is dark brown with slightly darker wings.','Open habitat, inlcuding woodland, parks, grasslands.','Prefers foraging on ground. Part of the family Turdidae that includes other more well-known thrushes in Singapore such as the Orange-headed Thrush and Eyebrowed Thrush.',28.0,29.0,'fst/pnr/open','black/brown','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Thrushes (Turdidae)',361,'Eyebrowed Thrush','Turdus obscurus','Murai-Belanda Bercelak Biasa','白眉鸫','Non-rarity','M','Male displays greyish head, olive-brown mantle, white supercilium, check-bar and chin, orange upperbreast and flanks and white belly. Female looked similar but head and mantle brownish.','Forest, secondary growth, mangroves and gardens on migration.','Fond of fruiting trees but may also forage ground.',22.5,24.5,'pnr/fst','brown/orange/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',362,'Oriental Magpie-Robin','Copsychus saularis','Murai-Kampung Biasa','鹊鸲','Non-rarity','I/R','Male has glossy blackish head, upperparts and upper breast, white lower breast to vent and broad white wing-stripe. Female resembles male but black plumage replaced by dark grey. Juvenile resembles female but has dark greyish scales at upper breast.','Forest edge, gardens, parks, wooded areas and mangroves.','Forages in trees as well as ground where it hops with tail raised.',19.0,21.0,'pnr/fst','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',363,'White-rumped Shama','Copsychus malabaricus','Murai-Hutan Biasa','白腰鹊鸲','Non-rarity','I/R','Male has glossy blue-black head, upperparts and upper breast, orange-rufous rest of underparts, conspicuous white rump and long blackish tail. Female resembles male but blue-black plumage replaced by dark grey and has shorter tail. Juvenile resembles female but has buff speckles on upperparts and dark scales at throat and upper breast.','Forest, forest edge and wooded areas.','Forages mainly ground amongst leaf litter.',21.5,28.0,'fst','orange/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',364,'Spotted Flycatcher','Muscicapa striata','Sambar-Kusam Lorek Erasia','斑鹟','Rarity','Va','Shows a more elongated appearance and is slightly larger than the familiar Asian Brown Flycatcher. Streaked breast similar to Brown-streaked Flycatcher, Dark-sided Flycatcher, and Grey-streaked Flycatcher, but well definined streaks on crown distinguishes this species from the rest. This species also has a buff eye ring and loral spot that is absent from all other similar flycatchers in Singapore.','Highly adaptable, occurring throughout open woodland and lightly-wooded parks and gardens in both its breeding and wintering range.','Hunts by sallying from perches like other flycatchers.',13.5,14.5,'open/pnr','brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',365,'Grey-streaked Flycatcher','Muscicapa griseisticta','Sambar-Kusam Lorek Utara','灰纹鹟','Rarity','Va','Resembles Dark-sided Flycatcher and Brown-streaked Flycatcher but is larger and has clean whitish underparts with extensive, well-defined broad dark greyish streaks across entire breast and flanks and whitish undertail-coverts.','Forest, parks, gardens, wooded areas and mangroves.','Feeds primarily on insects. Often perches on tree branches from which it sallies forth to hawk insects in flight and returns to the same perch or to one nearby.',15.0,15.0,'pnr/fst','black/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',366,'Dark-sided Flycatcher','Muscicapa sibirica','Sambar-Kusam Paruh Kecil','乌鹟','Non-rarity','M','Resembles Asian-brown Flycatcher but has darker upperparts, longer wings (tips reaching two thirds of the way down the tail), shorter and all black bill, smudgy greyish-brown breast/flanks and dark undertail-coverts centres. Juvenile has darker upperparts with distinct pale buff spots/streaks and scaled/blackish streaks on breast and flanks.','Forest, parks, gardens, wooded areas and mangroves.','Usually solitary, frequenting the canopy and middle storey. Typically sits upright on exposed perch, sallying after flying insects.',11.5,13.0,'pnr/fst','black/grey','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',367,'Asian Brown Flycatcher','Muscicapa dauurica','Sambar-Kusam Biasa','北灰鹟','Non-rarity','M','Nondescript flycatcher with brown upperparts and whitish underparts variably suffused with pale grey-brown on upper breast (usually lacking defined streaks), whitish eyering and pale greyish fringes to wing-coverts and tertials.','Forest, parks, gardens, wooded areas and mangroves.',NULL,12.5,13.5,'pnr/fst','brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',368,'Brown-streaked Flycatcher','Muscicapa williamsoni','Sambar-Kusam Lorek Melayu','褐纹鹟','Non-rarity','M','Resembles Asian Brown Flycatcher but has distinct brownish streaks on breast, upper belly and flanks and broad buffy to orange-buff wing-fringing at upperwing coverts. Bill is also slightly larger with pale yellowish and usually dark-tipped lower mandible.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Usually solitary and aerial sally after insects from perches to which they return.',13.0,13.0,'pnr/fst','brown/orange/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',369,'Ferruginous Flycatcher','Muscicapa ferruginea','Sambar-Kusam Api','棕尾褐鹟','Non-rarity','M','Adult has distinctive slaty-grey head, rufescent rump, uppertail-coverts and tail, rusty-rufous fringes on coverts/tertials and rusty-buff breast and flanks. Juvenile resembles adult but has buff streaks on crown, short rusty streaks on upper-mantle and scapulars and darkish scales/mottlings on throat-sides and breast.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Frequents the middle and lower storeys usually near streams.',12.5,13.0,'pnr/fst','brown/orange','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',370,'Chinese Blue Flycatcher','Cyornis glaucicomans','Sambar-Biru Utara','中华仙鹟','Rarity','M','Male resembles Mangrove Blue Flycatcher but orange-rufous plumage extends from throat to upperbreast only with rest of underparts whitish and extensive brown wash on flanks. Female resembles Mugimaki Flycatcher but slightly bigger and has warmer brown upperparts without whitish wingbar, rufescent tail and pale buff throat that contrasts with orange-rufous breast and brown-washed flanks.','Forest, parks, gardens, wooded areas and mangroves.','Forages mostly in the mid-stratum and understorey for insects.',14.0,15.0,'pnr/fst','blue/orange/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',371,'Mangrove Blue Flycatcher','Cyornis rufigastra','Sambar-Biru Bakau','红树仙鹟','Rarity','R','Male has all blue upperparts, deep orange-rufous throat to upper belly and rest of underparts whitish. Female looks like male but has whitish face marks.','Mangroves.','Sallies for flying insects from shaded perches. Nests in the rotted-out hollow top of nipah palm frond-base.',14.5,14.5,'pnr/wet','blue/orange','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',372,'Brown-chested Jungle Flycatcher','Cyornis brunneatus','Sambar-Hutan Cina','白喉林鹟','Non-rarity','M','Resembles Asian Brown Flycatcher but much bigger and has long stout bill with yellow mandible, whitish throat, brownish breast, rufescent tail and pinkish legs.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Frequents the lower storey.',15.0,15.0,'pnr/fst','brown/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',373,'Blue-and-white Flycatcher','Cyanoptila cyanomelana','Sambar-Berlau Rengkung Hitam','白腹蓝鹟','Rarity','M','Male has cobalt-blue upperparts, blackish head-sides, throat and breast with rest of underparts whitish. Female has rather uniform brownish upperparts and breast with contrasting white belly and vent, whitish throat-patch and all black bill. First-winter male resembles female but has blue wings, tail and back to uppertail-coverts. Based on current knowledge, it is not possible to separate non-adult male from Zappey''s Flycatcher in the field.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Forages mainly at the mid-stratum and canopy levels for insects.',18.0,18.0,'pnr/fst','blue/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',374,'Zappey''s Flycatcher','Cyanoptila cumatilis','Sambar-Berlau Rengkung Biru','琉璃蓝鹟','Rarity','M','Male resembles Blue-and-white Flycatcher but has less dark or more bluish head-sides, throat and breast. Female and first-winter male cannot be distinguished from Blue-and-white Flycatcher.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Forages mainly at the mid-stratum and canopy levels for insects.',18.0,18.0,'pnr/fst','blue/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',375,'Verditer Flycatcher','Eumyias thalassinus','Sambar-Ranting Biasa','铜蓝鹟','Rarity','Vi','Verditer-blue plumage makes this a rather distinctive flycatcher unlikely to be confused with other species. Also note whitish tips to undertail-covert feathers (which separate this species from the locally-unrecorded Pale Blue Flycatcher). Males have dark lores, while females and subadult birds have pale greyish lores.','Forests, parkland, and other wooded areas.','Like a typical flycatcher, feeds in mid- to upper-canopy, occasionally descending lower or even to the ground. Sometimes perches on telephone lines, or other man-made structures while hawking for insects.',15.0,17.0,'fst/pnr','blue/black','ground/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',376,'Siberian Blue Robin','Larvivora cyane','Murai-Kecil Biru Biasa','蓝歌鸲','Non-rarity','M','Male has dark blue upperparts, white underparts and pinkish legs. Female resembles male but has greyish-brown upperparts often with some dull blue on rump and uppertail-coverts, buffish-white throat and variably scaled throat-sides and breast. First-winter male resembles female but has more dull blue on upperparts.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Forages at the lowest under storey or on the forest floor. Usually seen bathing in forest streams at dusk.',13.5,14.5,'pnr/fst','blue/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',377,'Yellow-rumped Flycatcher','Ficedula zanthopygia','Sambar-Kunyit Kening Putih','白眉姬鹟','Non-rarity','M','Male has black upperparts with contrasting long white wing patch, pronounced white supercilium and yellow rump and underparts. Often shows strong orange flush on throat and breast in spring. Female looks more nondescript with dull greyish olive upperparts, pale yellowish-buff underparts with faint brownish scales/mottling on throat and breast, yellow rump and white wing patch but often with less white on greater coverts.','Forest, parks, gardens, wooded areas and mangroves.','Forages mostly at the crown level but in more open habitat may adopt lookout perches down to less than 1 meter from the ground.',13.0,13.5,'pnr/fst','black/white/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',378,'Green-backed Flycatcher','Ficedula elisae','Sambar-Kunyit Hijau','绿背姬鹟','Non-rarity','M','Male has olive-green upperparts with white wing patch and yellowish loral stripe, eyering, rump and underparts. Female resembles male but has paler yellowish underparts, no yellow rump and the white wing patch is replaced by two faint narrow pale bars on wing-coverts.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Prefers to forage at the lower storey in typical flycatcher pattern for insects.',13.0,13.5,'pnr/fst','black/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',379,'Narcissus Flycatcher','Ficedula narcissina','Sambar Kunyit Timur','黄眉姬鹟','Rarity','Va','Male resembles Yellow-rumped Flycatcher but has yellow supercilium, yellowish-white belly and small wing-patch without white line along edge of tertials. May shows orange flush on throat in spring. Female resembles Green-backed Flycatcher but much browner above with rusty-coloured wing linings and whiter below with variable dark scales/mottling on throat sides and breast.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Forages at mid-level in typical flycatcher pattern for insects.',13.0,13.5,'pnr/fst','black/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',380,'Mugimaki Flycatcher','Ficedula mugimaki','Sambar Dada Jingga Utara','鸲姬鹟','Non-rarity','M','Male resembles Yellow-rumped Flycatcher but white supercilium is shorter and starts behind eye, has bright rufous orange throat to upper belly and rest of underparts whitish. Female has greyish-brown upperparts with faint narrow whitish buff wingbar, buffish-orange throat to breast and faint or lacking supercilium. First-winter male resembles female but head-sides greyer, supercilium more pronounced, throat/breast brighter and uppertail-coverts mostly blackish.','Forest, parks, gardens and wooded areas.','Usually solitary at wintering grounds and forages frequently at the lower level but may also ascend to feed at the middle storey and canopy levels.',13.0,13.5,'pnr/fst','black/white/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',381,'Taiga Flycatcher','Ficedula albicilla','Sambar Rengkung Merah','红喉姬鹟','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding male and female resembles Asian Brown Flycatcher but has all black bill, distinctive blackish uppertail-coverts and tail and whitish vent and undertail-coverts which contrast prominently against rest of underparts. Male in breeding plumage resembles non-breeding male but has rufous-orange throat.','Forest edge, secondary growth, parks and gardens.','Regularly cocks tail and drops from perch to feed on ground.',13.0,13.0,'pnr','grey/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',382,'Black Redstart','Phoenicurus ochruros','Murai-Jingga Hitam','赭红尾鸲','Rarity','Va','Adult males of race phoenicuroides show grey-black back, head, and upper breast contrasting with orange-rufous lower breast, belly, and vent; rufiventris is similar, but larger, more richly-toned rufous below, and blacker on upperparts. Female is grey-brown on upperparts and underparts. First-winter males are highly variable; some attain near-adult plumage by autumn, while most retain a female-like plumage through the winter. Separated from Daurian Redstart in all plumages by the lack of white wing-spot, which is always present in that species. Most likely confusion species is Common Redstart, which breeds from western Europe to far northwestern China and winters in sub-Saharan Africa. It differs by being noticeably paler in all plumages and always shows some orange-rufous tones on underparts above the vent. The spacing of primaries, visible on photos showing a back view, is the most reliable separator. However, an in-depth discussion of this feature is impossible here; instead see Laurens B Steijn''s article in Dutch Birding 27(3), linked in the references below. Adult males separated from Hodgson''s Redstart (short-distance migrant in China and northern Myanmar) by lack of white wing-spots; females and first-winter birds of that species are noticeably paler and browner, with less grey tones.','Rocky areas and mountain-tops, open country, meadows, and scrubland; also frequently observed in highly urban settings, including villages, towns, and cities.','Often feeds on ground, primarily on invertebrates, but also takes fruits from trees.',14.0,15.0,'open/pnr/resd','grey/orange','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',383,'Daurian Redstart','Phoenicurus auroreus','Murai-Jingga Utara Asia','北红尾鸲','Rarity','Va','Male has greyish crown to upper mantle, black lower mantle and throat, broad white wing-patch and orange-rufous underparts, rump, uppertail-coverts and tail with blackish central feathers. Female and juvenile has uniform brownish overall plumage, smaller white wing-patch and similar rump and tail pattern as the male.','Open forest, forest edge, parks and gardens.',NULL,15.0,15.0,'pnr/fst','black/white/orange','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',384,'Blue Rock Thrush','Monticola solitarius','Tarum Biasa','蓝矶鸫','Rarity','M','Non-breeding male has dull greyish-blue plumage with blackish and white bars/scales and distinctive chestnut lower breast to vent while breeding male is bluer overall and lacks bars/scales. Female and juvenile resemble male but lack the chestnut plumage.','Forest and mostly in urban areas.','Attracted to gardens located in high-rise buildings.',21.0,23.0,'pnr/resd','blue/brown','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',385,'White-throated Rock Thrush','Monticola gularis','Tarum Rengkung Putih','白喉矶鸫','Rarity','Va','Non-breeding male has rufous-chestnut lores/malar/rump/underparts, white throat/wing patch, bluish crown/nape and pale fringes on upperparts. Breeding male has no pale fringings. Female has mostly greyish-brown body with blackish bars on upperparts (except crown and tail), heavy blackish scales on underparts (except belly and vent), whitish throat/submoustachial stripe and small whitish patch behind ear-coverts. First winter resembles non-breeding adults.','Forest, secondary growth and suitable wooded area.','Forages on the floor of the forest, including along path and at the edge of quiet stretches of road through forest.',18.0,19.5,'fst','brown/black/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Chats, Old World Flycatchers (Muscicapidae)',386,'Amur Stonechat','Saxicola stejnegeri','Murai-Sawah Biasa','东亚石䳭','Rarity','M','Breeding male has black head, upperparts and wings, broad white patch on side of nape and neck, white wing patch, whitish rump and orange-rufous breast. Female has streaked crown, sandy-brown upperparts and unmarked buffish underparts with rufescent breast. Non-breeding male resembles female but black feather-bases visible on head-sides/throat and lores/chin often all black.','Grasslands and other open habitats.','Often sits atop an open perch, drops to ground to pick up food and returns to the same perch or one nearby.',14.0,14.0,'open','black/brown/white','ground/feed/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leafbirds (Chloropseidae)',387,'Greater Green Leafbird','Chloropsis sonnerati','Burung-Daun Besar','大绿叶鹎','Non-rarity','R','Male has all green plumage apart from black face and stout bill. Female resembles male but has green face and sharply demarcated yellow throat and eyering. Juvenile looks like female but has yellowish submoustachial band.','Forest and forest edge.','Complex vocalisations incorporating much mimicry.',20.5,22.5,'fst','green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leafbirds (Chloropseidae)',388,'Lesser Green Leafbird','Chloropsis cyanopogon','Burung-Daun Kecil','小绿叶鹎','Rarity','R','Male looks very similar to Greater Green Leafbird except that it is smaller and has a slim bill and yellowish borders surrounding black face. Female and juvenile are more easily distinguished from Greater Green Leafbird by all green plumage without yellowish throat and eyering.','Forest and forest edge.','Arboreal, frequenting thick foliage and canopy.',16.0,19.0,'fst','green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Leafbirds (Chloropseidae)',389,'Blue-winged Leafbird','Chloropsis moluccensis','Burung-Daun Biasa','蓝翅叶鹎','Non-rarity','R','Easily distinguished from other Leafbird species from the bluish wing patch and tail sides. Male also has distinctive yellowish border around black face and golden nape while female has bluish malar band and throat. Juvenile resembles female but lack any blue on face and malar area.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.','Feed on insects, berries and nectar.',16.5,18.5,'fst','blue/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Flowerpeckers (Dicaeidae)',390,'Scarlet-breasted Flowerpecker','Prionochilus thoracicus','Sepah-Puteri Belakang Kuning','赤胸锯齿啄花鸟','Rarity','Vi','Parrot-like bill that is stouter than in any other local flowerpeckers. Male has black head with a small red crown patch, bright red breast with black border, yellowish body and black wings and tail. Female has greyish head, whitish throat and yellowish underparts. Juvenile has more greyish-olive underparts than female.','Forest and secondary growth.','Mainly or completely frugivorous.',10.0,10.0,'fst','black/green/red','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Flowerpeckers (Dicaeidae)',391,'Thick-billed Flowerpecker','Dicaeum agile','Sepah-Puteri Ekor Salji Biasa','厚嘴啄花鸟','Rarity','Vi','Adults have brownish to olive-green upperparts, pale white underparts with dark streaks, reddish orange eyes, malar line and a dark thick bill. Juveniles have pink bills and faint streaks.','Broadleaved forest and forest edge.','Forages at the canopy of flowering and fruiting trees probably for mistletoes and small insects. Often observed twisting/jerking its tail when perched like it is dancing.',10.0,10.0,'fst','green/grey','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Flowerpeckers (Dicaeidae)',392,'Yellow-vented Flowerpecker','Dicaeum chrysorrheum','Sepah-Puteri Tongkeng Kuning','黄臀啄花鸟','Rarity','R','Differentiated from other flowerpecker species from the whitish loral stripe, yellowish-olive upperparts, mostly white underparts with bold blackish steaks and the distinctive orange-yellow undertail-coverts or vent. Juvenile display greyer underparts with duller streaks and pale yellow undertail-coverts.','Broadleaved forest and forest edge.','Know as a frugivore, in particular as a visitor to fig crops.',10.0,10.5,'fst','green/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Flowerpeckers (Dicaeidae)',393,'Orange-bellied Flowerpecker','Dicaeum trigonostigma','Sepah-Puteri Perut Jingga','橙腹啄花鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male is distinctive, and shows slaty-blue upperparts (crown/nape/wings/tail) except for a large triangular orange patch on the mantle. It has a fairly thin and short bill that is slightly curved downwards at the tip. Upper-breast and throat are a lighter greyish blue; from the lower breast to the vent is a gradient from fiery orange (on the lower breast) to yellow (on the vent). Female is much duller, and is mostly drab olive brown overall, except for its pale orange rump and yellow belly.','Forested area and forest edge.','Feeds on flowers and fruits.',9.0,9.0,'fst','orange/blue','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Flowerpeckers (Dicaeidae)',394,'Scarlet-backed Flowerpecker','Dicaeum cruentatum','Sepah-Puteri Belakang Merah','朱背啄花鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male looks distinctive with bright red upperparts, blackish head-/breast-sides and blue-blackish wings contrasting with the mostly white underparts. Female is a drab brown with a bright red rump and uppertail-coverts. Juvenile resembles female but has a red-pink based lower mandible and uniform upperparts with orange-tinged uppertail-coverts.','Parks, gardens, wooded areas, secondary growth and forest edge.','Feeds on flowers and fruits',8.5,9.0,'pnr/fst','white/blue/red','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',395,'Ruby-cheeked Sunbird','Chalcoparia singalensis','Kelicap Pipi Merah','紫颊直嘴太阳鸟','Rarity','Vi','Male resembles Brown-throated Sunbird with iridescent dark green upperparts but has iridescent copper-red ear-coverts, pale orange-rufous throat and upper-breast. Female can be distinguished from other sunbirds by its greenish-olive upperparts, pale orange-rufous throat and upper-breast and yellow belly.','Forest and mangroves.','Frequents the canopy and middle storey.',11.0,11.0,'fst/wet','blue/yellow','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',396,'Brown-throated Sunbird','Anthreptes malacensis','Kelicap Mayang Kelapa','褐喉食蜜鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has dull brownish head-sides and throat, glossy dark green upperparts with iridescent purple shoulder patch and yellow lower breast to vent. Female can be separated from other sunbirds by combination of robust shape, relatively straight bill and broken broad pale yellow eyering.','Parks, gardens, secondary growth, mangroves, forest and forest edge.','Frequents trees as well as low scrubs.',14.0,14.0,'pnr/fst','blue/yellow','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',397,'Van Hasselt''s Sunbird','Leptocoma brasiliana','Kelicap Belacan Biasa','蓝肩花蜜鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has distinctive iridescent green crown, purple throat and dark red lower breast and belly. Female can be separated from other sunbirds by combination of small size, dull olive-colored uppperparts, plain head and dull yellow underparts with olive-washed throat and upper breast.','Forests, forest edges, gardens, parks and mangroves.',NULL,10.0,10.0,'pnr/fst','red/black/blue','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',398,'Copper-throated Sunbird','Leptocoma calcostetha','Kelicap Bakau','铜喉花蜜鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male is relatively long-tailed with distinctive iridescent green crown, shoulder-patch and uppertail-coverts, iridescent copper-red throat, purple flanks and blackish lower breast/belly. Female can be separated from other sunbirds by combination of greyish crown and head-sides, white throat and longish tail with white-tipped outer feathers.','Mangroves','Keeps mainly to the upper and middle storeys.',14.0,14.0,'wet','red/black/blue','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',399,'Olive-backed Sunbird','Cinnyris jugularis','Kelicap Biasa','黄腹花蜜鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has plain olive-green upperparts, iridescent blue-black forehead, throat and breast and yellow belly and vent. Female can be separated from other sunbirds by combination of obvious down-curved bill, all yellow underparts and extensive white on tail.','Gardens, parks, mangroves, secondary growth and other wooded areas.',NULL,11.5,11.5,'pnr','blue/yellow/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',400,'Crimson Sunbird','Aethopyga siparaja','Kelicap Merah Biasa','黄腰太阳鸟','Non-rarity','R','Male has red head, mantle and upper breast, iridescent dark blue crown and tail, dark malar streak and greyish belly. Female is the dullest sunbird in Singapore with dull olive-coloured upperparts and slightly yellower-tinged underparts.','Forest, forest edge, mangroves, secondary growth, gardens and parks.',NULL,11.0,13.5,'pnr/fst','red/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',401,'Little Spiderhunter','Arachnothera longirostra','Kelicap-Jantung Kecil Biasa','长嘴捕蛛鸟','Non-rarity','R','Adult has slaty-grey head with broken whitish eyering and throat, dark moustachial stripe, yellow belly and dull olive upperparts. Juvenile resembles adult but has yellowish-olive tinged throat.','Forest and forest edge.','Frequents the lower storey and has a partiality for wild bananas and ginger.',16.0,16.5,'pnr/fst','yellow/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',402,'Thick-billed Spiderhunter','Arachnothera crassirostris','Kelicap-Jantung Paruh Tebal','厚嘴捕蛛鸟','Rarity','Vi','Adult resembles Little Spiderhunter but has thicker bill, greyish-olive throat and upper breast, broken yellowish eyering and no white tail-tip. Juvenile has greyer underparts.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.','Frequents canopy and upper mid-stratum of forest, making observation difficult.',16.5,17.0,'fst','yellow/brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Sunbirds (Nectariniidae)',403,'Yellow-eared Spiderhunter','Arachnothera chrysogenys','Kelicap-Jantung Telinga Berus','小黄耳捕蛛鸟','Rarity','Vi','Adult has olive upperparts, yellow underparts with dark breast streaks, incomplete yellow eyering and a distinctive yellow drooping splayed ear patch. Juvenile is smaller and lack the ear patch.','Forest, forest edge and secondary growth.','Frequents the forest canopy but will occasionally descend to feed on flowering shrubs.',18.0,18.0,'fst','yellow/green','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Sparrows, Snowfinches (Passeridae)',404,'Eurasian Tree Sparrow','Passer montanus','Pipit Rumah','麻雀','Non-rarity','R','Distinctive sparrow, sexes similar. Separated from much male House Sparrow by smaller size, browner underparts, chestnut cap, dark cheek patch. Female House Sparrow more drab, lacks bib, chestnut cap, and richer brown colouration of Eurasian Tree Sparrow.','Open habitat, including parks, urban areas, grasslands, and fields. Often associated with human presence.','Gregarious, associates in flocks. Primarily feeds on ground but also forages on plants and trees.',14.0,14.5,'pnr/fst','brown/black/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Old World Sparrows, Snowfinches (Passeridae)',405,'House Sparrow','Passer domesticus','Pipit Ubun Kelabu','家麻雀','Non-rarity','I','Male has grey crown, whitish head-sides contrasting with black mask, lores, chin, throat and upperbreast, broad chestnut band from eye to nape-sides, greyish-white underparts and dull chestnut mantle with pale brownish and blackish streaks. Female is rather nondescript brownish, with paler supercilium and underparts. Also resembles female weavers but lacks streaks on head and underparts.','Town and villages.','Roosts communally in buildings.',15.0,15.0,'resd','brown/black/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Weavers, Widowbirds (Ploceidae)',406,'Golden-backed Weaver','Ploceus jacksoni','Tempua Tudung Belakang Emas','苏丹金背织雀','Non-rarity','I','Male is bright yellow, with black head and chrome orange underparts. Female is dull yellow; told from Baya Weaver female by less prominent streaks on wings and more yellow than brown.','Grasslands.','Builds teardrop shaped nests, similar to Baya Weaver.',15.0,15.0,'open','yellow/black/orange',NULL);
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Weavers, Widowbirds (Ploceidae)',407,'Streaked Weaver','Ploceus manyar','Tempua-Asia Lorek','纹胸织雀','Non-rarity','I','Female and non-breeding male has distinctive blackish streaks on breast and flanks, yellowish-white supercilium and submoustachial stripe, yellowish neck-patch and boldly streaked upperparts and crown. Male in breeding plumage has blackish head-sides, yellow crown and broader blackish breast streakings. Juvenile resembles female but lack the yellowish parts.','Grasslands.','Gregarious, observed in mixed flocks with Baya Weavers.',13.5,13.5,'pnr','yellow/brown/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Weavers, Widowbirds (Ploceidae)',408,'Baya Weaver','Ploceus philippinus','Tempua-Asia Biasa','黄胸织雀','Non-rarity','R','Exhibits sexual dimorphism, males in breeding plumage with rich golden plumage and dark brown face, with females and non-breeding males exhibiting a drab sandy-brown plumage. Male Asian Golden Weaver has all yellow underparts compared to Baya Weaver, where the yellow is restricted to breast and mantle. Size of bill is also important for separating the two species, especially for females, with Baya Weaver having a slimmer bill than Asian Golden Weaver. Female Golden-backed Weaver has more yellow plumage overall and slimmer bill, with yellow-fringed coverts and flight feathers.','Open habitats including grassland, scrubland, fields.','Mainly granivorous but also feeds on other invertebrates and small vertebrates. Often breeds in colonies, with males initiating nest-building by using strips of leaves for weaving.',15.0,15.0,'pnr/fst','yellow/brown','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Waxbills, Munias & Allies (Estrildidae)',409,'Scaly-breasted Munia','Lonchura punctulata','Ciak-Padi Pinang','斑文鸟','Non-rarity','I/R','The introduced topela shows distinctive plumage pattern with brown upperparts contrasting with brownish scales on breast and flanks, chestnut-tinged head-sides and whitish centre of belly and vent. Local race fretensis has paler upperparts and bolder/blacker scaling below. Juvenile is duller and scales are either very faint or not visible.','Urban areas as well as cultivated lands, grasslands, scrub, secondary growth.','Highly gregarious and forages in small flocks, sometimes with other Munia species.',12.0,12.5,'pnr/resd','brown','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Waxbills, Munias & Allies (Estrildidae)',410,'White-rumped Munia','Lonchura striata','Ciak-Padi Tuli','白腰文鸟','Non-rarity','I/R','Adult is similar to Javan Munia but has darkish brown plumage with fine pale shaft-lines at mantle and diagnostic whitish rump and belly. Juvenile resembles adult but dark parts paler/browner and rump/belly buffy-tinged.','Grasslands, marshes, tall reeds/grasses (especially near water bodies).','Gregarious and feeds mainly on seeds and also algae.',11.0,11.5,'pnr/wet','white/black','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Waxbills, Munias & Allies (Estrildidae)',411,'Javan Munia','Lonchura leucogastroides','Ciak-Padi Jawa','黑喉文鸟','Non-rarity','I','Adult has black face, throat and upper breast, dark brown upperparts and strongly contrasting white underparts. Juvenile has brownish face, throat and upper breast and pale buffish belly. Resembles White-rumped Munia but lacks the whitish rump.','Various habitats including grasslands, marshes, mangroves, forest, secondary growth, gardens and parks.','Usually forage for seeds in grasslands but has also been observed searching tree foliage apparently not for seeds.',11.5,11.5,'fst/wet','brown/black/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Waxbills, Munias & Allies (Estrildidae)',412,'Chestnut Munia','Lonchura atricapilla','Ciak-Padi Rawa Biasa','栗腹文鸟','Non-rarity','I/R','Adult has black hood that contrasts strongly with deep chestnut body, bluish-grey bill and darker belly-center/vent. Difficult to distinguish juvenile from Scaly-breasted Munia and White-headed Munia.','Grassland.','Forages in large mixed flocks with Scaly-breated Munia and White-headed Munia.',11.0,11.5,'pnr','brown/black','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Waxbills, Munias & Allies (Estrildidae)',413,'White-headed Munia','Lonchura maja','Ciak-Padi Uban Barat','白头文鸟','Non-rarity','I/R','Adult has pale white head, vinous-brown collar, milk chocolate brown body, wings and tail with a large black belly patch. Difficult to distinguish juvenile from Scaly-breated Munia and Chestnut Munia.','Grassland','Forages in large mixed flocks with Scaly-breated Munia and Chestnut Munia.',11.5,11.5,'pnr','brown/white','trees');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Waxbills, Munias & Allies (Estrildidae)',414,'Red Avadavat','Amandava amandava','Ciak Merah','红梅花雀','Non-rarity','I','Breeding male has distinctive bright red plumage, with white spots along flanks and on feather tips. Female has brownish-grey plumage with white spots on feather tips, black lores, and red rump.','Grasslands, fields.','Gregarious, occurs in flocks. Feeds on seeds and other small invertebrates.',9.5,10.0,'pnr/fst','red/black','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',415,'Forest Wagtail','Dendronanthus indicus','Pipit-Rimba','山鹡鸰','Non-rarity','M','A highly distinctive wagtail, unlikely to be confused with other species. Note its black triangular patch on upper breast (forming a "bib"), and crescent-shaped greyish-black markings on outer breast. Upperparts are olive-green with two broad whitish-yellow wing-bars.','Forests, parkland, and mangroves.','Join large roosts with other wagtails – this has traditionally been observed at Yishun along with large numbers of Grey Wagtails.',17.0,18.0,'pnr','grey/black/white','branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',416,'Eastern Yellow Wagtail','Motacilla tschutschensis','Pipit-Batu Zaitun Timur','黄鹡鸰','Non-rarity','M','Amount of yellow on underparts variable, in non-breeding plumage generally has whitish underparts with greyish-brown upperparts. Individuals in breeding plumage observed in Singapore have grey cap and nape with all yellow throat and underparts. Compared to Grey Wagtail in non-breeding plumage, has dark legs, more olive or brownish mantle and lacks yellow rump.','Variety of open habitats with grass cover, has preference for moist or wet habitats.','Similar to other wagtails, forages on ground and wags tail while moving. Can be spotted in flight with undulating flight.',17.0,17.0,'pnr','yellow/grey','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',417,'Citrine Wagtail','Motacilla citreola','Pipit-Batu Kepala Kuning','黄头鹡鸰','Rarity','Va','Compared to Eastern Yellow Wagtail and Grey Wagtail, key feature to look out for in non-breeding individuals is the supercilium wrapping around ear coverts and connecting to throat, creating the appearance of a distinct, isolated "cheek patch".','Marshes, fields, and coastal habitats, prefers wet habitats.','Similar to other wagtails, forages on ground and wags tail while moving. Can be spotted in flight with undulating flight.',16.5,20.0,'wet/sea','yellow/grey','ground/feed');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',418,'Grey Wagtail','Motacilla cinerea','Pipit-Batu Pinggul Kuning','灰鹡鸰','Non-rarity','M','Non-breeding adult shows slaty-grey crown and upperparts, narrow whitish supercilium. Amount of yellow on underparts can be variable but generally retains bright yellow vent. Breeding male has all yellow underparts and distinctive black throat and upper breast. Juvenile resembles non-breeding adult but browner-tinged above. Compared to Eastern Yellow Wagtail in non-breeding plumage, has grey mantle, contrasting yellow rump and pinkish legs.','Fast flowing rocky streams and rivers, also wetlands and coasts in winter.','Feeds on a variety of aquatic invertebrates including adult flies, mayflies, beetles, crustacea and molluscs. Has the longest tail of the wagtails and its tail is wagged continually.',17.0,20.0,'wet','yellow//black/grey','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',419,'White Wagtail','Motacilla alba','Pipit-Batu Murai Erasia','白鹡鸰','Non-rarity','M','Very variable in plumage across range and subspecies, individuals in Singapore can exhibit plumage differences in face, coverts, mantle, and chin. Plumage is a mixture of black, white, and grey compared to other migrant wagtails which generally exhibit some yellow in their plumage and are warmer in colour.','Variety of habitats including open fields, storm drains, reservoir edges, seawalls.','Similar to other wagtails, forages on ground and wags tail while moving. Can be spotted in flight with undulating flight.',16.5,18.0,'wet','white/black','swim');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',420,'Paddyfield Pipit','Anthus rufulus','Apit-apit Biasa','田鹨','Non-rarity','R','Adult has mainly greyish-brown streaked upperparts, pale buff underparts with streaks around upper-breast and long bill/tail/legs.','Grassland and other open habitats.','Typically has weaker, more fluttering flight pattern than Richard''s and rarely hovers before landing.',15.0,16.0,'pnr','brown/white','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',421,'Tree Pipit','Anthus trivialis','Apit-apit Pokok Barat','林鹨','Rarity','Va','Underparts: Well marked narrow black streaks across the chest/breast on a warm buff base. Streaks do not extend strongly onto the flanks. Upperparts: warm buff/brown, with dark centred feathers giving a well marked, but not strongly contrasting, appearance. A well marked row of greater primary coverts were slightly darker centred and paler fringed than surrounding feathers, producing a clear (but not bold) wing bar.','Open woodland, scrub and grass.','Spends most time walking through long grass foraging for invertebrates with a horizontal gait and occasionally giving gentle tail pumps (which is also a feature of Olive-backed Pipit). Flies with a strong bounding flight into mid-canopy of trees where it would perch, rest and preen before returning to feeding on the ground.',15.0,16.5,'open','brown/black/white','ground/feed/branch');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',422,'Olive-backed Pipit','Anthus hodgsoni','Apit-apit Pokok Timur','树鹨','Rarity','Va','Resembles Red-throated Pipit but has plain greenish-olive upperparts, broad whitish supercilium and lacks the pinkish-red head-sides and throat.','Wooded area.','Eats mainly insects, but takes some seeds, especially outside the nesting season. Forages ground or in low trees.',16.0,17.0,'pnr/fst','black/green','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Wagtails, Pipits (Motacillidae)',423,'Red-throated Pipit','Anthus cervinus','Apit-apit Rengkung Merah','红喉鹨','Rarity','M','Adult is characterised by heavily streaked upperparts with prominent streaked back, rump and uppertail-coverts, prominent blackish streaks/spotting on breasts and flanks and pinkish-red head-sides, throat and upper breast. Reddish coloration on head tend to be less extensive on autumn/winter birds and females and completely lacking in juveniles.','Grasslands and open habitats, often near water.','Forages by walking along ground, pecking at a variety of insects and occasional seeds.',15.0,16.5,'pnr/wet','black/white/orange','ground');
INSERT INTO "Birds" VALUES ('Buntings (Emberizidae)',424,'Black-headed Bunting','Emberiza melanocephala','Pipit-Belukar Besar','黑头鹀','Rarity','Va','Challenging to separate females and juveniles from Red-headed Bunting (Emberiza bruniceps), features that have been used to separate the two include the degree of crown streaking (more streaked), rump colour (less yellow), bill structure (larger), and primary projection (longer).','Found in open habitats with dense vegetation, including open fields and scrub forests.','Feeds on invertebrates and plant material, typically forages on ground or low in vegetation.',15.5,17.5,'fst/open','brown/white','ground/feed');
